Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.19,0:00:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,1957年10月 苏联将\N{\rE}In October 1957, the Soviet Union launched
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.57,0:00:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,世界上第一颗人造卫星 斯普特尼克1号送入轨道\N{\rE}the world's first artificial satellite, Sputnik 1, into orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.95,0:00:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,这一成就加剧了美苏两国之间的太空竞赛\N{\rE}Their achievement fueled a space race between the United States and the Soviets.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.08,0:00:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,之后发生了什么 人们说法不一\N{\rE}There has been some debate about what followed,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.00,0:00:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\bord0\fs28\b1}登  月  大  计  划
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.00,0:00:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs21}本WEB版外挂字幕由  {\c&H9B30FF&}风吹来的那片云{\c&HFFFFFF&}  双语合并
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.83,0:00:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,但我亲身经历过 所以接下来讲的都是真事 基本上是吧\N{\rE}but I was there, and this is the real story. Mostly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.88,0:00:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,直到两天前\N{\rE}Until two days ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.17,0:00:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上的人才头一次听到这个声音\N{\rE}that sound had never been heard on this earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.09,0:00:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,(苏联人将卫星送进太空)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.51,0:01:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,(《生活》 太空竞赛)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.35,0:01:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,(美国卫星一败涂地)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.22,0:01:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,美国尝试发射自己的卫星 结果惨不忍睹\N{\rE}America attempted to launch her satellite with disastrous results.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.77,0:01:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,(美国火箭计划启动失败)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.06,0:01:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,(第一个进入太空的人)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.19,0:01:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,苏联成功地将一个人送入太空 并把他活着带回地球\N{\rE}The Soviet Union has sent a man into space and brought him back alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.61,0:01:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,苏联人在全世界范围内\N{\rE}The Soviets made the most of the flight
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.57,0:01:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,大肆宣传这次航天行动 其国内自然也是举国欢庆\N{\rE}in their worldwide propaganda. Naturally, there was jubilation in Russia.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.37,0:01:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,在认识到苏联人取得领先后\N{\rE}Recognizing the head start obtained by the Soviets,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.08,0:01:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为我国应致力于实现一个目标\N{\rE}I believe that this nation should commit itself to achieving the goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.50,0:01:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,即在这个十年内\N{\rE}before this decade is out,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.63,0:01:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,把一个人送上月球并让他安全返回地球\N{\rE}of landing a man on the moon and returning him safely to the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.30,0:01:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,(美国宇航员环绕地球飞行)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.61,0:01:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我们选择在这个十年登月\N{\rE}We choose to go to the moon in this decade
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.57,0:01:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,并完成其他壮举 不是因为这个目标轻而易举\N{\rE}and do the other things, not because they are easy,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.78,0:01:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,而是因为它困难重重\N{\rE}but because they are hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.49,0:02:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,因为这个挑战是我们愿意接受\N{\rE}Because that challenge is one that we are willing to accept,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.03,0:02:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,不愿推迟 并准备大获全胜的\N{\rE}one we are unwilling to postpone, and one we intend to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.83,0:02:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,指挥飞行员 一 二 三 四 五\N{\rE}Command Pilot. One, two, three, four, five.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.00,0:02:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,五 四 三 二 一\N{\rE}Five, four, three, two, one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.33,0:02:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,着火了\N{\rE}Flame!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.17,0:02:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,驾驶舱里失火了\N{\rE}We've got a fire in the cockpit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.38,0:02:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,快出去 我们要烧死了\N{\rE}Let's get out! We're burning up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.46,0:02:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,宇航员维吉尔格里森 爱德华怀特 和罗杰查菲不幸遇难\N{\rE}Astronauts Virgil Grissom, Edward White and Roger Chaffee have been killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.64,0:02:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,媒体官员称 因为此次悲剧事件\N{\rE}Press officials say because of the tragedy,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.72,0:02:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波罗1号飞行任务将被无限期推迟\N{\rE}the Apollo 1 flight has now been postponed indefinitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.14,0:02:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我...登月之旅很有吸引力\N{\rE}I-- It's, uh-- It's a groovy trip,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.93,0:02:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,但在美国 还有很多更重要的事情要先做\N{\rE}but there are a lot more important things to do first in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.60,0:02:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,也许把这些事情都搞定了 我们才能登月\N{\rE}Maybe when all that's taken care of, we can afford to go to the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.44,0:02:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我们发现自己物质丰富 士气低下\N{\rE}We find ourselves rich in goods but ragged in spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.07,0:02:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,雄心勃勃地想要登月\N{\rE}Reaching with magnificent precision for the moon
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.82,0:02:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,却在地球上陷入一片混乱\N{\rE}but falling into raucous discord on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.07,0:02:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们想要和平 却被卷入战争\N{\rE}We are caught at war wanting peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.20,0:02:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我们想要团结 却四分五裂\N{\rE}We're torn by division wanting unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.70,0:02:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,这个巨大的土星号火箭\N{\rE}This giant Saturn rocket
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.46,0:02:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,(国家航空航天局预算削减)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.54,0:02:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,以及这里的其他设备 最初都是这场竞赛的一部分\N{\rE}and the rest of the equipment here began as part of a race
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.46,0:02:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,为的是战胜苏联人 它们肩负着\N{\rE}to beat the Russians with the national goal
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.71,0:02:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我国在这个十年内把人类送上月球的目标\N{\rE}of putting a man on the moon in this decade.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.34,0:03:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,但登月之旅的花费将超出所有人的预期\N{\rE}But their trip will cost more than anyone thought it would.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.72,0:03:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,而在1960年代成功登月的几率愈加渺茫\N{\rE}And their chances of landing on the moon in the 1960s are increasingly slim.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.56,0:03:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,(国家航空航天局)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.08,0:03:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,斯图 你当主管第一周 听着情况不妙啊\N{\rE}First week as manager, Stu. Doesn't sound like it's going great.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.37,0:03:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,要么是计量表不准 要么是某个储存罐漏了\N{\rE}So either our meters are off or there's a breach in one of the tanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.42,0:03:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,但这种情况没有规程 我们也找不到泄漏源头\N{\rE}But there's no protocol for this. And we can't source the leak
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.38,0:03:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- 因为是液态... - 液态氢\N{\rE}- because it's liquid hyd-- - Liquid hydrogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.92,0:03:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,它是无色无味的 所有人都出去 快\N{\rE}It's colorless and odorless. Everybody out! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.34,0:03:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,里德 凯尔 放下铅笔\N{\rE}Reed, Kyle, pencils down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.92,0:03:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,可能已经在燃烧了 我们却不知情 找门出去\N{\rE}It could be burning, and we wouldn't know it. Find a door.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.34,0:03:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,快 跑起来 别慢吞吞的\N{\rE}Come on! Run, run! No walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.73,0:03:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,他在干什么 打扫吗\N{\rE}What's he doing? Is he cleaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.02,0:03:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,不...这是...一种检查泄漏的老办法\N{\rE}No, no. It's an-- It's an old-school leak detection process.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.98,0:03:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,他用的是把扫帚\N{\rE}It's a broom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.74,0:04:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,斯图 你很聪明的 再想想 干麦秆加上液态氢等于...\N{\rE}Stu, you're better than this. Come on. Straw plus liquid hydrogen equals...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.16,0:04:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,好 没事了 别担心了 来吧\N{\rE}All right, we're good! Don't worry about it. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.08,0:04:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我们还有工作呢 快点\N{\rE}We got work to do. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.09,0:04:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,新的规程是用扫帚检查泄漏\N{\rE}Uh, the new protocol is the broom method.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.06,0:04:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要一把新扫帚\N{\rE}We need a new broom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.02,0:04:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我刚才真以为他死了\N{\rE}I for sure thought he was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.48,0:04:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托\N{\rE}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.82,0:04:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,这还是你上次发脾气时弄坏的\N{\rE}It's still broke from the last time you were in a mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.20,0:04:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 我能看出来\N{\rE}Yeah, I can see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.91,0:04:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- 波音又来电话了 - 亨利 打给议会 别找我\N{\rE}- Boeing called again. - Call Congress, Henry, not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.08,0:04:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有他们的电话号码\N{\rE}I don't have their number.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.29,0:04:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,每天...这里都有东西坏掉\N{\rE}Every day, every day, something is breaking around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.79,0:05:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,或者爆炸 我们资金不足 人手不足\N{\rE}Or blowing up. We're underfunded, under-- understaffed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.92,0:05:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,但没错 他们还期望我们吊打苏联人\N{\rE}But yeah, we're still expected to beat the pants off the Russians.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.26,0:05:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你能告诉我到底该怎么做到吗\N{\rE}You mind telling me how the hell we're supposed to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.76,0:05:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,就从善待自动售货机开始吧\N{\rE}Could start by being a little nicer to the vending machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.01,0:05:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,快看 在那里\N{\rE}Ooh! There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.52,0:05:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么  - 有一只猫\N{\rE}- What? - There's a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.43,0:05:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- 那又怎么了  - 是一只黑猫 亨利 代表霉运\N{\rE}So what? - It's a black cat, Henry. It's bad luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.94,0:05:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 不见了\N{\rE}- Okay, it's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.86,0:05:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好 谢天谢地 - 好吧 我们走\N{\rE}- All right. Thank God. - Okay. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.70,0:05:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- 叫保安 - 不要\N{\rE}- Call security. - I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.24,0:05:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我不叫 这... - 你要去叫\N{\rE}- I will not. It-- - Yes, you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.57,0:05:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我们这里最不该出现的就是一只黑猫\N{\rE}The last thing that we need around here is a black cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.24,0:05:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,保安又不管这种事\N{\rE}They don't deal with things like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.20,0:05:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,他们管的 现在管了\N{\rE}Yes, they do. They do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.91,0:05:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你反应过头了 - 不 是你反应迟钝\N{\rE}- Y-You're overreacting. - No, you're not overreacting enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.96,0:05:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,立刻叫保安 马上去\N{\rE}Call 'em right now. Right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.39,0:05:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我看起来如何\N{\rE}How do I look?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.64,0:05:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,容光焕发 加油\N{\rE}You're glowing. Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.90,0:06:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,下午好 小伙子们\N{\rE}Good afternoon, boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.11,0:06:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,走错房间了 亲爱的 我们不需要笔录\N{\rE}Wrong room, sweetheart. We don't need dictation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.98,0:06:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我叫凯莉琼斯 今天的会议由我主持\N{\rE}I'm Kelly Jones. I'll be running the meeting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.94,0:06:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你们一定是菲尔亨利 尼尔布朗和...\N{\rE}You must be Phil Hunley, Neil Brown and--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.62,0:06:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,扎克坦纳 不介意我坐下吧\N{\rE}Zack Tanner. You don't mind if I sit down, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.83,0:06:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,恕我直言 琼斯太太 我们是一家进步的公司\N{\rE}Uh, all due respect, Mrs. Jones, we're a progressive company.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.95,0:06:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的速记员团队有16名女性\N{\rE}We employ 16 women in our steno pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.66,0:06:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我们向男人出售跑车 出售300马力...\N{\rE}We're selling sports cars to men. We're selling a 300 horsepower--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.75,0:06:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,355马力 你们卖的是7014CC排量 V8引擎的猛兽\N{\rE}355, 428 cubic inch V-8 beast is what you're selling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.80,0:06:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你们要着重推销车的速度 比如这个\N{\rE}You want to focus on the car's speed. Something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.89,0:06:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,眼熟吗 雪佛兰科迈罗 庞蒂亚克火鸟 还有奥斯莫比尔\N{\rE}Look familiar? Chevy Camaro. Pontiac Firebird. And Oldsmobile.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.60,0:06:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,都是上个月的\N{\rE}All from last month.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.98,0:06:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,幸好你们有些竞争对手没有的东西\N{\rE}Thankfully, you have something that your competition doesn't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.06,0:06:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,野马Fastback “给他355马力 给家人安全带”\N{\rE}The Mustang Fastback. "355 horses for him. Seat belts for the family."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.74,0:06:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,安全带 我们安装安全带 只是因为明年可能会有强制安装的规定\N{\rE}The seat belts? We only put them in because they might be mandatory next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.86,0:06:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我们来做个游戏吧\N{\rE}Let's play a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.95,0:06:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我来猜你们几位先生分别驾驶什么车\N{\rE}Now I'm gonna guess what kind of car each one of you gentlemen drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.62,0:07:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,扎克 1966年款福特野马敞篷车 罂粟红色的\N{\rE}Zack, Ford Mustang '66 convertible. It's poppy red.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.67,0:07:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,不过你们当了老公的人不会开野马 尼尔开林肯大陆\N{\rE}Oh, no Mustangs for you husbands though. A Lincoln Continental for Neil.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.68,0:07:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,可怜的菲尔开客货两用车 菲尔 你知道我每天什么时候最开心吗\N{\rE}A station wagon for poor Phil. Oh, Phil. You know what the best part of my day is?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.69,0:07:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,是我老公查理晚上回家时\N{\rE}When my husband Charlie comes home at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.98,0:07:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我无法想象他有一天晚上不回家会怎样\N{\rE}I can't even imagine what it would be like if-if one night he-- he didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.78,0:07:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你来想象一下这段对话\N{\rE}- Now imagine the conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.70,0:07:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,如果有人跟你老婆说这辆车\N{\rE}if someone told your wife that this car,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.96,0:07:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,拥有355马力和169公里的最高时速\N{\rE}its 355 horses and 105 top speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.67,0:07:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,正是这辆车每天晚上 载着她老公安全回到家人身边\N{\rE}this car is what brings her husband home safe to her family every night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.51,0:07:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,她希望你拥有这辆车\N{\rE}Now she wants you to have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.34,0:07:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,她说出每个已婚男士梦想听到的话\N{\rE}She says the words every married man dreams of hearing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.14,0:07:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“如果你买下这辆野马\N{\rE}"I'd feel so much better
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.64,0:08:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我会感觉比现在更幸福 亲爱的”\N{\rE}if you bought yourself that Mustang, sweetheart."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.65,0:08:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么猜到他们开什么车的\N{\rE}How did you guess what kind of cars they drive?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.45,0:08:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,贿赂了他们的秘书还是怎样\N{\rE}What, bribe their secretaries or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.66,0:08:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉 真的假的\N{\rE}Kelly, seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.66,0:08:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,两包维珍妮牌女士香烟和一瓶帕科香水\N{\rE}Two packs of Virginia Slims and a bottle of Paco Rabanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.20,0:08:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,每个人都是有价的\N{\rE}Everyone has their price.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.12,0:08:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,幸好刚才我的羊水没破 天啊\N{\rE}I'm just lucky that my water didn't break in there. Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.04,0:08:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨 罗恩 你老婆好吗\N{\rE}Hi, Ron. How's the wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.50,0:08:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,(创意总监 凯莉琼斯)
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.25,0:08:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 假肚子只能干洗\N{\rE}Now, the baby bump, dry-clean only.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.59,0:08:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,好的 我记下了 还有 欧米茄确认了下周的安排\N{\rE}Yes, I have that noted. A-Also, Omega confirmed for next week,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.09,0:08:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我完成了芭斯罗缤的画\N{\rE}I finished the Baskin-Robbins artwork,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.30,0:08:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Palmex那个人问你的地址 想给你送玫瑰\N{\rE}and that guy from Palmex asked for your address to send roses,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.01,0:08:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,但我给了他我的 我知道\N{\rE}but I gave him mine because I know
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.22,0:08:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你对玫瑰的看法 - 你知道我对玫瑰的看法\N{\rE}- how you feel about roses. - You know how I feel about roses.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.39,0:08:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,还有 约翰又来电了 他想在星期二带你去吃晚餐\N{\rE}Also, John called. Again. He wants to take you to dinner Tuesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.77,0:08:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉他我搬到洛杉矶去了 给陶氏化学的布鲁斯打电话\N{\rE}Tell him I moved to LA. And call Bruce from Dow Chemical.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.48,0:08:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我听说他们在给密保诺密封袋找新代理\N{\rE}I hear they're looking for a new agency for Ziploc.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.90,0:08:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,人们应该抵制陶氏化学 他们做凝固汽油弹\N{\rE}People should be boycotting Dow. They make napalm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.90,0:08:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,人们嘴上说着抵制 但还是在买装三文治的袋子\N{\rE}People say they're boycotting, but they're still buying sandwich bags.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.03,0:08:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,他们还卖保鲜膜和泡沫塑料\N{\rE}They also sell Saran Wrap and Styrofoam.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.91,0:09:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你认为人们会停止使用泡沫塑料吗  你的咖啡用什么装的\N{\rE}Think people are going to stop using Styrofoam? What's your coffee in?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.91,0:09:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 我知道你和你的朋友们想拯救世界\N{\rE}Now, I know you and your friends want to save the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.62,0:09:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,但等到你在1984年当上这里的主管\N{\rE}and by the time you're running this place in 1984,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.17,0:09:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,世上已经没有核弹 全体人类平权了\N{\rE}there's gonna be no nukes and equal rights for all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.00,0:09:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,但在那之前 我们得干好本职工作\N{\rE}But until then, we've got a job to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.71,0:09:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉...我们有大麻烦了\N{\rE}Kelly! Kelly! Kelly. Kelly. We've got a big problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.93,0:09:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我刚刚愤怒地离开片场 对 我有充分的理由\N{\rE}I just stormed off set, and, yes, it was justified.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.56,0:09:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我没法跟胡佛这些人合作\N{\rE}I cannot work with these Hoover people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.14,0:09:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,显然他们对我给他们拍广告的方式有意见\N{\rE}Apparently, they have issues with the way that I am shooting their commercial.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.65,0:09:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,他们真是这么说的 “他们的” 那可是我的广告\N{\rE}They actually said that. "Their." It's my commercial.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.86,0:09:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,不就是做吸尘器的嘛 我可是搞艺术的\N{\rE}They make vacuums. I make art.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.53,0:09:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- 抱歉 我们约了见面吗  - 没有...\N{\rE}- Sorry, did we have a meeting set? - No. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.40,0:09:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,不好意思 我没意识到还得约时间\N{\rE}I'm sorry. I didn't realize I had to set a time
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.32,0:09:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,才能跟最亲爱的朋友说话\N{\rE}to speak to one of my dearest friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.82,0:09:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,上次我们说话时你把我炒了 我现在不为你工作了\N{\rE}The last time we spoke, you fired me. And I don't work for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.24,0:09:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我跟你讲 凯莉 我不是来听你训斥的\N{\rE}You know what, Kelly, I didn't come in here to be berated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.54,0:09:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我是来找你支持我的\N{\rE}I came in to be agreed with!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.62,0:09:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你十分钟后要向雀巢推销 这很重要\N{\rE}You have that Nestlé pitch in ten. Very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.33,0:09:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,骗人的 再见\N{\rE}- That is a lie. Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.21,0:09:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,兰斯 给你拿到这份导演工作 堪称圣诞奇迹\N{\rE}Lance, getting you this directing gig was a Christmas miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.96,0:09:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你搞砸了那个果冻广告拍摄后 我用了三周时间\N{\rE}It took me three weeks to convince them that you were stable
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.55,0:09:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,才说服他们你并非喜怒无常\N{\rE}- after your Jell-O shoot from hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.05,0:09:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,果冻广告那事不怪我\N{\rE}Jell-O was not my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.34,0:10:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- 那个演员... - 才五岁 你把他弄哭了\N{\rE}- Ugh. That actor wa-- - Was five. You made him cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.97,0:10:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我是帮了那孩子一把 好莱坞可不好混\N{\rE}Well, I did that child a favor. Hollywood is no cakewalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.43,0:10:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,那亨氏食品广告呢 你超了预算四万块 只是个番茄酱广告而已\N{\rE}What about the Heinz commercial? You went 40,000 over budget. It was about ketchup.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.56,0:10:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,才不是 重点是番茄酱带来的希望\N{\rE}It was not about ketchup. It was about the promise of ketchup.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.86,0:10:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,没有人看到我在为他们的产品做什么\N{\rE}No one sees what I'm doing for their products.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.23,0:10:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我在提升产品价值\N{\rE}I am elevating them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.49,0:10:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在应该在拍电影了\N{\rE}I should be in film by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.86,0:10:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我拒绝了执导《娃娃谷》的机会\N{\rE}I passed on directing Valley of the Dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.53,0:10:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- 那事怪我 但我还是该拍电影 - 好了 我们是怎么称呼你的\N{\rE}- That is on me, but still. - Now, what do we call you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.66,0:10:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- 广告界的库布里克 好了 - 天啊 斯坦利是半吊子\N{\rE}- The Kubrick of commercials. All right. - Oh, my God. Stanley is a hack.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.46,0:10:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,拍出一部好电影就突然成了天才\N{\rE}He does one good movie, and suddenly he's a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.50,0:10:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你是传奇 好吗 创意天才\N{\rE}You are a legend, right? Creative genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.04,0:10:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,但你也脾气暴躁 反复无常 永远不能按预算拍摄\N{\rE}You're also hotheaded, mercurial and can't stick to a budget for shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.63,0:10:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢 - 这不是夸你\N{\rE}- Oh, thank you. - That wasn't a compliment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.51,0:10:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这时就该当耳旁风 - 你若不跟胡佛合作 以后就没人请你了\N{\rE}- It is when you stop listening. - If you quit Hoover, you'll be unhirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.76,0:10:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rE}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.60,0:10:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,兰斯 不如你回片场吧\N{\rE}Lance, why don't you march your ass back to set,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.35,0:10:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,不管发什么脾气 都道个歉 好吗\N{\rE}and you apologize for whatever fit you threw, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.10,0:10:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,给你男朋友买个棒棒的圣诞礼物 谢谢他容忍你\N{\rE}Buy your boyfriend something nice for Christmas for putting up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.94,0:10:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,也给我买个礼物 好吗\N{\rE}Get something for me too, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.31,0:10:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- 圣诞快乐 兰斯 - 圣诞快乐\N{\rE}Merry Christmas, Lance. - Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.86,0:10:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,请你给我找份像样的工作 好吗\N{\rE}Can you get me a decent job, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.28,0:11:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波罗8号于今早成功发射\N{\rE}Apollo 8 launched successfully this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.70,0:11:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,(阿波罗8号发射录影)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.83,0:11:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,这场胜利是国家航空航天局的及时雨 在越南方面 今天有更多人牺牲\N{\rE}A much needed win for NASA. In Vietnam, more men were lost today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.54,0:11:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,二千五百万公里...\N{\rE}...and 15 million miles...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.38,0:11:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,麻烦再来一杯 另外把晚餐菜单拿给我\N{\rE}I'll have another round, please, and a look at the dinner menu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.96,0:11:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好的 女士 - 谢谢\N{\rE}- Yes, ma'am. - Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.47,0:11:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,今晚有两个特色菜 鸡肉馅饼和洛克菲勒牡蛎\N{\rE}Two specials tonight. Chicken potpie and Oysters Rockefeller.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.60,0:11:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我们吃鸡好了 她对牡蛎过敏\N{\rE}We'll do the chicken. She's allergic to oysters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.93,0:11:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,给我来一杯麦卡伦 一个柠檬和一个砧板\N{\rE}And I'll take a shot of Macallan, a lemon and a cutting board.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.89,0:11:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好的 先生 - 不好意思 我认识你吗\N{\rE}- Yes, sir. - Oh, I'm sorry. Do I know you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.57,0:11:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,跑车上装安全带 这个点子很不错\N{\rE}Seat belts in a sports car. I mean, that's a great angle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.86,0:11:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,很不幸 他们即将停止跟你合作\N{\rE}Unfortunately, they're about to kill the account.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.91,0:11:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么\N{\rE}Why would they do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.12,0:11:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,因为有人告诉他们 你肚子里其实没孩子\N{\rE}Because someone told them that you don't really have a bun in the oven.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.21,0:11:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,菲尔 让我解释一下\N{\rE}Phil. Let me explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.00,0:11:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我以后再也不会相信女人了\N{\rE}That's the last time I trust a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.55,0:12:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我还给你送了一份婴儿礼物\N{\rE}I actually sent you a baby gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.76,0:12:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你那么做非常贴心 请让我...\N{\rE}Which was so sweet, by the way. Let me just--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.68,0:12:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,尼尔 让我解释一下 如果你们...\N{\rE}Neil, let-let me explain. If you--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.72,0:12:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么回事 你为谁工作 奥美广告\N{\rE}What is this? Who do you work for, Ogilvy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.81,0:12:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你业绩拼不过我 就害我被解雇\N{\rE}Huh? You can't outsell me, so you got me fired?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.68,0:12:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,恰恰相反 我想聘请你\N{\rE}Just the opposite. I wanna hire you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.40,0:12:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我叫莫伯克斯 在总统办公室工作\N{\rE}Name's Moe Berkus. I work for the president's office.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.57,0:12:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,哪家公司的\N{\rE}Of what company?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.86,0:12:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,美国总统\N{\rE}The president.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.45,0:12:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要一位营销专家 听说你是最厉害的\N{\rE}We need a, uh, marketing specialist, and word has it you are the very best.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.46,0:12:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,于是我做了些调研 发现...\N{\rE}So I did a little digging, and, uh--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.25,0:12:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你的经历很有趣 凯莉\N{\rE}You have quite a colorful past, Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.96,0:12:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,还是说我该叫你简 来自芝加哥的空姐\N{\rE}Or should I call you Jane? Stewardess from Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.84,0:12:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,也许你更喜欢被称为艾米 俄亥俄州的护士\N{\rE}Or perhaps you would prefer Amy, the nurse from Ohio.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.43,0:12:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,有这么漂亮的脸蛋 谁还会看推荐信\N{\rE}Face like that, who's gonna check references?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.85,0:12:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你找的那一页不在这里\N{\rE}Page you're looking for isn't in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.40,0:13:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道你在说什么\N{\rE}I don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.24,0:13:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你当然不知道 我懂\N{\rE}Oh, sure you don't. And I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.74,0:13:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 我也有几十个身份证 我的真名也不叫莫\N{\rE}Hey, I have dozens of IDs, and my real name's not Moe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.70,0:13:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,有那么多名字可以选 你却挑了“莫”\N{\rE}With all the names you could've picked, you landed on Moe?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.66,0:13:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,你天赋出众\N{\rE}You have singular talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.21,0:13:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,可以用来成就更伟大的事业 何必浪费在卖车上呢\N{\rE}Why waste it selling cars when you can think bigger?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.80,0:13:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,莫 有什么公司比福特更伟大\N{\rE}Well, Moe, what's bigger than Ford?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.05,0:13:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你去过佛罗里达州吗\N{\rE}You ever been to Florida?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.23,0:13:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他们想让你推销月球  - 月球 阿波罗任务\N{\rE}- They want you to sell the moon? - The moon. The Apollo mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.48,0:13:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,一整套\N{\rE}The whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.06,0:13:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这个叫莫的家伙为国家航空航天局做事\N{\rE}And this Moe guy works for NASA?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.07,0:13:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,对 不 算是吧 他是政府的人\N{\rE}Yeah. I mean, y-- Well, no. Um, kind of. He-He-He works for the government.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.95,0:13:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,哪个部门\N{\rE}Oh, which part?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.78,0:13:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉\N{\rE}Kelly?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.91,0:13:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这个人...我们在为理查德尼克松工作\N{\rE}Does this guy-- Are we working for Richard Nixon?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.79,0:13:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我才不会为理查德尼克松工作 凯莉\N{\rE}Because, Kelly, I will not work for Richard Nixon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.29,0:14:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我是持证女权主义者 我真的有证\N{\rE}I'm a card-carrying feminist. I actually have a card.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.34,0:14:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我甚至不相信他要当总统了\N{\rE}I can't even believe he's going to be president.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.21,0:14:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我本来不知道自己对美国有这么多意见\N{\rE}I had no idea I disagreed with this much of the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.80,0:14:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我们为国家航空航天局工作 推销月球 没人对月球有意见\N{\rE}We are working for NASA to sell the moon. Nobody disagrees about the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.43,0:14:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,不是 你我都清楚\N{\rE}- No. You and I both know
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.22,0:14:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我们身边每天都有可怕的事发生\N{\rE}that everywhere around us every day something terrible is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.39,0:14:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,无所不在\N{\rE}- Everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.56,0:14:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,除了太空\N{\rE}Except in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.06,0:14:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- 真讨厌 你说动我了 - 他们绝对需要我们的帮助\N{\rE}- I hate that this is working on me. - They definitely need our help.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.11,0:14:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道国家航空航天局的头29次任务 只有48%的成功率吗\N{\rE}Did you know of NASA's first 29 missions, only 48% have been successful?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.99,0:14:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这不可能 太离谱了\N{\rE}That can't be. That's crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.36,0:14:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道可可海滩市的 男女比例是五比一吗 天啊\N{\rE}Did you know the ratio of men to women in Cocoa Beach is 5-to-1? [chuckles] Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.37,0:14:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,只要你给我们找的住处不在兄弟会街就行\N{\rE}As long as you got us a quiet place that's not on Frat Row.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.21,0:14:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,指南手册说那里很古雅\N{\rE}The-- The guidebook said it's quaint.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.13,0:14:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,(卫星汽车旅馆 客满)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.10,0:14:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,你被炒鱿鱼了\N{\rE}You're fired.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.06,0:14:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,这些都是什么人啊\N{\rE}Who are all these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.27,0:15:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,今天星期三 他们好像在另一个星球上\N{\rE}It is a Wednesday. It's like they're on a different planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.85,0:15:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,这里叫佛罗里达\N{\rE}They call it Florida.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.77,0:15:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,请告诉我你订了一个远离游泳池的房间\N{\rE}Please tell me you booked a room away from the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.37,0:15:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- 16 21 - 天气\N{\rE}...sixteen and 21... Weather!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.41,0:15:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,明天晴间多云\N{\rE}...Clear to partly cloudy tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.62,0:15:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,(佛罗里达州 可可海滩)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.71,0:15:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,下午及傍晚 局部地区有雷阵雨\N{\rE}A few isolated thundershowers during the afternoon and early evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.17,0:15:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,今晚最低气温18至24摄氏度\N{\rE}A low tonight, 65 to 75.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.54,0:15:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,目前月球火箭发射场周边城市 气温25摄氏度\N{\rE}Currently 77 in the Moonport cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.84,0:15:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是KO2020电台 为你带来的体育新闻和天气预报\N{\rE}That's KO twenty-twenty news, sports and weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.63,0:15:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,WKKO\N{\rE}WKKO--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.34,0:15:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,(沃尔菲餐厅)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.73,0:15:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- 嗨 乔 - 晚上好 科尔 来点什么\N{\rE}- Hey, Joe. - Evening, Cole. What'll it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.69,0:15:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,黑咖啡\N{\rE}Coffee. Black.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.69,0:15:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,再来点最快能打包带走的吃的 朋友\N{\rE}And whatever takes the least amount of time to put in a bag, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.23,0:16:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,小姐 你很惹火\N{\rE}Uh, miss, you're on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.02,0:16:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,真有创意\N{\rE}Very original.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.23,0:16:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,得了 我不想跟你玩干柴烈火\N{\rE}No, I do not wanna stop, drop and roll with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.40,0:16:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,不是 你的书着火了\N{\rE}No, your book is on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.86,0:16:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊\N{\rE}God.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.24,0:16:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好 没事的... - 我的天\N{\rE}- All right. All right. All right. - Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.57,0:16:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- 抱歉 谢谢你 我只是... - 教你个经验法则\N{\rE}- I'm sorry. Thank you. I just-- - Just as a rule of thumb,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.33,0:16:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,酒精和火焰 绝配\N{\rE}alcohol and flames, they-- they like each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.54,0:16:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,是 天啊 我把你的外套烧坏了\N{\rE}Yeah. Oh, gosh. I-I-I ruined your jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.50,0:16:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,没事 这衣服跟我出生入死\N{\rE}No, this thing's seen worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.83,0:16:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- 经历过千锤百炼 - 请你喝一杯补偿你吧\N{\rE}- Been through worse. - Let me buy a drink for your troubles.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.92,0:16:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不必了 - 必须的\N{\rE}- That's not necessary. - I insist.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.09,0:16:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我不喝酒 没关系\N{\rE}I don't drink. It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.59,0:16:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,真的 不喝酒的宇航员 真有意思\N{\rE}Oh, really? An astronaut who doesn't drink. That's very intriguing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.68,0:16:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么会认为我是宇航员\N{\rE}What makes you think I'm an astronaut?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.93,0:16:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你戴着阿波罗胸针 只有宇航员才有\N{\rE}Because you have an Apollo pin, and only astronauts get those.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.72,0:17:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,看来你对国家航空航天局略知一二\N{\rE}So you know a thing or two about NASA.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.52,0:17:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,是 我是新晋粉丝 我叫凯莉琼斯\N{\rE}Yeah, well, I'm a recent fan. I'm Kelly Jones.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.27,0:17:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我不是宇航员 我只是在肯尼迪中心工作 科尔戴维斯\N{\rE}I'm no astronaut. I just work at Kennedy. Cole Davis.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.73,0:17:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,你做什么工作\N{\rE}Well, what do you do there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.24,0:17:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 我最不愿意在闲聊中谈工作\N{\rE}Look, the last thing I want to do is make small talk about my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.91,0:17:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 我不是那个意思\N{\rE}Sorry. That didn't sound--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.08,0:17:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我不是想... - 没关系 对 你只是实话实说\N{\rE}- I didn't mean it for it to-- Uh. - That's okay. No. You were being honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.41,0:17:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你点的餐好了 科尔\N{\rE}Order up, Cole.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.73,0:17:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我没实话实说 如果我真的坦诚\N{\rE}I wasn't being honest. If I was being honest,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.73,0:17:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我会跟你说 你是我记忆中\N{\rE}I'd have told you you're the most beautiful woman
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.94,0:17:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,所见过最美的女人\N{\rE}that I've seen in longer than I can remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.61,0:17:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,而我的记忆力很好\N{\rE}and I have a very good memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.20,0:17:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我只想请你喝一杯 然后跟你聊上几小时\N{\rE}All I really want to do is just buy you a drink and talk to you for hours,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.95,0:18:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,但我做不到 所以我要努力忘记你在这里\N{\rE}but I can't so I'm trying really hard to just forget that you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.04,0:18:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,很高兴认识你 凯莉\N{\rE}It was nice to meet you, Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.00,0:18:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,非常抱歉\N{\rE}I really am sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.26,0:19:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,欢迎来到火箭路\N{\rE}Welcome to Rockets Road,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.47,0:19:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,又称鳄鱼巷\N{\rE}also known as Alligator Alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.19,0:19:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,如果想保住胳膊和腿\N{\rE}You'll wanna keep your arms and legs inside the cart
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.94,0:19:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,请不要把手脚伸出车外\N{\rE}if you wanna keep your arms and legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.15,0:19:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,(国家航空航天局 约翰F.肯尼迪航天中心)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.86,0:19:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,没有啦 开个小玩笑 它们主要在水中发动攻击\N{\rE}No, that's just a little joke. They mostly attack in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.66,0:19:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 今天的参观大约要两个半到三小时\N{\rE}Now, today's tour will take approximately two and a half to three hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.08,0:19:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,请舒适地坐好\N{\rE}So let's get comfy-cozy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.20,0:19:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,右手边是我们的测试楼\N{\rE}Now on the right is our testing facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.46,0:19:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,是世界顶尖水平的\N{\rE}State-of-the-art.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.58,0:19:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- 失火了 - 它经常失火\N{\rE}It's on fire. - It is often on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.96,0:19:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,前方是载具组装大楼\N{\rE}Up ahead, we have the vehicle assembly building.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.92,0:19:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,是组装火箭的地方\N{\rE}That's where they assemble the rockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.72,0:19:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,是全世界最高的单层建筑\N{\rE}That is the tallest single-story building in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.39,0:19:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,里面能放下四座自由女神像\N{\rE}You can fit four Statue of Liberties inside that building.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.44,0:19:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊 《生活》杂志 完全没拍出它有多壮观\N{\rE}Wow. Life Magazine really doesn't do it justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.57,0:19:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,这也太...我想进去看看\N{\rE}This is so gre-- I'd love to go inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.23,0:19:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这里严禁入内 抱歉 - 走 我们靠近点看看\N{\rE}- It's highly restricted. I'm sorry. - Come on, let's get a closer look.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.24,0:20:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,不行...这里不得进入\N{\rE}Oh, no, no. No. There's no entry here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.49,0:20:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你需要一个特殊的胸卡才能进\N{\rE}You need a special access badge to enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.03,0:20:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- 比如这个  - 对\N{\rE}Oh, like-- like this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.45,0:20:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,那...不行...那是我的胸卡\N{\rE}Yeah. That's, uh-- Oh, no, no, no, that's-- that's my badge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.50,0:20:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- 嘿 - 看看这地方 太大了\N{\rE}- Uh, hey-- Oh. - Look at this place. It's enormous!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.25,0:20:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- 似乎大得多... - 她们拿走了我的胸卡\N{\rE}- It seems like it's much bigger-- - They took my badge!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.46,0:20:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,看看这个建筑\N{\rE}I mean, look at this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.88,0:20:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- 喂 那是我的胸卡 - 你好 先生 嗨\N{\rE}- Hello? That's-That's my badge. - Hello, sir. Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.38,0:20:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我是国家航空航天局 公共事务部的凯莉琼斯\N{\rE}Kelly Jones from NASA Public Affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.84,0:20:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我们俩的万能通行证 谢谢\N{\rE}Here's our all-access pass for both of us. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.22,0:20:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢 - 等等...我的胸卡\N{\rE}Thank you. - Wait, wait. My card.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.14,0:20:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,这个我能推销出去\N{\rE}Now, this I can sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.32,0:20:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,哟呼\N{\rE}Yoo-hoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.44,0:20:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你们好 小伙子们...\N{\rE}Hello. Boys, boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.57,0:20:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨 凯莉琼斯\N{\rE}Hi. Kelly Jones.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.28,0:20:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我是国家航空航天局 新成立的公共事务部的\N{\rE}I'm from the new NASA Public Affairs team.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.66,0:20:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我能问你们俩几个问题吗\N{\rE}Can I ask you two a few questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.54,0:20:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,姓名 年龄 你们在这里的工作\N{\rE}Name, age, and what's your job here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.71,0:20:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我是斯图布莱斯 总工程师之一 24岁\N{\rE}Uh, I'm Stu Bryce. One of the, uh, head engineers, and I'm 24.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.54,0:20:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们就说35岁 - 好\N{\rE}- We'll say 35. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.13,0:20:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,你呢\N{\rE}And you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.13,0:21:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我叫唐哈珀 我是他的手下 23岁\N{\rE}I'm Don Harper. I-I work for him, and I'm 23.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.72,0:21:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你们真年轻\N{\rE}You guys are babies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.72,0:21:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,国家航空航天局的平均年龄是26岁\N{\rE}The average age at NASA is 26.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.51,0:21:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们知道这里也有些老年人\N{\rE}But w-we do know some old people that work here as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.01,0:21:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- 对 32 33岁的 - 是\N{\rE}- Yeah, like, 32, 33. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.43,0:21:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,听你们这么说 我很想杀了你俩\N{\rE}I'll try not to kill both of you for saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.73,0:21:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,跟我们说说 斯图 你为什么加入这伟大的美国任务\N{\rE}So, tell us, Stu, what brings you to join this great American mission?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.86,0:21:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我在大学宿舍里看到了一张传单\N{\rE}Well, I s-- saw a, uh, flyer in my college dorm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.28,0:21:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- “从小就热爱群星” - 很好\N{\rE}-"A childhood love of the stars." - That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.20,0:21:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- 非常感人 - 非常好\N{\rE}- That's very moving. - That's very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.57,0:21:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你呢  - 不好意思\N{\rE}- And you? Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.20,0:21:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么来了\N{\rE}What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.37,0:21:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我特意来找你的 想给你我的电话号码\N{\rE}Well, I-- I tracked you down to give you my phone number,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.66,0:21:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我感觉我们很来电\N{\rE}'cause I felt we had a connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.29,0:21:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么  - 别紧张 我开玩笑的\N{\rE}- What? - Relax. I'm joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.50,0:21:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在在这里工作 莫伯克斯招我进来 改组国家航空航天局公共事务部\N{\rE}I work here now. Moe Berkus brought me on to revamp NASA Public Affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.05,0:21:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你就是来自曼哈顿的广告精英\N{\rE}So you're the killer from Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.09,0:21:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你一定就是发射主管 这是我的同事露比马丁\N{\rE}And you must be the launch director. This is my associate, Ruby Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.68,0:21:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,好 我不在乎 听着 这栋楼完全禁止进入\N{\rE}Yeah, I don't care. Look. This building is completely off-limits.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.56,0:21:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,这里有各种可能烧伤 冻伤 烤焦\N{\rE}Everything in here can burn you, freeze you, fry you,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.56,0:21:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,毒死 砸死你们的东西\N{\rE}poison you and crush you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.56,0:21:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- 走吧 出去 - 你在这里工作多久了\N{\rE}- So let's go. Out. How long have you worked here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.02,0:22:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,很长时间了\N{\rE}A substantial amount of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.15,0:22:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你在写什么  - 你的原话\N{\rE}- What are you writing? - Your quote.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.73,0:22:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,这不算原话 我只是随口一说\N{\rE}That's not a quote. It was just a thing that I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.28,0:22:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我会添油加醋的 你今天有时间接受采访吗\N{\rE}I'll punch it up. Do you have time today for an interview?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.74,0:22:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我还需要跟你的上级谈谈\N{\rE}And also, I need to sit down with your senior officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.87,0:22:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- 上相的优先 - 我可以帮忙挑\N{\rE}- The photogenic types first. - I can help with the selection process.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.37,0:22:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 我这里的人都太奇怪了 不适合采访\N{\rE}Look, my guys are too weird for interviews,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.41,0:22:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,而且他们真的在忙生死攸关的工作\N{\rE}and they're actually busy doing life-and-death work.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.29,0:22:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 我不需要你的批准\N{\rE}Well, you know, I don't need your permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.00,0:22:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,美国人跟太空之间 漫长且昂贵的蜜月期已经结束\N{\rE}The Americans are over their long and expensive honeymoon in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.05,0:22:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我是来提醒大家当初为什么爱上太空的\N{\rE}and I'm here to remind them why they fell in love in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.88,0:22:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,是吗 美国人应该心存感激\N{\rE}Is that right? Well, Americans should be very grateful
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.43,0:22:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,这些人为了这项任务在冒生命危险\N{\rE}that these men are putting their lives on the line for the mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.18,0:22:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你并不怎么了解美国人 是吧\N{\rE}Well, you don't know much about American people, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.98,0:22:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你也不怎么了解 你的办公室吧 我带你看看\N{\rE}You don't know very much about your office I'm about to show you, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.36,0:22:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,这是储物间吗\N{\rE}Is this a storage closet?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.03,0:22:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,不是 储物间有窗户\N{\rE}Nope. Storage closet has a window.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.20,0:22:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,好 速溶咖啡在休息室\N{\rE}Okay, so, instant coffee... ...is in the break room.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.04,0:22:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,记得先把水龙头打开 放一分钟的水 把铁锈冲掉\N{\rE}Just run the tap for a minute to flush out the rust.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.29,0:23:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你们有谁会用灭火器吗\N{\rE}Do either of you know how to work a fire extinguisher?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.71,0:23:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,不会 好吧 四步口诀 很简单\N{\rE}No? Mkay. PASS method's pretty simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.13,0:23:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,拔安全销 对准火焰 压下把手 喷向火焰\N{\rE}Just, uh, pull the pin, aim, squeeze, sweep.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.47,0:23:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你们有任何其他需要\N{\rE}If you need anything else,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.30,0:23:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,可以回纽约去拿 祝你们愉快\N{\rE}uh, maybe just go back to New York and get it. Have a good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.18,0:23:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 至少他还算养眼 - 但说话很刺耳\N{\rE}- Well, at least he's easy on the eyes. - He's hard on the ears though.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.10,0:23:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,欢迎仪式很烂啊 我以为你说他们想要我们帮忙呢\N{\rE}Not a great welcome wagon. I thought you said they wanted our help.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.69,0:23:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我说他们需要我们帮忙 这一点现在已经实锤到不能再实锤\N{\rE}Oh, no. I said they needed our help. And I do believe that now more than ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.19,0:23:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们谁都不能谈或什么都不能看\N{\rE}How are we supposed to do that if we can't talk to anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.57,0:23:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,那要怎么帮忙\N{\rE}or look at anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.24,0:23:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,是一只猫...\N{\rE}Aw, it's a cat. It's a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.99,0:23:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是一只猫 - 是一只猫\N{\rE}It's a cat! - It's a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.28,0:23:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道关于黑猫的说法吗\N{\rE}You know what they say about black cats?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.29,0:23:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,如果黑猫从你面前路过 可能是要去其他地方\N{\rE}If they cross your path, they're probably going someplace else.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.04,0:23:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,好 该把旧名片夹翻出来了\N{\rE}Okay, time to dig out the old Rolodex.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.54,0:23:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,创意时间到\N{\rE}Let's get creative.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.11,0:24:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波罗11号将把我们的人送上月球\N{\rE}Apollo 11 will land our men on the moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.99,0:24:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,这会让我们成为世界第一\N{\rE}and that makes us first.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.74,0:24:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们完成工作 将会在那里发射\N{\rE}If we do our jobs, we will launch right from there,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.25,0:24:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,时间是7月16日一大早\N{\rE}July 16, bright and early.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.04,0:24:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,在那之前\N{\rE}Between now and then,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.12,0:24:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要完成人类历史上\N{\rE}we will piece together the biggest jigsaw puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.00,0:24:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,最大的拼图\N{\rE}in the history of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.88,0:24:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,六百万个零部件散落在全国各地\N{\rE}Six million parts spread out around the country,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.97,0:24:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要对每一个零件 进行组装 测试 再测试\N{\rE}and we will assemble, test, and retest every single one
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.18,0:24:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,直到我们确定阿波罗11号 可以万无一失地发射\N{\rE}until we are certain that Apollo 11 will take off
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.72,0:24:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,并飞向月球 就在...\N{\rE}without a hitch and head to the moon in--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.27,0:24:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,亨利 你说\N{\rE}Henry, sing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.06,0:24:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,在七个月后\N{\rE}Seven months. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.23,0:24:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,七个月后\N{\rE}Seven months.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.44,0:24:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,请帮我恭喜阿波罗11号的宇航员\N{\rE}Please help me congratulate the astronauts of Apollo 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.57,0:24:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,阿姆斯特朗 奥尔德林和柯林斯\N{\rE}Armstrong, Aldrin and Collins.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.96,0:25:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿...伙计们 你们觉得白宫怎么样\N{\rE}Hey, hey! How'd you like the White House, boys? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.38,0:25:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,(月球 我们来了)
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.92,0:25:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,还不错 只可惜尼尔不让我偷那里的瓷器\N{\rE}Yeah, it was all right, except Neil wouldn't let me steal the china.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.13,0:25:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,好 因为在八个月后 等这一切都结束\N{\rE}All right. Because in eight months, when this is all over,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.72,0:25:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,他们需要新历史书 来记载我们在这里取得的成就时\N{\rE}and they need new history books to cover what we've accomplished here,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.72,0:25:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你们每一个人都能说\N{\rE}each and every single one of you will be able to say that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.69,0:25:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“我做了有史以来最困难的事” 对吗\N{\rE}"I did the hardest thing that has ever been done." Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.61,0:25:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,对\N{\rE}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.65,0:25:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- 行动起来 - 开工\N{\rE}Let's do it. - Let's get to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.20,0:25:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- 漂亮 说得好 - 谢谢\N{\rE}- Beautiful. Perfect. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.37,0:25:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是 - 长官\N{\rE}- Yeah. - Sir,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.29,0:25:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你说新来的女士 只要做任何你不喜欢的事就通知你\N{\rE}you said to tell you when the new lady did anything you wouldn't like.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.46,0:25:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我身处肯尼迪航天中心\N{\rE}I'm here at the Kennedy Space Center
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.29,0:25:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,有幸采访到副发射主管亨利斯莫尔斯\N{\rE}with Deputy Launch Director, Henry Smalls.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.50,0:25:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么回事 那是我的名字 他盗用了我的名字和职位\N{\rE}What's going on? That's my name. He's got my name and my job!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.42,0:25:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,这段时间对我们所有人来说都很美好 对我来说更具个人感情\N{\rE}It's been a great time for all of us. You know, for me, this is very personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.59,0:25:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我父亲是一位空军士兵\N{\rE}My father was an airman...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.93,0:25:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,这是谁啊\N{\rE}Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.80,0:26:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- 反正不是我 - 他在服役时牺牲了\N{\rE}- It's not me. - ...he died in the line of duty
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.39,0:26:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- 当时我还是个孩子 - 我没那么帅\N{\rE}- when I was a child... - I'm not that handsome.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.35,0:26:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,这是为了你 老爸\N{\rE}...so this is for you, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.52,0:26:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- 真是够了 - 听到这个我很遗憾\N{\rE}- Oh, that's it. - So sorry to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.39,0:26:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢你的分享 这一定很... - 我爸还活着呢\N{\rE}- Thanks for sharing. That must've been... - My dad's still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.15,0:26:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,对 要怎样才能约在晚上6点左右呢 好\N{\rE}Right. What is it that we can do to sort of make 6:00 p.m.? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.07,0:26:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,国家航空航天局公共事务部 我是凯莉琼斯\N{\rE}NASA Public Affairs, this is Kelly Jones.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.20,0:26:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉 美国广播公司 想要下周的媒体录影带\N{\rE}Kelly, ABC wants next week's press reel.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.66,0:26:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,还想要我们手上最好的阿波罗8号照片\N{\rE}They also want the best photo we have from the Apollo 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.91,0:26:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,跟他们说 如果让我们 上晚6点时间段就给他们\N{\rE}Tell them they can have it if they give us their 6:00 p.m. time slot.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.41,0:26:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- 明白 - 如果你们播放动画片段\N{\rE}- Got it. - If you air an animated segment,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.96,0:26:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我能给你们提供独家的... - 非常感谢\N{\rE}- I can offer you an exclusive-- Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.25,0:26:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你父亲是个英雄 你是个英雄 我们非常感激你勤恳地...\N{\rE}Your father was a hero. You are a hero. We so appreciate you working at...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.05,0:26:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- 那是全国广播公司新闻主管 - 是 我不管 这人是谁\N{\rE}- That was the head of NBC News. - Yeah, I don't care. Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.92,0:26:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢 我们月球上见\N{\rE}Thank you. See you on the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.55,0:26:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,在公众眼里 他是亨利斯莫尔斯\N{\rE}To the world, that's Henry Smalls.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.09,0:26:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,他不是亨利斯莫尔斯\N{\rE}That's not Henry Smalls.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.30,0:26:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,对 但你跟我说你们不接受采访\N{\rE}No, but you told me that your guys don't do interviews,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.35,0:26:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我只能另请新人\N{\rE}so I had to hire new guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.10,0:26:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你让两位全球最顶尖的工程师装窗户\N{\rE}You have two of the best engineers on the planet installing a window.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.31,0:26:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,菲尔 你再挥一下锤子 我一定会疯掉\N{\rE}Phil, if you hammer one more time, I swear to God I'm gonna lose my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.98,0:26:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,把锤子放下 摘掉该死的工具带\N{\rE}Put down the hammer, take your stupid belts off
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.94,0:26:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,回去测试\N{\rE}and get back to testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.99,0:26:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,动起来 走了\N{\rE}On the move. Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.20,0:26:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,这景色绝了吧\N{\rE}Can you believe that view?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.78,0:27:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们拿到了阿波罗8号的第一批照片 - 比我的好\N{\rE}- We got the first photos from Apollo 8. - It's better than mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.16,0:27:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,从月球拍的第一张地球照片\N{\rE}The first shot of the earth from the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.08,0:27:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,这是不是你见过最美的东西\N{\rE}Isn't that the most beautiful thing you've ever seen?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.50,0:27:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你怎么比我先拿到  - 他们称之为“地出”\N{\rE}- How'd you get this before me? - They're calling it "Earthrise."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.63,0:27:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,这张照片会登上今晚所有新闻的头条\N{\rE}It's going to be at the top of every news segment tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.75,0:27:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,1968年太糟糕了\N{\rE}I mean, '68 has been such a terrible year.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.50,0:27:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,刺杀 可憎的战争 我们见证了人类最丑恶的一面\N{\rE}Assassinations, this heinous war, we've seen the worst of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.67,0:27:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,这时国家航空航天局公布这张照片 一个看世界的全新视角\N{\rE}Now NASA gives us this? A whole new way to see the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.97,0:27:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我会确保所有人都看到\N{\rE}And I'm gonna make sure everybody sees it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.73,0:27:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能找人冒充别人啊\N{\rE}You can't just fake people!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.73,0:27:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨 我是来参加选角的\N{\rE}Hey, I'm here for the casting.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.73,0:27:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他是谁  - 是你 你这个角色可抢手了\N{\rE}- Who's he? - You. You're a juicy part.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.90,0:27:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,要拍这几场戏 这里是角色生平\N{\rE}So, here's the scenes and the character bio.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.78,0:27:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你要扮演的就是这位 所以最好提升一点魅力\N{\rE}This is the man that you're playing, so you wanna up the charisma a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.28,0:27:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好 我会提升... - 明白 好\N{\rE}- Can do. I'll up the-- - Okay? Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.66,0:27:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- 在朝鲜执行过60次任务  - 是的\N{\rE}- Sixty missions in Korea? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.04,0:27:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我很荣幸 - 我在朝鲜飞过52次任务\N{\rE}It's an honor. - I flew 52 missions in Korea.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.29,0:27:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我取了个整数\N{\rE}I rounded up.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.75,0:27:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“我在朝鲜飞过52次任务” 怎么样\N{\rE}"I flew 52 missions in Korea." How was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.92,0:27:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么  - 我会练习一下的\N{\rE}- What? - I'll work on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.34,0:28:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,她现在都找好人冒充我了\N{\rE}She has a fake me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.76,0:28:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- 她已经有了个假的我 - 她有个假的我 假的你\N{\rE}- She got a fake me. - She got a fake me and a fake you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.60,0:28:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不能冒充你和我 - 一无所获\N{\rE}- You can't fake me and you. - There's nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.22,0:28:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,没有莫伯克斯 我每个字都看过了\N{\rE}There's no Moe Berkus. I checked every spelling.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.89,0:28:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,有个叫莫伯克斯的打来电话\N{\rE}I have a Moe Berkus on the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.07,0:28:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- 要我来说吗  - 不...我会很享受的\N{\rE}- Do you want me to talk? - Oh, no, no. I'm gonna enjoy this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.74,0:28:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,这将是国家航空航天局史上最快速的解雇\N{\rE}This is gonna be the fastest firing in NASA's history.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.41,0:28:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- 嗨 莫 - 科尔 我听说你在找我\N{\rE}- Hey, Moe. - Cole, I hear you're looking for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.78,0:28:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 凯莉琼斯 聘请了演员来假扮国家航空航天局工程师\N{\rE}I am. Kelly Jones hired actors to play NASA engineers.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.20,0:28:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,这是不可接受的 我要她今天就走人\N{\rE}It is unacceptable. I want her desk cleared today.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.62,0:28:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,冷静点...好吗\N{\rE}Calm, calm, calm down, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.34,0:28:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,华盛顿的政要们会看电视 阿波罗现在上电视了\N{\rE}Washington watches TV. Apollo is now on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.38,0:28:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,每个频道 每天都播\N{\rE}Every channel, every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.18,0:28:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你们想登月吗\N{\rE}So, you want to get to the moon?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.76,0:28:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我建议你们专心做好本职工作\N{\rE}I suggest, focus on your job.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.06,0:28:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,也让凯莉做好本职工作\N{\rE}Let Kelly do hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.93,0:28:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,如果她把你打造成舞会上的焦点\N{\rE}If she's made you the belle of the ball,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.52,0:28:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,你不妨穿上芭蕾舞裙来跳一段\N{\rE}why don't you just slip on your tutu and do some dancing?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.32,0:29:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,炒掉她了\N{\rE}She fired?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.78,0:29:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我们被炒了\N{\rE}Are we fired?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.62,0:29:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波罗8号载着宇航员 博尔曼 洛弗尔和安德斯\N{\rE}Apollo 8, carrying astronauts Borman, Lovell and Anders
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.88,0:29:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,由土星5号送入了太空\N{\rE}was launched into space by a Saturn V.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.21,0:29:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,每一个电视网都在播放地出照片\N{\rE}Every single network is airing the Earthrise shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.09,0:29:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,会传遍世界各地\N{\rE}I mean, it's-- it's gonna be everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.22,0:29:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我试着画了几笔\N{\rE}You know, I tried a little something on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.97,0:29:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- 但好像效果还不行 - 不够吸引人 我们需要一个关联\N{\rE}- but I just don't think it's working yet. - It's not enough. We need a hook,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.89,0:29:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,一个把登月和人们日常生活挂钩的方法\N{\rE}a way to weave the moon landing into people's everyday lives
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.56,0:29:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,还得潜移默化\N{\rE}without them realizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.69,0:29:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨 你们有类似沙拉的东西吗\N{\rE}Uh, hi. Do you have anything close to a salad?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.73,0:29:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,汉堡上的腌黄瓜\N{\rE}Pickles come on a burger.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.77,0:29:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,不过要等一等 阿波罗的新闻一出 生意变好了\N{\rE}It's gonna be a minute, though. Apollo news has business picking up.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.36,0:29:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,有很多游客想来亲眼见证历史\N{\rE}All the tourists love to come in and see little pieces of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.86,0:29:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- 见证历史  - 对 比如那支笔\N{\rE}- Pieces of history? - Yeah, like-- like that pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.91,0:29:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,1961年 约翰格伦每晚都来这里用餐\N{\rE}John Glenn ate here every night in '61.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.70,0:29:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,(沃尔菲上太空了)
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.12,0:29:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,他用我们的一支笔来写飞行手册\N{\rE}He would work on his flight manuals, and he'd use one of our pens.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.87,0:29:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,那支笔上过水星6号\N{\rE}That one ended up on Mercury 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.29,0:30:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是全世界唯一一家 名字上过太空的餐厅\N{\rE}You're at the only restaurant in the world whose name's been in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.30,0:30:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,很酷\N{\rE}That's cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.01,0:30:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,正前方\N{\rE}And right up ahead,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.68,0:30:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,是著名的水星火箭\N{\rE}it's the famous Mercury rockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.43,0:30:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,一定要在这里拍照 但别站太近\N{\rE}Be sure to get a picture here, but don't stand too close.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.44,0:30:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,火箭可能会发射\N{\rE}They might go off.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.86,0:30:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,(你能准备好吗 距离发射还有171天)
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.19,0:30:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,那个周末过后 他就恢复了\N{\rE}He recovered after that weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.66,0:30:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你每次进房间 大家都会安静下来 你感到困扰吗\N{\rE}Does it bother you that a room dies every time you walk into it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.99,0:30:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你该待在你那边的\N{\rE}You're supposed to stay on your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.29,0:30:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我想你了\N{\rE}I missed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.54,0:30:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望你批准我们新的推广活动\N{\rE}I'd like you to approve our new ad campaigns.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.29,0:30:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,你不如就像上次一样先斩后奏吧\N{\rE}Why don't you just sidestep me like you did last time?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.21,0:30:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我想为那些让你措手不及的采访道歉\N{\rE}I wanna apologize for blindsiding you with the interviews.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.21,0:30:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我有办法解决我们的资金问题\N{\rE}I have a fix for our money problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.92,0:30:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我不接受你的道歉 也不接受这些莫名奇妙的东西\N{\rE}Well, your apology is rejected, and so is whatever this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.34,0:30:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- 欧米茄 - 听着 这里不是麦迪逊大道\N{\rE}- Omega. - Look, this isn't Madison Avenue.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.18,0:30:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们不会为这种东西买单 - 不 免费的\N{\rE}- We don't pay for this stuff. - No, it's cost-free.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.35,0:30:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,品牌方能得到钱都买不到的合作机会\N{\rE}The brands get a tie-in money can't buy,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.31,0:30:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,而国家航空航天局 可以潜移默化去影响普通人\N{\rE}and NASA works its way into the minds of everyday people.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.19,0:30:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,手表广告 这就是你的绝妙点子\N{\rE}A watch ad? That's-That's your big idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.81,0:31:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,准备好了\N{\rE}Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.32,0:31:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,牙膏\N{\rE}Toothpaste.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.99,0:31:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,菓珍 “阿波罗宇航员选择的 能量早餐饮品\N{\rE}Tang. "The energy breakfast drink chosen for Apollo astronauts
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.86,0:31:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- 专供登月之旅使用” - 月球优惠券\N{\rE}- on their trip to the moon." - Moon coupons?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.16,0:31:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,但我个人最喜欢的要属这个\N{\rE}But, my personal favorite,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.33,0:31:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,鲜果布衣 是吧\N{\rE}Fruit of the Loom. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.25,0:31:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,宇航员在太空服里面总得穿点什么吧\N{\rE}The guys gotta wear something under those big suits, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.79,0:31:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,鲜果布衣真的太能代表航天局了\N{\rE}Nothing says NASA like Fruit of the Loom.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.46,0:31:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 我不会把飞船变成飞行广告牌\N{\rE}Look, I am not turning this ship into a flying billboard
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.96,0:31:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,无论你多么渴望都不行\N{\rE}no matter how much you want it to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.88,0:31:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,还有 我们没时间在发射前测试这些东西\N{\rE}And by the way, we don't have time to test all this before liftoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.64,0:31:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不必真的把这些送上太空 只要说说就好\N{\rE}We don't have to send any of this up into space as long as we say it went.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.22,0:31:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你打算撒谎\N{\rE}Oh, so you're gonna lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.64,0:31:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,这叫推销 我们不会欺骗顾客\N{\rE}It's called selling. We're not lying to the customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.60,0:31:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们在改变他们的思维方式 - 不 这叫撒谎\N{\rE}- We're changing the way they think. - No, it's called lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.81,0:31:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,所有人在你眼里都只是顾客吗\N{\rE}Everyone is just a customer to you, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.73,0:31:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 我知道你是个厉害的广告精英\N{\rE}Look, I know that you're a big old fancy ad shark and everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.27,0:31:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,但国家航空航天局 不是能用广告曲和广告词推销的\N{\rE}but NASA's not something that you sell with a jingle and a slogan.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.49,0:31:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你不知道我们是谁\N{\rE}You do not know who we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.91,0:31:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,行 好吧 玛格丽特汉密尔顿是谁\N{\rE}Yeah, okay. Who's Margaret Hamilton?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.45,0:31:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,- 谁  - 她是你的手下\N{\rE}- Who? - She works here for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.49,0:31:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,有四十万人和太空计划有关\N{\rE}There are 400,000 people that are affiliated
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.91,0:31:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- 琼斯女士 - 她是你的工程师之一\N{\rE}- with this space program, Ms. Jones. - She's one of your engineers.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.41,0:32:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- 乔安摩根是谁  - 她是点火室的\N{\rE}- Who's JoAnn Morgan? - She works in the firing room.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.63,0:32:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,你问过她当初为什么接这份工作吗  我就问过\N{\rE}Did you ever ask her why she took this job in the first place? I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.67,0:32:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,她说因为她的血液里流的都是火箭燃料\N{\rE}She says it's because she has rocket fuel in her blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.84,0:32:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,国家航空航天局不光是个标志 也代表着人民\N{\rE}And NASA's not just a logo, it's people.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.01,0:32:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,那些每天早上醒来\N{\rE}People who wake up every morning
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.51,0:32:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,决心创造奇迹的人\N{\rE}and commit to accomplishing the impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.10,0:32:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,同时跟大家穿着一样的内衣\N{\rE}And all while wearing the same underwear as the rest of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.48,0:32:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,艾拉 你有任何需要吗\N{\rE}Ella, can I help you with anything at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.57,0:32:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rE}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.11,0:32:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我预估了一下 如果你接受关键赞助\N{\rE}So I ran the projections, and this is what you stand to make
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.82,0:32:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,能赚到这个数\N{\rE}if you accept key sponsorships.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.75,0:32:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不能收私人的钱\N{\rE}We-We can't take private money.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.66,0:32:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,无所谓的 明白吗\N{\rE}It doesn't matter, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.87,0:32:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我即将让航天局变得非常受欢迎\N{\rE}I'm about to make NASA so popular
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.67,0:32:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,国会终将重新提供资金\N{\rE}that Congress will finally turn the taps back on around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.50,0:32:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我只需让阿姆斯特朗 戴上一块欧米茄手表就行\N{\rE}And all I have to do is just let Armstrong put on an Omega watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.13,0:32:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,不 如果我们得到资金\N{\rE}No. If we get the money flowing,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.68,0:32:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,那你必须向我证明\N{\rE}then you've gotta prove to me
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.18,0:32:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,可可海滩也有不错的地方可以吃晚餐\N{\rE}that Cocoa Beach has a decent place to get dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.90,0:33:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- 成交 我... - 好 成交 太好了 呜呼\N{\rE}- Deal. I-- - Yes! Deal! Yes! Whoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.11,0:33:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,不 等等 我得设置底线 手纸不行\N{\rE}Uh, no, wait. I'm drawing the line at toilet paper though,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.24,0:33:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,因为世人不用知道我们的人用什么擦屁股\N{\rE}because the world does not get to know what our guys wipe their ass with.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.20,0:33:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,真臭\N{\rE}Well, shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.04,0:33:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你返回地球后想去度假吗\N{\rE}Would you like to go for a vacation when you come back to earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.96,0:33:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,根据目前的情况看\N{\rE}The situation being what it is now,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.63,0:33:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我最可能去的地方...\N{\rE}the place I would most like to go, uh--
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.59,0:33:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,下次把桌子撤掉 沃尔特\N{\rE}Lose the table next time, Walter.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.55,0:33:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,尼尔看起来 像在做通用电气的季度盈利报告\N{\rE}Neil looks like he's giving GE's quarterly profit report.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.30,0:33:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我们一直用这张桌...\N{\rE}That's always been our table--
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.05,0:33:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,电视让他们走进人们的起居室\N{\rE}TV brings them in to people's living rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.93,0:33:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,他们应该看起来像家中的客人\N{\rE}They should look like they belong there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.51,0:33:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,那意味着我们成功了\N{\rE}- It'd mean that we succeeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.93,0:33:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你还是负责人 沃尔特 别担心\N{\rE}You're still in charge, Walter. Don't you worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.73,0:33:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,不过等我帮完忙后\N{\rE}When I'm done helping though,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.23,0:33:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这些人会比披头士乐队还火\N{\rE}those men are gonna be bigger than The Beatles.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.36,0:33:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以完成99.9%的登月之旅 我很满意\N{\rE}I'm getting to go 99.9% of the way there, and that suits me just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.95,0:33:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,(下一站:月球)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.41,0:33:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,(阿波罗11号:最危险的航行)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.83,0:34:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,(阿波罗登月在即)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.91,0:34:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 家乐氏的那个副总叫什么  - 应该是哈里森德里斯科尔\N{\rE}- What's the name of that VP at Kellogg's? - I believe it's Harrison Driscoll.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.33,0:34:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,好 哈里森\N{\rE}All right, Harrison.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.25,0:34:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,不要用“噼啪 笑笑 泡泡” 改用“尼尔 巴兹和迈克” 不错吧\N{\rE}So instead of "Snap, Crackle, Pop," "Neil, Buzz and Mike." It's cute, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.18,0:34:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,科尔\N{\rE}Cole!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.23,0:34:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- 确保那个不会生锈 亨利 - 能签一下这些吗\N{\rE}- Make sure that doesn't rust, Henry. - Can you mark these?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.40,0:34:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- 嘿... - 你看见了吗\N{\rE}Hey, hey. - Did you see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.77,0:34:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你没看见那只猫\N{\rE}You didn't see the cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.95,0:34:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,菓珍的瓶子再推近些\N{\rE}Go closer on the Tang bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.45,0:34:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,字体再大些 放上培根和鸡蛋\N{\rE}Make the font bigger and put bacon with the eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.45,0:34:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,别忘了 我们推销的是美国\N{\rE}Let's not forget, we're selling America, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.66,0:34:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“彼得潘花生酱 丝滑到飞起 此酱只应天上有”\N{\rE}"Peter Pan Peanut Butter. Peanut butter that's out-of-this-world smooth."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.92,0:34:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“哈苏 以他们的视角看世界”\N{\rE}"Hasselblad. See the world the way they do."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.21,0:34:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,拉里 这是欧米茄的好机会\N{\rE}Larry, this is Omega's big chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.30,0:34:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,在每一块超霸的背面 直到永远\N{\rE}On the back of every Speedmaster till the end of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.18,0:34:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,(宇航员登上月球时将佩戴欧米茄手表)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.97,0:35:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“第一块被戴上月球的手表” 对吧\N{\rE}"The first watch worn on the moon." Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.89,0:35:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我们得把它立起来\N{\rE}Now we just gotta stand her up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.35,0:35:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,一切都将是值得的\N{\rE}It's all gonna be worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.81,0:35:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,(美国靠阿波罗11号取得领先)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.07,0:35:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- 嘿...你占了我的车位 - 我们在为凯莉布景\N{\rE}- Hey. Hey! You're in my spot. - We're setting up a shot for Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.96,0:35:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的阿波罗11号任务有三位宇航员\N{\rE}We've got three astronauts on the Apollo 11 mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.59,0:35:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,他们站在三辆漂亮的美国汽车前\N{\rE}There they are in front of three beautiful American cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.26,0:35:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,真棒\N{\rE}Oh, this is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.51,0:35:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你们必须立刻前往测试楼\N{\rE}You gotta be in the test facility right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.05,0:35:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,跟凯莉说\N{\rE}Talk to Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.01,0:35:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉说我们花1块就能开走科尔维特\N{\rE}Kelly said we could take a Corvette home for a dollar.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.89,0:35:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你来啦 - 1美元\N{\rE}- There you are. - A dollar?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.93,0:35:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要占用他们15分钟而已\N{\rE}I'm gonna need them for 15 minutes, but that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.68,0:35:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我15分钟前就需要他们了 凯莉\N{\rE}I needed them 15 minutes ago, Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.77,0:35:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道他们穿的宇航服有多贵吗\N{\rE}You know how expensive those suits are?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.81,0:35:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,别担心 他只是发射主管\N{\rE}Oh, don't worry. It's just the launch director.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.44,0:35:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,登月舱的样子很怪 凯利先生 它的原理是什么\N{\rE}This strange looking bird, the LEM, Mr. Kelly. How does it work?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.48,0:35:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,这是让人\N{\rE}Well, this is a spacecraft that's used
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.78,0:35:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,着陆到月球表面的飞船\N{\rE}to take men down to the lunar surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.49,0:36:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,登月舱里三位宇航员中的两位...\N{\rE}And two of the three astronauts in the LEM...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.45,0:36:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,飞行指挥 我们错过了目标 正飘向广袤的虚空\N{\rE}Flight, we missed target and are drifting into the vast abyss.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.42,0:36:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们死了 再来 - 是\N{\rE}- And we're dead. Again. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.55,0:36:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,着陆前30秒耗尽了燃料\N{\rE}Ran out of fuel 30 seconds before touchdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.72,0:36:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,是 但是着陆本身不错\N{\rE}Yeah, but the landing, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.01,0:36:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- 很顺利 很好 - 俯仰角度很好 继续\N{\rE}- it was smooth-- It was good. - Great pitch. Forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.93,0:36:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你们俩撒谎的技术真烂\N{\rE}You're both bad liars.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.39,0:36:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,尼尔 迈克 巴兹 能再为琼斯女士 和欧米茄多拍一张照片吗\N{\rE}Neil, Mike, Buzz, if I can get one more photo for Ms. Jones and Omega?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.97,0:36:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,哥们 你谁啊\N{\rE}Who are you, man?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.27,0:36:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,好 举起手表 小伙子们\N{\rE}- All right, watches up, boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.44,0:36:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,给欧米茄来个微笑\N{\rE}And smile for Omega.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.74,0:36:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我是戴维斯 - 我打扰到你了吗\N{\rE}- Davis. - Am I interrupting?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.58,0:36:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- 一直在打扰 - 你面前应该有个盒子\N{\rE}- Always. - There should be a box in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.29,0:36:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,不如打开看看\N{\rE}- Why don't you open it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.21,0:36:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,欧米茄感谢你的服务\N{\rE}Omega thanks you for your service.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.63,0:37:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你的宇航员们在电视上大出风头\N{\rE}Your boys are all over TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.38,0:37:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,资金又开始流入了 所以...共进晚餐\N{\rE}the taps are flowing again. So... dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.35,0:37:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,好 卡纳维拉尔码头 5点\N{\rE}Yeah. Canaveral Pier. Five o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.94,0:37:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,戴着手表来\N{\rE}Wear your watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.69,0:37:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,下午3点是他们播放采访的 最佳时段 也是最后一个\N{\rE}3:00 p.m. is their best and final time slot to air the interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.86,0:37:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,播阿姆斯特朗的独家采访  下午3点是给小孩和闲人看的\N{\rE}For an exclusive with Armstrong? 3:00 p.m. is for children and deadbeats.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.20,0:37:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,他们说有战争方面的突发新闻\N{\rE}They said they have breaking news from the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.87,0:37:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,敌军规模未知\N{\rE}Unknown size enemy force.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.74,0:37:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,敌军伤亡人数不详\N{\rE}Enemy casualties are unknown,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.12,0:37:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,但大家都看到过到底是怎么回事\N{\rE}but you've seen how it really was.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.83,0:37:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,让阿波罗任务一直有新闻的努力失败了\N{\rE}So much for keeping Apollo back in the news cycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.96,0:37:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,英雄主义 危险 恐惧 全部融为一体\N{\rE}Heroism, danger, fear, all rolled into one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.42,0:37:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,无法用语言形容\N{\rE}Words don't describe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.17,0:37:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我是哥伦比亚广播公司新闻台的 理查德思雷尔克德 柬埔寨边境附近报道\N{\rE}Richard Threlkeld, CBS News. Near the Cambodian border.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.93,0:37:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 斯科蒂船长 感谢\N{\rE}Thank you, Captain Scotty. Appreciate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.81,0:37:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,好\N{\rE}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.81,0:37:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,你对女士可真是一毛不拔\N{\rE}Well, you spare no expense on a lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.73,0:37:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,尝尝看嘛\N{\rE}Just try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.14,0:37:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,虾 蛋黄酱 面包\N{\rE}Shrimp, mayo, bun.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.60,0:37:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这恰好是方圆百里之内最美味的一餐\N{\rE}And that happens to be the best meal in a hundred miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.53,0:38:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我没说错吧\N{\rE}Told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.11,0:38:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我怎么不知道这地方\N{\rE}How'd I not know about this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.74,0:38:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,不是所有人都喜欢打广告\N{\rE}Not everybody likes to advertise.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.66,0:38:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,说得妙 有两下子嘛\N{\rE}Nice one. That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.71,0:38:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,那是火箭发射的地方 就是那里\N{\rE}That's where the rocket will launch out of. Right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.59,0:38:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你戴那块手表戴可真好看 你戴着很合适\N{\rE}That watch looks great on you. You wear it very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.68,0:38:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rE}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.89,0:38:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,那天晚上我在酒吧里跟你说...\N{\rE}That night at the bar, what I said to you--
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.35,0:38:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你的目光无法从我身上挪开\N{\rE}That you couldn't take your eyes off me,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.98,0:38:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我是你见过最美的女人\N{\rE}and I was the most beautiful woman that you'd ever seen?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.36,0:38:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,对 就是这句 这...对\N{\rE}Y-Yeah, that part. That-- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.44,0:38:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,是我冲动了\N{\rE}It was impulsive.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.99,0:38:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,那是对陌生人说的话 可我们现在共事了\N{\rE}It was meant for a stranger, and we're working together now.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.95,0:38:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是不希望你认为我...\N{\rE}So, I just don't want you to think that I was--
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.37,0:38:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,对我有意思\N{\rE}Interested?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.75,0:38:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是想把话说清楚\N{\rE}I just wanted to clear the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.54,0:38:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,好的 说得很清楚\N{\rE}Well, the air was clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.33,0:39:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rE}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.72,0:39:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我有个想法 - 对 那话只适用30秒\N{\rE}-I had a thought. -Yeah. It was perfect for 30 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.60,0:39:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,有哪个电视网是全天候报道的\N{\rE}What are the networks covering night and day?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.31,0:39:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得我有时间看电视吗\N{\rE}You think I have time to watch TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.43,0:39:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,越南 他们直接从前线报道\N{\rE}Vietnam. They're broadcasting straight from the action.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.69,0:39:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,人们已经不想只听新闻了\N{\rE}And people don't want to just hear the news anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.52,0:39:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,他们想直击新闻现场\N{\rE}They wanna see it in the making.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.15,0:39:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rE}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.20,0:39:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,(登月现场直播 阿波罗11号)
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.37,0:39:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,不妨就让他们看\N{\rE}Why not let 'em?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.87,0:39:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,你想在登月舱里放个电视直播摄像机\N{\rE}Oh, you want to put a live television camera on the LEM?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.29,0:39:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rE}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.54,0:39:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我的人在太空里努力活命\N{\rE}My guys are trying to survive up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.17,0:39:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,没时间学如何拍电影\N{\rE}They don't have time to figure out how to film a movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.13,0:39:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我们替他们学 他们只需对准目标拍摄即可\N{\rE}We'll figure it out for 'em. All they have to do is point and shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.63,0:39:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你不明白 这是后勤方面的噩梦\N{\rE}You don't get it. It's a logistical nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.01,0:39:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,问题涉及电力 储存空间 重量\N{\rE}There's power issues, storage, weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.76,0:39:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至没有摄像机能在太空里工作\N{\rE}There's not even a camera that would work up there
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.68,0:39:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,因为夜晚温度是零下129摄氏度 白天超过121摄氏度\N{\rE}'cause it's negative 200 degrees at night and over 250 degrees during the daytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.81,0:39:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你能想象看直播的情景吗\N{\rE}Can you imagine seeing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.02,0:39:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,不能 我刚说了这不可能\N{\rE}No. I just said it's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.48,0:40:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,对 这就是重点\N{\rE}Yes. That's the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.23,0:40:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,这将是有史以来最伟大的电视节目\N{\rE}It would be the greatest televised event ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.32,0:40:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你认为这是个综艺节目吗\N{\rE}Do you think this is a game show?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.65,0:40:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,苏联人没有播出\N{\rE}There is a very good reason
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.32,0:40:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,他们在太空行走是有充分理由的\N{\rE}why the Soviets aren't broadcasting their space walks.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.16,0:40:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,因为苏联是守口如瓶的独裁政权国\N{\rE}Because they're a tight-lipped dictatorship.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.20,0:40:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,- 对 我们不是 - 天啊\N{\rE}- Yeah, that's not us. - Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.49,0:40:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我们取得成功 是举国成功\N{\rE}When we succeed, we do it as a nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.54,0:40:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们遭遇失败 是举国悲痛 - 对\N{\rE}- And when we fail, we grieve as a nation. - Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.91,0:40:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是作为美国人的意义所在\N{\rE}That's what it means to be American.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.71,0:40:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,别跟我说作为美国人意味着什么\N{\rE}Oh, stop telling me what it means to be an American.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.25,0:40:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我们当中只有一个人一辈子在报效祖国\N{\rE}There's only one of us here that has served their country their entire life.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.09,0:40:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 登月舱里不会放摄像机的\N{\rE}I'm sorry. We're not putting the camera on the LEM.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.06,0:40:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我是认真的 不放\N{\rE}I mean it. We're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.56,0:40:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会放的\N{\rE}We are.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.44,0:40:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,(压力点)
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.07,0:40:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,没有更多燃料 他不可能成功\N{\rE}There's no way he can do it without more fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.07,0:40:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- 让他再测一次 - 好\N{\rE}- Have him run it again. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.58,0:41:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,好 我时间很紧 什么事\N{\rE}Okay. [sighs] I'm on a tight schedule. What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.79,0:41:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉跟我说了摄像机的点子 我们很喜欢\N{\rE}Kelly briefed me on the camera idea, and we like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.76,0:41:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,非常喜欢\N{\rE}We like it a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.72,0:41:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,她说错了 我们做不到\N{\rE}- She misspoke. We can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.64,0:41:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,根本没有这种科技\N{\rE}There is no such technology that even exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.01,0:41:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,其实有 你知道吗\N{\rE}Actually it does. You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.22,0:41:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,这是国防部设计的\N{\rE}The Department of Defense designed this
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.39,0:41:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,为了夜间寻找在越南被击落的飞行员\N{\rE}to find downed fighter pilots in Vietnam at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.81,0:41:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 这是机密 但国防部会给你使用\N{\rE}Now, it's classified but the DOD is going to let you use it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.44,0:41:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,只要没人知道它是什么即可\N{\rE}as long as nobody knows what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.28,0:41:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,绝对没有空间装这么重的设备\N{\rE}There's absolutely no space for equipment that heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.45,0:41:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,老天 我们连螺丝钉都称重\N{\rE}We are weighing screws for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.20,0:41:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,什么...这也就7公斤吧\N{\rE}What-- I mean, what is this, 15 pounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.08,0:41:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 那就用轻一些的螺丝钉\N{\rE}Okay. So, just, like, lighter screws.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.95,0:41:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在试用另一个燃料单元\N{\rE}We're trying for another fuel cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.87,0:41:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,好让我们的人登月后 依然有足够的燃料发射\N{\rE}So our men, when they get to the moon, they still have enough fuel to lift off.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.67,0:41:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,她所有的馊主意当中 这个是最糟糕的\N{\rE}Out of all her bad ideas, this one is the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.92,0:41:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,其实总统很喜欢这个点子\N{\rE}Actually, the president loves it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.34,0:41:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,所以现在这就是个好主意\N{\rE}So, now it's a great idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.93,0:41:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我跟你用简单的话说吧 科尔\N{\rE}So, let me put it to you simply, Cole.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.64,0:42:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,找个办法把这东西放进那东西\N{\rE}Find a way to put this on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.39,0:42:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,这是命令 顶头老大下达的\N{\rE}This is an order. From the tippy top.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.07,0:42:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,唐 斯图 请到这里来\N{\rE}Don, Stu. Can you come in here, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.08,0:42:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢 别什么事都闹别扭\N{\rE}Thank you. Let's not make everything so hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.42,0:42:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,请帮琼斯小姐把这个绝密摄像机拆出来\N{\rE}Please help Miss Jones strip this top secret camera down.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.67,0:42:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我不希望他们知道这是绝密\N{\rE}I don't want 'em to know it's top secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.84,0:42:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,现在他们知道了\N{\rE}Well, now they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.92,0:42:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,请把这个绝密摄像机拆出来\N{\rE}Please strip this top secret camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.76,0:42:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,装在登月舱上 以备直播\N{\rE}Mount it onto the LEM for live broadcasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.30,0:42:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,科尔 还有一件事\N{\rE}Cole. One last thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.85,0:42:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,上周 一架中情局的间谍飞机拍到几张\N{\rE}Last week, a CIA spy plane took some surveillance photographs
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.81,0:42:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,苏联新型N1火箭的照片\N{\rE}of the new Russian N1 rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.61,0:42:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,国会看到了\N{\rE}And Congress saw it,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.32,0:42:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,有些议员对最后一轮拨款\N{\rE}and some of the members are having cold feet
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.19,0:42:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,产生了疑虑\N{\rE}- about the final round of funding.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.86,0:42:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我们还有好几个月才能赢下登月竞赛\N{\rE}We're months away from winning this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.78,0:43:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我会让他们来这里参观\N{\rE}I'm gonna send them down here,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.53,0:43:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你要说服他们稍安勿躁\N{\rE}and you're gonna convince them to sit tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.58,0:43:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我...来写几个和他们谈话的要点\N{\rE}No. I'm-- I'm gonna write up some talking points.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.13,0:43:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,别往心里去\N{\rE}Don't take it personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.26,0:43:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,飞行员和重力对抗 这是他们的天性\N{\rE}Pilots fight gravity. It's part of their nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.95,0:43:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,亨利\N{\rE}Henry?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.21,0:43:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我...很高兴你不是科尔\N{\rE}Well, I'm-- I'm glad you're not Cole.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.84,0:43:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,是\N{\rE}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.67,0:43:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,他不喜欢我吸烟\N{\rE}- He don't like me smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.42,0:43:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么 你怕他会给你下禁足令\N{\rE}What, are you worried he's gonna ground you?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.26,0:44:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我...去年做了紧急搭桥手术\N{\rE}Uh, no. I, uh... I had emergency bypass surgery last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.76,0:44:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,对 那个混蛋非常顽固 非要我活下去\N{\rE}Yeah. That son of a bitch. He's hell-bent on keeping me alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.31,0:44:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 我不知道\N{\rE}I'm sorry. I didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.81,0:44:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,是 这里没人知道\N{\rE}Yeah. Nobody here does.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.94,0:44:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,除了科尔\N{\rE}Just Cole.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.94,0:44:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,对 他到医院来 安慰了我太太三天\N{\rE}Yeah. He came to the hospital and held my wife's hand for three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.82,0:44:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 我们认识很久了\N{\rE}Yeah. It's a long way from the day we met.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.62,0:44:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,当时那小子刚从朝鲜回来\N{\rE}Kid had just got back from Korea.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.62,0:44:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,是空军最优秀的飞行员\N{\rE}The top pilot in the Air Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.58,0:44:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,银星勋章 飞行十字勋章\N{\rE}Silver Star. Flying Cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.17,0:44:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他们当时选宇航员时 他在爱德华兹空军基地是头号人选\N{\rE}He was first in line at Edwards when they were looking for astronauts.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.80,0:44:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,但他最后没能入选\N{\rE}But, uh, he ended up not making the cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.93,0:44:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么 是他的脾气吧\N{\rE}So, what got him? It was his temper.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.10,0:44:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,不...是他的心脏\N{\rE}No, no. His heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.98,0:44:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,医生发现他有心房颤动\N{\rE}Doc found an A-fib.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.36,0:44:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,这个小毛病足以让他无法参加太空计划\N{\rE}A little thing but enough to keep him out of the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.24,0:45:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,最优秀的飞行员科尔戴维斯 却永远无法上太空\N{\rE}Cole Davis is the best pilot who will never get to space.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.63,0:45:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我在过去15年里天天看这个景色\N{\rE}You know, I've been looking at this view every day for the last 15 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.84,0:45:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,但最近我有种第一次看到的感觉\N{\rE}But lately, it's like I'm seeing it for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.35,0:45:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波罗1号给这里留下了巨大的阴影\N{\rE}Apollo 1 cast a big shadow on this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.19,0:45:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,重新看到一些光明真好\N{\rE}It's nice to have some light back.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.78,0:45:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,好了\N{\rE}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.08,0:45:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 我总看到科尔每天晚上开车去那边\N{\rE}Hey, I keep seeing Cole drive out there every night.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.08,0:45:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,他在做什么\N{\rE}What's he doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.09,0:45:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,做园艺\N{\rE}Gardening.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.69,0:46:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,(34号发射场)
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.69,0:47:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,(阿波罗1号乘组的精神永垂不朽)
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.42,0:47:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- 准备好了吗  - 好了\N{\rE}You ready? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.05,0:47:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,好 听着 我们...带参议员参观一下\N{\rE}All right. Look, we just-- We give the senator a tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.39,0:47:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我们好好哄他30分钟 把这个地方运营下去\N{\rE}We play nice for 30 minutes. We keep the lights on.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.77,0:47:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,好 行吧\N{\rE}Okay. Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.39,0:47:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 怎么了  - 它在那里\N{\rE}-What? -She's just there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.10,0:47:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- 别...跑 - 不...\N{\rE}- Don't run. - No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.27,0:47:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- 千万别跑 别... - 等等 闭嘴\N{\rE}- Just don't run. Don't-- - Wait. [shushing] Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.15,0:47:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,不 你看 你把它吓跑了\N{\rE}No. See, you scared it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.28,0:47:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我刚吃过东西\N{\rE}I just ate.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.49,0:47:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,亨利 快...\N{\rE}Henry, come on! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.96,0:48:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我讨厌那只猫\N{\rE}I hate that cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.83,0:48:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我懂你的意思\N{\rE}I see what y-- you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.59,0:48:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这...猫真讨厌 - 你看到它看我的眼神了吗\N{\rE}- That's an asshole cat. - Did you see the look it gave me?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.13,0:48:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,它在嘲讽我\N{\rE}It's just taunting me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.97,0:48:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这是什么  - 是猫食\N{\rE}- What is that? - That's cat food.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.35,0:48:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- 有人在喂它 - 是谁\N{\rE}- Somebody's feeding that thing. - Who's doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.60,0:48:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,找出来 立刻查出是谁 立刻炒掉\N{\rE}Find them. Find them immediately, and fire them immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.48,0:48:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,戴维斯先生 长官 霍普参议员来了\N{\rE}Mr. Davis. Sir, uh, Senator Hopp is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.06,0:48:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,好 怎么了 你看起来很帅\N{\rE}All right. What? You look fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.77,0:48:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,参议员\N{\rE}Senator.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.44,0:48:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你好 戴维斯先生 - 参议员 我很荣幸\N{\rE}- Hello, Mr. Davis. Senator. What an honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.23,0:48:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我很荣幸 幸会 先生 - 幸会\N{\rE}It's an honor and a pleasure. - Very nice to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.86,0:48:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波罗11号太空舱已经运达\N{\rE}Well, the Apollo 11 capsule has arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.87,0:48:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,下周 我们会把它装在土星5号火箭上\N{\rE}and next week, we will be attaching it to the Saturn V rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.33,0:48:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是发射升空 带我们离开地球大气层的那个火箭\N{\rE}And that gets us off the ground and out of Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.54,0:48:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,这些都很了不起 但我得直说\N{\rE}Well, that's all very impressive, but I have to be up-front.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.34,0:48:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,佐治亚州今年洪水泛滥\N{\rE}Georgia had some devastating floods this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.63,0:48:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我要投票把这笔钱用于赈灾\N{\rE}And I'm voting to put this money toward our relief fund.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.97,0:48:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,这似乎有点自私 不是吗\N{\rE}That seems a little selfish, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.55,0:48:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你说什么  - 就是一种说法\N{\rE}- Excuse me? - Uh, that's a figure of speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.47,0:48:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他是这个意思 - 我的大多数投票人认为\N{\rE}- Here's what he means. - My voters mostly think
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.10,0:48:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在登月计划上花费过多\N{\rE}we are overspending on the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.73,0:49:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- 有意思 因为当我... - 哟呼\N{\rE}That's funny, because-- Yoo-hoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.35,0:49:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,不好意思 霍普参议员\N{\rE}Excuse me. Senator Hopp.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.44,0:49:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你可能不记得我了\N{\rE}Oh, you probably don't remember me,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.86,0:49:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,但你在我大二时来我学校做过演讲\N{\rE}but you spoke at my sophomore year of college.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.03,0:49:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,佐治亚理工学院 1955级\N{\rE}Georgia Tech. '55.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.20,0:49:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你是个大黄蜂校友\N{\rE}You're a Buzz?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.45,0:49:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是的 先生 - 我当然记得\N{\rE}Yes, sir. - Of course I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.58,0:49:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,那天 你的话激励了我\N{\rE}Your words inspired me that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.79,0:49:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你说“承诺意味着忠于一项事业”\N{\rE}You said, "Commitment means staying loyal to a cause."
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.71,0:49:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,两年后 我以优异的成绩毕业 现在我负责这个部门\N{\rE}Two years later, I graduated with honors. Now I run this department.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.92,0:49:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,1962年 你曾说过 你无论如何\N{\rE}You know, in '62, you said that you would fight
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.63,0:49:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,都会为肯尼迪的梦想而奋斗\N{\rE}for Kennedy's dream no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.67,0:49:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道登月任务在当时比现在受欢迎\N{\rE}I know that the moon mission was more popular back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.72,0:49:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果那个激励我 在国家航空航天局工作的人\N{\rE}but it would be just a shame
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.85,0:49:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,没能照当年的那些话去做\N{\rE}if the man whose words inspired me to work at NASA
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.10,0:49:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,就太可惜了\N{\rE}didn't live by those very same words.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.19,0:49:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- 那就太可惜了 不是吗  - 先生 你真是个了不起的人\N{\rE}- It would be a shame, wouldn't it? - Sir, you are just such a wonderful man.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.36,0:49:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,非常感谢\N{\rE}Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.53,0:49:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你真了不起\N{\rE}You are a wonderful man.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.91,0:49:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,她可真是个佐治亚州甜心美女\N{\rE}Isn't she just a wonderful Georgia peach here?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.99,0:49:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- 天啊 - 是\N{\rE}- Oh, my. - Oh. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.07,0:49:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你嘴真甜 - 是的\N{\rE}- You are so sweet. - Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.24,0:50:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我带你来一次贵宾级的参观吧 这是他们的保密项目\N{\rE}Let me take you on the special VIP tour they didn't tell you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.25,0:50:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好啊 - 太好了\N{\rE}- Oh, I'd love that. Wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.21,0:50:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,你会陪我一起参观吗\N{\rE}Do you go on this tour with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.21,0:50:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,当然会\N{\rE}I absolutely will.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.75,0:50:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你真好\N{\rE}That's so sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.38,0:50:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,她都热泪盈眶了 真吓人\N{\rE}She teared up. I mean, it's scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.13,0:50:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,挥手微笑\N{\rE}Wave and smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.51,0:50:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,拜拜\N{\rE}Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.06,0:50:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,太空计划不光臃肿又混乱\N{\rE}The space program is not only a bloated mess,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.89,0:50:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波罗号还是对上帝\N{\rE}but Apollo flies in the face of our creator
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.90,0:50:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,和我国国父的不敬 我想提醒大家 我们不...\N{\rE}and the true father of this country. I would remind you that we don't--
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.11,0:50:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我们搞定了霍普 还需要两票 看起来不会是范宁了\N{\rE}We landed Hopp. We need two more votes. Looks like it's not gonna be Vanning.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.07,0:50:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- 绝对不是范宁 - 接下来是库克参议员\N{\rE}- Definitely not Vanning. - Next, we have Senator Cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.70,0:50:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,库克有点吓人 我实话实说\N{\rE}Cook's a little scary. I'm not gonna lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.54,0:50:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,他是冷战时期的保守派\N{\rE}He's a Cold War conservative.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.41,0:50:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,他担心我们的预算 会从国防部的武器研发经费里出\N{\rE}He's worried that our budget takes away from weapons development at the DOD.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.75,0:50:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,好 参议员 有了N1火箭\N{\rE}Now, Senator, with the N1 rocket,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.80,0:50:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,苏联人还是有可能抢在我们前面登月\N{\rE}the Russians still could land on the moon before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.22,0:50:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我们接下来要向你展示的最新情报\N{\rE}What we're about to show you is our most recent intel
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.26,0:50:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,是他们登月后计划建造的东西\N{\rE}on what they plan to build if they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.52,0:51:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这些是照片  - 不是 先生\N{\rE}- And these are photos? - No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.81,0:51:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,是概念画 描绘可能的未来\N{\rE}Those are, uh, renderings of a possible future.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.90,0:51:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,未来的照片\N{\rE}Future photos?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.65,0:51:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,那是个激光炮\N{\rE}Is that a laser?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.65,0:51:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,它正对着地球开火 先生\N{\rE}It's going towards Earth, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.53,0:51:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- 它叫什么  - “要你命月球激光大杀器” 先生\N{\rE}- What are they calling it? -"Killer Lunar Laser Eliminator," sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.24,0:51:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- “要你命月球激光大杀器”  - 是 先生\N{\rE}-"Killer Lunar Laser Eliminator"? - Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.21,0:51:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,见鬼 厉害了\N{\rE}Damn it. That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.21,0:51:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,最后还有赫奇斯参议员\N{\rE}And, finally, we have Senator Hedges.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.67,0:51:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,他一直是阿波罗的粉丝\N{\rE}Now, he's always been a fan of Apollo,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.92,0:51:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,但州政党给他施压 叫他不得拨款\N{\rE}but he's getting pressure from his state party not to fund.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.22,0:51:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,他连呼吸都要对着媒体的镜头\N{\rE}He can't take in oxygen without a camera pointed at him,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.84,0:51:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,那我们就去请点扛摄像机的朋友来\N{\rE}and we're about to have a few of those around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.35,0:51:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,有什么问题吗\N{\rE}Any questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.51,0:51:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,没有 女士\N{\rE}No, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.31,0:51:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,那我们去搞定他吧\N{\rE}Well, let's get him then.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.85,0:51:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,大家好\N{\rE}- Hello, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.90,0:51:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,先生们\N{\rE}Gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.99,0:51:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我...很高兴能故地重游 各位\N{\rE}It's-- It's-- It's great to be back, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.11,0:52:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你们知道我有多喜欢阿波罗计划\N{\rE}You know how much I love the Apollo program.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.54,0:52:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,参议员 阿波罗10号只会绕月飞行\N{\rE}Senator. Apollo 10 will just be orbiting the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.21,0:52:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,但能给我们带来 11号在月球着陆的关键信息\N{\rE}But it's gonna get us information critical for the touchdown of 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.79,0:52:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- 比如着陆条件和地点 - 了不起\N{\rE}- Like landing conditions and location. - Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.09,0:52:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我们为你准备了专座 参议员 在你的支持者中间\N{\rE}And we've a special seat for you here, Senator, amongst your fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.59,0:52:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,为我吗 谢谢\N{\rE}For me? Oh. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.84,0:52:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波罗发射控制中心 现在可以开始\N{\rE}Apollo launch control, and we are go on the countdown
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.22,0:52:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波罗10号登月任务的倒计时了\N{\rE}for the Apollo 10 lunar mission at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.06,0:52:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,点火程序启动\N{\rE}We have ignition sequence start.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.40,0:52:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,五 四 三 二...\N{\rE}Five, four, three, two...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.94,0:52:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,所有引擎启动\N{\rE}All engines running.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.37,0:52:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,发射 火箭升空\N{\rE}Liftoff. We have liftoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.12,0:52:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,现在是整点后49分\N{\rE}Forty-nine minutes past the hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.75,0:52:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,发射塔已分离...\N{\rE}Tower clear. Tower clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.54,0:52:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,休斯敦 交给你了\N{\rE}Houston, she's all yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.36,0:53:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,壮观的发射 我都等不及回来看阿波罗11号了\N{\rE}Glorious launch. Can't wait to be right back here for Apollo 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.95,0:53:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我们非常感谢你的支持 参议员\N{\rE}We cannot thank you enough for your support, Senator.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.53,0:53:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,有件事会麻烦你们一下\N{\rE}It's gonna cost you more than a pair of binoculars.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.87,0:53:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我欠老家做新闻的人一个人情\N{\rE}I owe a favor to the news fellas back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.12,0:53:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望你能接受他们的出镜采访\N{\rE}I'd like you to give them an on-camera interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.13,0:53:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,参议员 我是最不适合出镜的人了\N{\rE}Uh, Senator, I'm the very last person that you want in front of a camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.51,0:53:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我...不接受采访的\N{\rE}Uh, I d-- I don't do interviews.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.59,0:53:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,但为你可以破例 赫奇斯参议员 我们很乐意\N{\rE}Except for you, Senator Hedges. We would be delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.47,0:53:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,这女士很机智\N{\rE}Smart lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.43,0:53:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 晚安 - 晚安\N{\rE}- Good night. - Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.14,0:53:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉\N{\rE}Kelly?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.10,0:53:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,没事的\N{\rE}It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.44,0:53:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,一切尽在掌握\N{\rE}Got it all under control.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.49,0:54:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,(好样的 阿波罗)
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.93,0:54:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- 嘿 - 嘿\N{\rE}Hey. - Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.43,0:54:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你也可以休息一晚的\N{\rE}You're entitled to a night off too, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.06,0:54:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我若休息 那就是睡觉\N{\rE}If I am, it's to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.73,0:54:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你真的有家吗\N{\rE}Oh, you actually have a house?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.94,0:54:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我还以为你在办公室睡呢\N{\rE}I thought you slept at the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.65,0:54:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,对 通常是 但...我有时和珍妮一起睡\N{\rE}Well, yeah. Usually. But, uh... Well, I mean, sometimes I sleep with Jenny.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.32,0:54:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 是 她一定很棒\N{\rE}Oh, yeah. Right. Oh. I'm sure she's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.78,0:54:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,珍妮吗 对 确实\N{\rE}Jenny? Yeah. She-- She is.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.66,0:54:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,想认识一下吗\N{\rE}You wanna meet her?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.41,0:54:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好啊 - 好 珍妮会喜欢你的 来\N{\rE}- Yeah. - Yeah. She'll love you. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.43,0:55:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,珍妮 这是凯莉\N{\rE}Jenny. Jenny, uh, this is Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.18,0:55:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉 这就是珍妮\N{\rE}Kelly, meet Jenny.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.60,0:55:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,跟我战争中开的那架一样\N{\rE}She's just like the one I flew in the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.73,0:55:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我把它放在这里 方便在周末开出去兜兜风 省时间\N{\rE}Keep her here so I can get my flight hours on the weekends. Saves time.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.52,0:55:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,很漂亮\N{\rE}She's quite a lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.36,0:55:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rE}Yeah. She is.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.57,0:55:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- 想飞一圈吗  - 不了\N{\rE}- Wanna go up? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.07,0:55:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你确定  - 确定\N{\rE}- You sure? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.91,0:55:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,好 来吧\N{\rE}Okay. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.95,0:55:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我带你看第二美的景色\N{\rE}Show you the second-best view.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.39,0:55:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- 看见那些深色的部分了吗  - 看见了\N{\rE}- You see those dark parts there? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.68,0:55:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我们称之为“月海”\N{\rE}We call them the seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.06,0:55:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,月海里的重力更强一些 所以...\N{\rE}The gravity is stronger in the seas, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.48,0:56:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我们研究过在每一片月海里着陆的情况\N{\rE}We've looked to land in, uh, pretty much every single one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.11,0:56:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,有澄海\N{\rE}You got the Sea of Serenity.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.19,0:56:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,危海 我们很快便排除了这个\N{\rE}Sea of Crises. We crossed that one off the list pretty quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.32,0:56:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,对 这个名字不利于宣传\N{\rE}- Yeah. That's bad PR.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.03,0:56:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我们最后决定在宁静海着陆\N{\rE}And then we finally settled on, uh, the Sea of Tranquility.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.16,0:56:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,那是最佳地点\N{\rE}That's the sweet spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.83,0:56:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,这么一想 我...对月球的了解\N{\rE}You know, come to think about it, I-- I know a lot more about the moon
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.25,0:56:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,远远超过我对你的了解\N{\rE}than I know about you by a long shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.21,0:56:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我甚至不知道你是哪里人\N{\rE}I don't even know where you're from.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.13,0:56:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,堪萨斯\N{\rE}Kansas.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.68,0:56:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,来自堪萨斯的凯莉\N{\rE}Kelly from Kansas.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.81,0:56:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,堪萨斯的凯莉 你是怎么进入广告这一行的\N{\rE}How'd you get into advertising, Kelly from Kansas?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.68,0:56:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我爸爸离开时我四岁 妈妈失去了房子\N{\rE}Uh, well, I was four when my dad left, and my mom lost the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.77,0:56:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我们住在汽车里\N{\rE}We lived in a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.61,0:56:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,一个教堂给了她一份卖曲奇罐的工作\N{\rE}And... ...a church gave her a job selling cookie tins.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.41,0:56:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,所以她想了个点子 如果由我挨家挨户推销就能卖出更多\N{\rE}So, she had this idea that we'd sell more if it was me going door-to-door.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.58,0:56:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊 聪明的女士\N{\rE}Oh, yeah. Smart lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.75,0:57:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,曲奇罐 然后卖吸尘器 我长大些就转而卖美容用品\N{\rE}Cookie tins, then it was vacuums, then beauty goods when I got older.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.21,0:57:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 我和我妈周游全国\N{\rE}Yeah. Traveling the country, me and my mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.38,0:57:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的生活就是这样重回正轨的\N{\rE}It's how we got back on our feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.51,0:57:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我很遗憾你不得不经历这些\N{\rE}Well, I'm sorry you went through that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.85,0:57:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,不必 我...\N{\rE}Well, don't be. I...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.02,0:57:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,对 我很小就学会了如何生存\N{\rE}Yeah. I learned early on how to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.44,0:57:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,而且家家都有本难念的经\N{\rE}Plus, we all have our share of tough breaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.58,0:57:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,亨利跟我说了 心房颤动和你被计划除名的事\N{\rE}Henry told me about the A-fib and you getting kicked out of the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.04,0:57:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我得去跟亨利聊聊\N{\rE}Hmm. I'm gonna have to have a little conversation with Henry.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.63,0:57:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,不过我并不完全赞同你的说法\N{\rE}You know, I don't totally agree with you though.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.22,0:57:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- 怎么讲  - 我就是不...\N{\rE}- How's that? Well, I just don't--
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.68,0:57:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我不认为我们的悲伤故事\N{\rE}I don't think that our sad stories are supposed to
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.73,0:58:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,就该教会我们如何在世上生存\N{\rE}teach us how to survive the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.02,0:58:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为它们应该激励我们去改变世界\N{\rE}I think they're supposed to make us wanna change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.32,0:58:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,科尔\N{\rE}Cole!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.23,0:58:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,巴兹正在试图短路发动你的科迈罗\N{\rE}Buzz is trying to hot-wire your Camaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.65,0:58:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托 天啊\N{\rE}Come on, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.32,0:58:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,那么...\N{\rE}Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.41,0:58:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,你最好去阻止他\N{\rE}You better go stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.75,0:58:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rE}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.10,0:58:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,(卫星汽车旅馆)
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.15,0:58:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,老天\N{\rE}Jesus!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.15,0:58:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我们得谈谈\N{\rE}- We need to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.78,0:58:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,阿凯 你的工作做得十分出色\N{\rE}You have done outstanding work, Kel.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.20,0:58:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,公众的兴趣大大提高了\N{\rE}Public interest is way up.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.83,0:59:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,你搞定了参议员们 确保发射能顺利进行\N{\rE}You landed the senators and secured the launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.46,0:59:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你就闯进我的旅店房间\N{\rE}And that's why you broke into my motel room?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.50,0:59:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,作为感谢吗\N{\rE}As a thank-you?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.75,0:59:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我们知道全世界都会盯着我们看\N{\rE}Now that we know the whole world will be watching,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.17,0:59:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不容有失\N{\rE}we can't afford to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.01,0:59:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我们必须准备好呈献一个备用版本的\N{\rE}We need to be prepared to present an alternate version
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.68,0:59:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,登月任务\N{\rE}of the moon landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.56,0:59:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,一个备用版本\N{\rE}An alternate version?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.64,0:59:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,阿尔忒弥斯版本\N{\rE}The... Artemis version.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.02,0:59:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,(绝密 阿尔忒弥斯计划)
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.52,0:59:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,她是阿波罗的孪生姐姐 也就是“备胎”\N{\rE}She was the twin sister of Apollo, uh, you know, the backup.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.52,0:59:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我们必须准备好拍一个小短片\N{\rE}So we just need to be ready to shoot a little picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.03,0:59:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,向人们展示宇航员在月球上行走\N{\rE}Something showing us, you know, up there walking around,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.66,0:59:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,朝镜头挥手\N{\rE}waving at the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.45,0:59:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你是说作假  - 如果一切顺利 短片永远也用不上\N{\rE}- You mean, to fake it? - All goes well, we never use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.87,0:59:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,但万一...\N{\rE}But if not...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.17,0:59:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我为什么从没坐过牢吗\N{\rE}You know why I never went to prison?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.01,0:59:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,大概知道 但你说吧\N{\rE}Probably, but humor me.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.72,0:59:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我见好就收\N{\rE}'Cause I quit while I'm ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.93,1:00:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,这么大的事没法保密 这里有成千上万的员工\N{\rE}Can't keep a secret this big. Thousands of people work here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.68,1:00:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,也有成千上万人 在一个沙漠中的保密地点工作\N{\rE}Well, thousands of people work at a classified location in the desert
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.35,1:00:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,他们在对一个外星飞行器舰队做实验\N{\rE}that experiments on a fleet of extraterrestrial pods
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.48,1:00:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,是我们从海底捞上来的\N{\rE}that we found at the bottom of the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.94,1:00:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,你从来没听说过吧\N{\rE}And you never heard about that, did ya?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.61,1:00:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托 没这回事\N{\rE}Come on, that's not true.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.99,1:00:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,也许没有 也许有\N{\rE}Uh, maybe it is, maybe it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.79,1:00:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,但有一件事是可以肯定的\N{\rE}But the one thing you can be sure of
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.62,1:00:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,全世界都将看到美国人 在月球上插上美国国旗\N{\rE}is that the world will watch Americans plant an American flag on the moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.59,1:00:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你是说尼克松总统支持这么干\N{\rE}And you are telling me that President Nixon supports this?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.68,1:00:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,可能会 他还不知情\N{\rE}He probably would. He doesn't know about it
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.06,1:00:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,同样 科尔戴维斯也会永远蒙在鼓里\N{\rE}in the same way that Cole Davis will never know about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.31,1:00:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,这应该不是个问题\N{\rE}And that shouldn't be a problem
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.10,1:00:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,毕竟虽然你们越走越近\N{\rE}considering what else you haven't shared with him
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.44,1:00:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,但你还是有些事瞒着他\N{\rE}while you've grown closer.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.61,1:01:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,那么帅气的一个人会怎么想...\N{\rE}I mean, what would a clean-cut guy like that think about--
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.07,1:01:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你已经说得很清楚了\N{\rE}You made your point.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.03,1:01:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,谁也摆脱不了自己的过往\N{\rE}No one can outrun their past.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.70,1:01:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,但我可以永远抹除一个人的黑历史\N{\rE}But I can make it go away. Forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.33,1:01:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,不必再逃亡\N{\rE}No more running.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.84,1:01:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我得需要助理帮忙\N{\rE}I'm gonna need my assistant.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.59,1:01:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,当然\N{\rE}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.80,1:01:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会给你配一个安全特工团队\N{\rE}And we'll get you a team of secure agents.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.72,1:01:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 你手里最厉害 但却没人听说过的导演是谁\N{\rE}Now, who's the best director you've got that no one's ever heard of?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.90,1:01:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,你会喜欢他的\N{\rE}You're gonna love him.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.53,1:01:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,(政府财产 非请莫入)
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.03,1:01:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,这是基地里最偏远的飞机库\N{\rE}This is the most remote hangar on the base.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.07,1:01:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,没有我的允许 任何人不得出入\N{\rE}No one can go in or out without my permission.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.24,1:01:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,等等 任何人 连科尔都不行\N{\rE}Wait, no one? Not even Cole?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.70,1:01:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,科尔尤其不行\N{\rE}Especially not Cole.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.08,1:01:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,难以置信 凯莉\N{\rE}Unbelievable, Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.59,1:01:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你找人强行把我拖上飞机\N{\rE}You have me... ...forced onto a plane,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.96,1:01:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,把我带到这该死的佛罗里达\N{\rE}and brought to godforsaken Florida!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.72,1:02:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,能松手吗\N{\rE}Do you mind?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.26,1:02:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我是美国导演工会成员\N{\rE}I'm a member of the DGA.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.47,1:02:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,不能被这样粗暴对待\N{\rE}I will not be treated this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.81,1:02:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我要给经纪人打电话 - 不行\N{\rE}- I am calling my agent. - You can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.27,1:02:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我这就打给你看\N{\rE}Watch me.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.35,1:02:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,记住 我们谈过的 这是安保级别很高的政府项目\N{\rE}Remember we talked about this. This is a high-security government job.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.69,1:02:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我给你的报价翻倍 - 好吧\N{\rE}- I'm doubling your quote. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.90,1:02:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,还有奖金\N{\rE}With a bonus.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.07,1:02:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,对 唯一的条件是不能让任何人知道 我们在干什么\N{\rE}Yes. The only caveat being that no one can ever know what we're doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.91,1:02:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这我无法接受 - 他们会枪毙你\N{\rE}- I cannot accept that. - They will shoot you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.87,1:02:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,预算是多少\N{\rE}What is my budget?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.87,1:02:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你花多少钱都行 只要把这里变成月球\N{\rE}Your budget is whatever it costs to turn this into the moon
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.62,1:02:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,拍出两个半小时的片子来\N{\rE}for two-and-a-half hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.79,1:02:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,比《宾虚》短\N{\rE}It's shorter than Ben-Hur.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.52,1:02:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要在那边摆一台装满汽水的冰箱\N{\rE}I will need a fridge full of Tab over there.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.10,1:02:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,和一大群不会提问的手下\N{\rE}And an army of minions who don't ask questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.78,1:03:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉 这些都不是真正的演员\N{\rE}Kelly, these aren't real actors.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.21,1:03:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你只能用他们 这是最好的情况了\N{\rE}- Well, this is the best you're gonna get.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.42,1:03:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,尼尔身高1.8米 谁是1.8米高\N{\rE}Neil's 5'11". Anybody 5'11"?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.17,1:03:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,好 其他人散了吧\N{\rE}Okay. The rest of you are dismissed.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.80,1:03:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- 选吧 - 等等 你\N{\rE}- Take your pick. - Mmm. Hold on. You.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.84,1:03:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你来做我的私人助理\N{\rE}You're gonna be my personal assistant.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.17,1:03:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我就叫你约瑟夫 这样有什么事你不会往心里去\N{\rE}I'll just call you Joseph so you can't take things personally.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.55,1:03:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,随便站一边去吧\N{\rE}Go stand somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.84,1:03:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,好 能把墨镜都摘了吗\N{\rE}All right. Can we take these sunglasses off, please,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.14,1:03:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,好让我看到你们的眼睛 相信你们的话\N{\rE}so I can see your eyes and believe your truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.10,1:03:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,好 我要每个人来一段独白\N{\rE}Now, I want each of you to do a monologue.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.89,1:03:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,最好是经典桥段 但是老天啊\N{\rE}Preferably something classical, and by God,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.10,1:03:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,千万别给我来七遍《哈姆雷特》\N{\rE}don't make me watch seven Hamlets.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.73,1:03:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你到时候看不见他们的脸 都戴着头盔呢\N{\rE}You're not gonna see their faces. They're wearing helmets.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.82,1:03:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,什...\N{\rE}Wh--
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.78,1:03:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 那我如何\N{\rE}All right, how do I convey
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.07,1:03:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,在不让观众看到人脸的情况下\N{\rE}the gripping fear of being on the moon for the first time
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.70,1:03:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,展示第一次登月那揪心的恐惧\N{\rE}if we can't show a human face?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.41,1:03:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,表演是一种运动 凯莉\N{\rE}Acting is a sport, Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.66,1:03:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- 需要能量 身体... - 我把设备放哪\N{\rE}- It is energy, body, bu-- Where do I set up?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.17,1:03:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,爱德华\N{\rE}Edvard?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.83,1:04:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你怎么进来的  - 从门口走进来的\N{\rE}- How did you get in here? - I just walked through the door.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.25,1:04:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“此事说出去会害我们被杀” 这句话你哪儿不明白\N{\rE}What part of "talking about this is gonna get us killed" do you not understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.18,1:04:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- 而且他是纽约动作最慢的摄影指导 - 我来选摄影师\N{\rE}- And he's the slowest DP in New York. - I pick the cinematographer.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.80,1:04:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- 写在合同里呢 - 什么 你没有合同\N{\rE}- It's in my contract. - What? You don't have a contract.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.18,1:04:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,他最棒 所有的摄影指导动作都慢\N{\rE}He's the best, and all DPs are slow.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.93,1:04:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉 我们最需要的\N{\rE}What we need to have a serious conversation about, Kelly,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.81,1:04:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,就是美术指导\N{\rE}is production design, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.19,1:04:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我们用什么材料来仿造月球表面\N{\rE}What materials are we using to recreate the lunar surface?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.32,1:04:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,月球就是块大石头 对吧\N{\rE}It's just a big rock, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.28,1:04:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我没法这样工作 凯莉\N{\rE}I can't work like this, Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.58,1:04:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你是了解我这一点的\N{\rE}You know this about me. Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.58,1:04:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要细节\N{\rE}I need details.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.12,1:04:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要细节 具体细节\N{\rE}We need details. Specifics.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.21,1:04:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,是多尘 多石还是有风 光源是怎样的\N{\rE}Is it dusty, rocky, windy? What is the light source? Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.84,1:04:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- 就是太阳咯 大灯 - 别自作聪明 爱德华\N{\rE}- It's the sun. Big light. - Do not smart-mouth me, Edvard.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.80,1:04:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,太阳和着陆区的位置关系是怎样的\N{\rE}And what is the sun's position in relation to the landing area?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.60,1:04:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要建一个仿制版吗 我们有计划吗\N{\rE}And are we building a replica? Do we have a plan?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.68,1:04:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我们有宇航服吗  演员穿上宇航服如何行动\N{\rE}Do we have suits, and how do people move in those suits?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.23,1:05:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,还有 凯莉 太空里到底什么样子\N{\rE}And what, Kelly, does space even look like?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.77,1:05:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我...得躺一下\N{\rE}You know, I gotta-- I gotta lie down.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.77,1:05:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我的拖车呢\N{\rE}Where is my trailer?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.82,1:05:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们得想办法 把那个模拟室里的一切都照搬过来\N{\rE}We need to find a way to copy everything in that simulation room.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.20,1:05:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好的 - 尽快\N{\rE}- Okay. - ASAP.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.83,1:05:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,等等 我有拖车吗\N{\rE}Wait a second. Do I even have a trailer?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.08,1:05:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你不说话我也知道\N{\rE}Your silence tells me what I already know.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.04,1:05:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,你还没想过怎样复刻月球\N{\rE}You haven't thought about how to recreate the moon,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.08,1:05:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- 怎么会想拖车的事  - 我觉得我们该找库布里克了\N{\rE}- why would you think about a trailer? - I think we should've gotten Kubrick.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.13,1:05:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我们必须把新的飞船做对了\N{\rE}We've got to get this new ship right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.00,1:05:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,阿姆斯特朗很生气\N{\rE}I mean, Armstrong, he was pissed off
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.76,1:05:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们不能再惹他了 - 抱歉\N{\rE}- and we can't have that again. - Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.88,1:05:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,伙计...\N{\rE}Buddy, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.93,1:05:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,等等...这些都是敏感材料\N{\rE}Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa. This is sensitive material.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.97,1:05:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- 亨利... - 不行 你不能待在这里\N{\rE}- Henry. Henry. - Uh-uh. You can't be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.89,1:05:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,这些照片是为了企鹅出版社的档案书拍的\N{\rE}These photos are for the archival book that Penguin is doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.68,1:05:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么书  - 对 你没收到备忘录\N{\rE}- What book? - Yeah, didn't you get the memo?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.48,1:05:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- 没有 - 什么 你要写前言\N{\rE}- No. - What? You're writing the foreword.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.94,1:05:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我...写前言  - 对 是啊\N{\rE}- I-- I'm writing the foreword? - Yeah, absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.77,1:05:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我  - 没错\N{\rE}- Me? - Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.32,1:05:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我从没写过前言 - 编辑想听听你的话\N{\rE}- I've never written a foreword. - The editor wants to hear from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.69,1:05:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们都想 - 他要我写\N{\rE}- We all do. - He wants me to write it?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.99,1:05:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,别这么谦虚好吗 我们给你拍一张和...\N{\rE}Don't be so humble, all right? Let's get a photo of you with the--
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.32,1:05:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- 登月舱的合影 - 我可以写 但...\N{\rE}- with the LEM. - I mean, I can do it, but--
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.91,1:05:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,说“我们要登月了”\N{\rE}Say, "we're going to the moon."
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.12,1:05:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们要登月了 - 真不错\N{\rE}- We're going to the moon. - There you go!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.79,1:06:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,奥尔德林和阿姆斯特朗 每一个动作都要练习\N{\rE}Aldrin and Armstrong will practice every single movement that they make,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.96,1:06:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,在这里练好几个月\N{\rE}um, right here for months.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.83,1:06:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- 真了不起 - 是\N{\rE}- That is incredible. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.21,1:06:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是月球表面\N{\rE}So, this is, like, the surface of the moon?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.46,1:06:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是 这... - 对\N{\rE}- Well, yeah. It's-- - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.59,1:06:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,是我们最接近的模拟\N{\rE}It's our best approximation.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.47,1:06:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,这看起来就像个肮脏的海滩 我不信 不可能\N{\rE}This just looks like a dirty beach. I don't believe it. No.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.88,1:06:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是按...我们得到的沉积物做的 - 约瑟夫\N{\rE}- It is-- It's based off sediment we got. - Joseph.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.84,1:06:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,来自航天局\N{\rE}It's from NASA--
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.76,1:06:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,等等 我不相信这就是国家航空航天局\N{\rE}Wait. I do not believe this is what NASA uses
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.64,1:06:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,用来登月的装备 你别告诉我...不行\N{\rE}to go to the moon. You cannot tell me-- No.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.81,1:06:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我要你们假装抱着母亲在沙漠里行走\N{\rE}Want you to walk as if you're carrying your mother across the desert.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.90,1:06:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,她很脆弱 但也很重\N{\rE}She's frail but also heavy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.77,1:06:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,等等 嘿\N{\rE}Oh. Whoa. Hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.78,1:06:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- 真抱歉 嘿 对不起 - 不能拍...\N{\rE}- So sorry. Hey. Sorry. - Oh, no, no. No.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.32,1:06:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这是机密 你不能... - 斯图 没事\N{\rE}- This is classified. You're not allow-- - Stu, we're good.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.11,1:06:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是机密 - 没事 这是为那本书拍的\N{\rE}- Very classified. - We're good here. This is for the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.95,1:06:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你会听说的\N{\rE}No, you'll hear about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.07,1:06:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我要写前言\N{\rE}I'm doing the foreword,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.99,1:06:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你很快会听说的 - 好吧\N{\rE}- so you'll hear about it soon. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.33,1:06:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我这个阿姆斯特朗是个总爱抱怨的烂人 我们得重新选角\N{\rE}My Armstrong is a whiny, little bitch. We have to recast.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.16,1:06:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我们不重新选角\N{\rE}No-- We're not recasting.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.33,1:06:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 那就平庸着拍吧\N{\rE}All right. Well, mediocre it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.04,1:06:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,爱德华 我的太阳呢\N{\rE}Edvard! Where is my sun?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.34,1:06:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rE}Nice!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.34,1:06:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- 非常好 - 至少来个倒数啊\N{\rE}- Very nice. - A countdown at least.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.59,1:06:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,好 再开一次\N{\rE}Okay. Try it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.84,1:06:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我再开一次 - 从三倒数\N{\rE}- Gonna try it again. - Do a three, two, one!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.47,1:06:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- 拜托 - 满意吗\N{\rE}- Come on! Ah! - Happy?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.55,1:06:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,约瑟夫 给我拿汽水来\N{\rE}J-- Joseph, bring me my Tab.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.85,1:06:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,你得来找我 因为我眼都瞎了\N{\rE}You're gonna have to find me 'cause I can't see a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.10,1:07:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托 拿个汽水要多久\N{\rE}Come on. How long does it take to give someone a Tab?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.23,1:07:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我的手就在这里\N{\rE}My hand's right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.81,1:07:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,一定会很棒的 你们都该聚过来\N{\rE}Uh, this will be great. You guys should all come around
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.81,1:07:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们来给那本书拍一张 - 很好吧\N{\rE}- and we'll do a shot for the book. - Great?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.98,1:07:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 各位 这么说如何 “我们要登月了”\N{\rE}Hey, how about this? Everybody, "We're going to the moon!"
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.53,1:07:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要登月了\N{\rE}We're going to the moon!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.40,1:07:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我好像眨眼了 再拍一张\N{\rE}My eyes might have been closed. You wanna do one more?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.24,1:07:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,最近没看到你\N{\rE}I haven't seen you around lately.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.83,1:07:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,彼此彼此\N{\rE}Well, I can say the same thing about you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.83,1:07:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么一次就系好了\N{\rE}How do you do it on the first try?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.54,1:07:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,这又不是多复杂的事 好 准备好了吗\N{\rE}It's not rocket science. Okay. You good?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.05,1:07:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- 那些问题 我... - 是的\N{\rE}- About the questions, I-- - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.26,1:07:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我都看过了 没有关于阿波罗1号的 他们答应过我 好吗\N{\rE}I went over them. Nothing about Apollo 1. They promised me. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.01,1:07:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,你会表现得很好的 明白吗\N{\rE}You're gonna be great. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.93,1:07:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,去吧\N{\rE}Go on.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.01,1:07:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好 - 上\N{\rE}- Okay. - Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.69,1:07:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,戴维斯先生 你是我们口中的“采访困难户”\N{\rE}Mr. Davis. You are what we call "a tough get."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.60,1:07:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,哪有 谢谢\N{\rE}Ha! No. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.69,1:07:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我们将看到尼尔阿姆斯特朗 和巴兹奥尔德林走上月球表面\N{\rE}Is there any legal importance to what we'll be watching
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.98,1:07:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,这有什么法律方面的重要意义吗\N{\rE}when Neil Armstrong and Buzz Aldrin walk on the lunar surface?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.61,1:07:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,他们着陆的区域会被视为归美国所有吗\N{\rE}Will the area they land on be considered property of the United States?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.66,1:08:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要送一块匾上去 写着“我们为全人类的和平而来”\N{\rE}We're sending a plaque that says, "We came in peace for all mankind."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.33,1:08:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,那正是我们的意思\N{\rE}And that is precisely what we mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.91,1:08:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,国家航空航天局还会留下其他什么东西\N{\rE}What else will NASA leave behind?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.46,1:08:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,足迹 一面美国国旗和12袋粪便\N{\rE}Footprints, an American flag and 12 bags of feces
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.79,1:08:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,他们跟我说了很多次不要提 但是...\N{\rE}that I was told many times that I should not bring up, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.75,1:08:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我们真该早点让他接受采访\N{\rE}Should've put him in front of a camera sooner.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.72,1:08:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你戴着一枚阿波罗胸针\N{\rE}You wear an Apollo pin.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.43,1:08:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rE}I do. Um,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.97,1:08:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,是阿波罗1号乘组的太太们\N{\rE}the wives of Apollo 1's men,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.51,1:08:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,在丈夫们牺牲后送我的\N{\rE}after we lost them, they gave me this.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.60,1:08:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,在那悲剧的一天 你是发射主管\N{\rE}You were launch director on that tragic day.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.52,1:08:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波罗1号出了什么故障\N{\rE}What went wrong with Apollo 1?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.49,1:08:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,用你自己的话说 发生了什么\N{\rE}- In your own words, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.99,1:08:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,帮我回顾一下\N{\rE}Take me back.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.29,1:08:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,好 我来给你列举一些事实\N{\rE}Okay. Here's some facts for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.33,1:08:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,《纽约时报》报道\N{\rE}The New York Times reported
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.50,1:08:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,那艘飞船曾有两万份安全事件报告\N{\rE}there were 20,000 safety reports filed about that ship.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.21,1:08:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,实在太多 以至于加斯格里森 用一个柠檬表示自己的不满\N{\rE}So many, that Gus Grissom hung a lemon outside it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.47,1:09:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 乘组 待确认 位置\N{\rE}All right, crew. To be confirmed. Location.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.47,1:09:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,着火了\N{\rE}Flame!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.47,1:09:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,驾驶舱里失火了\N{\rE}We've got a fire in the cockpit.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.56,1:09:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,快出去\N{\rE}Let's get out!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.47,1:09:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,戴维斯先生 你读过那些报告吗\N{\rE}Mr. Davis? Did you read those reports?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.48,1:09:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,发射台主管 快进去救他们\N{\rE}Pad leader, get in there and help 'em.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.15,1:09:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,发射台主管 盯着C3\N{\rE}Pad leader, stay on C3.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.11,1:09:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,戴维斯先生 你读过那些报告吗\N{\rE}Mr. Davis? Did you read those reports?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.82,1:09:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你读过那些报告吗  - 我当然读过那些报告\N{\rE}- Did you read those reports? - Of course I read the reports.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.45,1:09:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,每一份都读过\N{\rE}I read every single one of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.66,1:09:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,独立供电测试期间 氧气压力过高的同时遇到了线路故障\N{\rE}Overpressured oxygen and a bad wire on a "plugs-out" test.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.67,1:09:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我本该查出一切问题的 我看漏了 辜负了他们\N{\rE}I was supposed to catch everything, and I missed it. And I failed them.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.71,1:09:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我余生中的每一天都会为此感到愧疚\N{\rE}And I will live with that every single day for the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.55,1:09:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,人渣 这是你想引述的原话吗\N{\rE}Is that the quote that you were looking for, you piece of shit?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.18,1:09:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,让我跟你的老板通话 立刻 马上\N{\rE}Get me on the phone with your boss. Now. Now!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.60,1:09:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,等等 你干什么 采访还有20分钟\N{\rE}Oh, uh, wait. W-What are you doing? We have another 20 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.89,1:09:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,去死吧\N{\rE}Go to hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.98,1:09:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,别生我的气 害死三个宇航员的人不是我\N{\rE}Don't be angry with me. I'm not the reason three astronauts are dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.40,1:10:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你再提一句那些宇航员试试 - 嘿...别冲动\N{\rE}- Say one more thing about the astronauts. - Hey, hey, hey! Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.49,1:10:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,放开我 你再说一句试试\N{\rE}Get off me. Let me hear you say one more thing--
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.41,1:10:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你再提他们一句试试\N{\rE}Let me hear you say one more thing about them!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.20,1:10:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你不认识他们 你不准再提他们\N{\rE}You don't know those men! You don't talk about those men!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.37,1:10:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,放开我 放开\N{\rE}Get off me! Get off!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.16,1:10:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,放开\N{\rE}Get off!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.75,1:10:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,听懂了吗\N{\rE}Do you understand me?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.80,1:10:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我跟制作人们谈过了 他们同意不播出这段采访\N{\rE}So, I spoke to the producers, and they've agreed to seal the film
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.97,1:10:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,条件是阿姆斯特朗着陆后 给他们独家采访\N{\rE}if we give them the exclusive with Armstrong after he lands.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.85,1:10:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,不过我们失去了赫奇斯的支持 他要投反对票了\N{\rE}We lost Hedges though. He's voting no.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.98,1:10:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你说过他们不会问的 - 是的 他们撒谎了\N{\rE}- You said they wouldn't ask about it. - Yeah. Well... they lied.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.44,1:10:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,人们有时是会撒谎的 科尔\N{\rE}You know, people do that sometimes, Cole.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.07,1:10:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你也许可以说点假话 那也算为自己\N{\rE}You could have done yourself and this program a favor
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.07,1:10:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,和这登月计划帮了个忙 对吗\N{\rE}and maybe tried it yourself. Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.11,1:10:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,责怪国家航空航天局\N{\rE}Blame NASA.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.95,1:10:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,责怪这个体系\N{\rE}Blame the system.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.95,1:10:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,事关价值五亿美元的资金啊\N{\rE}I mean, there was half a billion dollars worth of funding on the line.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.62,1:10:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,撒谎对你来说一定轻而易举吧 毕竟你总在撒谎\N{\rE}Lying must be so easy for you when you do it all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.96,1:10:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,撒谎总是一个可选项\N{\rE}It's just always an option.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.17,1:10:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你该试试说真话 - 你装什么清高呢\N{\rE}- What you should try is the truth. - What is this sanctimonious bullshit?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.71,1:10:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我永远不会就那些人或那一天的事撒谎\N{\rE}I'm never going to lie about those men or that day.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.38,1:10:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,你明白吗\N{\rE}Do you understand that?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.46,1:11:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,随便你怎么看我\N{\rE}You think what you want about me,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.13,1:11:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,但因为不冷静 而让全人类登月梦破碎的人不是我\N{\rE}but I didn't cost the world a dream because I lost my goddamn cool.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.92,1:11:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这是34号发射场 发生阿波罗1号悲剧的地方\N{\rE}This is Launch Complex 34, where the Apollo 1 tragedy occurred.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.00,1:11:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,这是牺牲英雄的纪念碑\N{\rE}This is a tribute to our fallen heroes,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.71,1:11:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,这些勇敢的人为我们的成功铺平了道路\N{\rE}the brave men who paved the road to our success.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.34,1:11:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,请大家为他们默哀片刻\N{\rE}Please, let's take a moment of silence for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.36,1:12:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,爱德华 真令人称奇\N{\rE}Edvard, that looks incredible.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.69,1:12:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我完全看不到线缆 你怎么做到的\N{\rE}I can't see the wires at all. How did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.53,1:12:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是用了一块遮光板 很简单\N{\rE}I just put a flag. It's very simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.53,1:12:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,老办法了\N{\rE}Old school.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.45,1:12:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,不行 从头再来\N{\rE}No. Again. From the top.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.95,1:12:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,这次多加一些跳跃\N{\rE}And maybe let's get some more bounce this time.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.62,1:12:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你们可是在月球上啊\N{\rE}You are on the moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.25,1:12:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,好\N{\rE}Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.50,1:12:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- 天啊 - 我看不下去了 今天不行\N{\rE}- Oh, my God. - I-I can't. I can't with this day.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.38,1:12:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- 天啊 好 坚持住 - 约瑟夫 失火了\N{\rE}- Oh, dear. Uh-- Okay, hold on. Joseph, there's a fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.30,1:12:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我来\N{\rE}I got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.10,1:12:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,别忘记四步口诀\N{\rE}Don't forget to PASS.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.40,1:12:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,好 能放他们下来吗 算了 挂着吧\N{\rE}Okay. Can you bring them down? Actually, leave them up.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.73,1:12:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,让他们反思一下自己都干了什么\N{\rE}Let them think about what they did.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.82,1:12:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我放弃了 我去吃午饭\N{\rE}I give up. I'm taking lunch.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.82,1:12:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,你们明白自己干了什么吗  你们让她提早去吃午饭了\N{\rE}You see what you did? You made her take lunch early.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.87,1:12:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这都怪你们\N{\rE}That's on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.59,1:13:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我跟你赌5美元 你不擅长道歉\N{\rE}I'll bet you $5 you're bad at apologies.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.97,1:13:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我到处找你\N{\rE}I've been looking all over for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.26,1:13:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你欠我5块 - 我有个想法\N{\rE}- You owe me five bucks. - I got an idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.85,1:13:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\rE}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.93,1:13:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,来 去路易斯安那州的路上告诉你\N{\rE}Come on. I'll tell you on the way to Louisiana.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.39,1:13:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,不 你想尝试获得范宁的投票\N{\rE}No. You wanna take a shot at Vanning?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.48,1:13:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我给咱们弄到了晚餐邀请 就是今晚 走吧\N{\rE}I got us a dinner invite, for tonight. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.44,1:13:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,今晚 我们不可能赶得上 有800公里呢\N{\rE}Tonight? We're never gonna make it. It's 500 miles away.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.48,1:13:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我们能赶上 来 你得相信我\N{\rE}We're gonna make it. Come on. You gotta trust me.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.44,1:13:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,等等 不\N{\rE}Oh, wait. No.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.49,1:13:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不行... - 什么叫“不行”\N{\rE}- No, no, no. - What do you mean, "no"?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.82,1:13:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们不能...有其他...我们可以... - 你想不想要范宁支持\N{\rE}- We don't-- There's other-- We could-- - Do you want Vanning or not?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.70,1:13:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我不... - 来 我们走\N{\rE}- Ugh. No. I don't-- - Come on. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.16,1:13:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得我们可以乘民航 如果我们出发...\N{\rE}I think we could just take a commercial flight. If we left--
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.33,1:13:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,不行 现在没有民航航班\N{\rE}Nope. No commercial flights are flying right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.25,1:13:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,来 跳上来\N{\rE}Come on. Just hop on in.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.92,1:13:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,就是这样 你只管上来就行 你可以跳上来的 你行的\N{\rE}This is it. This is all you gotta do. You can hop up, you can get in.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.63,1:13:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- 脚踩那里 - 好吧 拿着我的鞋\N{\rE}- Put your foot there. Okay, well, take these.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.42,1:13:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- 听着 我们得走了 - 好\N{\rE}- Look, we gotta go. All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.88,1:13:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,等等...\N{\rE}Hold on. Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.51,1:13:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- 完美 - 等等\N{\rE}- Perfect. - Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.34,1:13:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,没问题\N{\rE}We're good.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.40,1:14:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,风景不错吧\N{\rE}You enjoying the view?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.77,1:14:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊 太美了\N{\rE}Wow! It's stunning!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.11,1:14:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我打赌你闭着眼呢\N{\rE}I bet your eyes are closed.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.74,1:14:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,没有\N{\rE}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.67,1:14:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我猜你还会些其他南方口音\N{\rE}So, I'm betting you have some other Southern accents
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.46,1:14:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,毕竟你“多才多艺” 会路易斯安那的吗\N{\rE}in that bag of tricks of yours. Can you do Louisiana?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.42,1:14:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,会 新奥尔良还是巴吞鲁日\N{\rE}Yeah. New Orleans or Baton Rouge?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.96,1:14:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- 用他老婆家乡的 - 好\N{\rE}- Wherever his wife's from. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.18,1:14:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,科尔戴维斯\N{\rE}Cole Davis.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.51,1:14:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你一定是凯莉琼斯小姐\N{\rE}And you must be Miss Kelly Jones.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.39,1:14:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,两位请进\N{\rE}Please come in, y'all.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.81,1:14:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,非常感谢你们邀请我们吃晚餐\N{\rE}Thank you so much for having us for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.18,1:14:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,好...我听说你是纽约城里人\N{\rE}Oh, now-- now, I was told you were a New York City type.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.98,1:14:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊 不是 我只是在那里工作 我是路易斯安那人\N{\rE}Oh, God, no. I just work there. I'm from Louisiana.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.44,1:14:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,土生土长的 也会落叶归根\N{\rE}Born and raised and, one day, buried.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.81,1:14:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我老家在弗吉尼亚 - 不会吧 我们是亲人啊\N{\rE}- I'm from Virginia. - No? We're family.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.57,1:14:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,特克斯里特尔总说 弗吉尼亚是得克萨斯的母亲\N{\rE}You know, Tex Ritter always said Virginia was the mother of Texas.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.15,1:14:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我们一直不知道父亲是谁 总怀疑是路易斯安那\N{\rE}Well, we never knew who the father was. We always suspected it was Louisiana.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.28,1:14:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我妈可喜欢这个笑话了\N{\rE}- Oh! - Huh? My mother loves that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.41,1:14:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是她想出来的 - 太有意思了\N{\rE}- She was the one that came up with it. - Oh, just so colorful.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.25,1:15:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你真有趣 - 你家可真漂亮\N{\rE}You're fun. - This is a beautiful home.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.83,1:15:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,参议员 竞选活动怎么样\N{\rE}So, h-how is the campaign going, Senator?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.21,1:15:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,说实话 政治更像是我的一项爱好\N{\rE}Truth be told, politics is more of a hobby to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.59,1:15:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,服事基督才是我的全职工作\N{\rE}Serving Christ, that's my full-time job.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.43,1:15:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,现在美国正有一场针对宗教的战争\N{\rE}You know, there's a war on religion in this country.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.98,1:15:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,有人说要怪科学\N{\rE}And some say science is to blame.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.94,1:15:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,是科学让我们今天齐聚一堂\N{\rE}Well, science is what brought us to this table.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.07,1:15:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你从阿波罗1号的事上学到了\N{\rE}You learned a little lesson on the provocation of pride
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.69,1:15:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,关于骄傲的一课 科尔 不是吗\N{\rE}on Apollo 1, now, didn't you, Cole?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.20,1:15:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,其实科学让我离上帝更近了 先生\N{\rE}Science has actually brought me closer to God, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.16,1:15:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,上帝用了六天创造了我们所知的一切\N{\rE}Took the Lord six days to put forth everything that we know as creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.04,1:15:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,第六天 他把这些交给我们管理\N{\rE}And on that sixth day, he gave us dominion over it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.42,1:15:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我个人认为这是一种责任\N{\rE}And, personally, I take that as a responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.96,1:15:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你听起来很虔诚\N{\rE}You sound like a man who knows his way to church.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.92,1:15:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得最能体现虔诚的方法\N{\rE}Well, I can't think of a greater act of faith
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.34,1:15:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,莫过于追逐星辰\N{\rE}than pursuing the stars.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.01,1:16:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“诸天述说上帝的荣耀 穹苍传扬他的作为”\N{\rE}"The heavens declare the glory of God. And the firmament shows us his handiwork."
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.02,1:16:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,这是乔琳娜最喜欢的诗篇句子之一\N{\rE}- That's one of Jolene's favorite Psalms.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.65,1:16:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,是这样 等我们的人从太空归来\N{\rE}You see, our men, when they come back from space,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.19,1:16:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,他们对上帝的信仰会更多 不会减少\N{\rE}they believe more in God, not less.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.99,1:16:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们登月时\N{\rE}But when we land on the moon,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.99,1:16:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,多亏了这位琼斯小姐 全球都能看到\N{\rE}and thanks to Miss Jones here, the world watches us do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.66,1:16:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望世界各地的人都能感受到 那种圣神的存在\N{\rE}And it's my hope that people everywhere feel the presence of that divine.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.33,1:16:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rE}Well...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.13,1:16:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你的话确实得让我好好想想 小伙子\N{\rE}...you've, uh, certainly given me a lot to think about, son.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.14,1:16:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你这推销还真有说服力啊\N{\rE}You really sold the hell out of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.35,1:16:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我没在推销\N{\rE}I wasn't selling.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.48,1:16:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,郑重声明 做真实的自己也能赢得人心\N{\rE}For the record, you can win people over just by being who you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.36,1:17:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我们现在不赶时间了 所以不必飞回去\N{\rE}You know, we're not in a rush, so we don't really have to fly home.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.41,1:17:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,那可不算飞\N{\rE}Ooh. That wasn't flying.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.59,1:17:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托 睁开眼睛\N{\rE}Come on. Open your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.98,1:17:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,相信我吗\N{\rE}You trust me?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.40,1:17:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,坐稳了\N{\rE}Hold tight.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.20,1:17:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,现在才是最好玩的 滑下来就行\N{\rE}Now, this is the fun part. Just slide off.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.87,1:17:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,完美\N{\rE}- Perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.25,1:18:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我过去对国家航空航天局的计划 有过诸多意见不一致的地方\N{\rE}I've had my disagreements with the NASA program in the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.93,1:18:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,但经过深思熟虑和反复祈祷后\N{\rE}But after a great deal of thought, and prayer,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.47,1:18:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我决定投赞成票\N{\rE}I've decided to vote yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.23,1:18:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,太好了
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.85,1:18:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,好样的\N{\rE}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.69,1:18:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我有样东西 你一定得看看\N{\rE}I have something that you need to see.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.99,1:19:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么... - 跟我来\N{\rE}- What-- - Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.07,1:19:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我之前不知道结果会如何 因为你根本看不透政客\N{\rE}Whoo! I didn't know which way it was gonna go, 'cause you can't tell with these guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.62,1:19:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我之前向来不喜欢这家伙 但我现在喜欢他了\N{\rE}I never liked that guy before, but... I like him now.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.29,1:19:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,太好了\N{\rE}All right!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.46,1:19:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这里好黑啊 你... - 快到了\N{\rE}It's so dark in here. You-- Almost there.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.63,1:19:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我有点害怕 - 好了 就在这里\N{\rE}I'm a little scared. Yeah, it's right around here.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.34,1:19:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,(对你的感谢有如登月往返)
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.21,1:19:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我们想对你表达谢意\N{\rE}We wanted to show you our appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.01,1:19:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- 天啊 这也太隆重了 - 谢谢\N{\rE}- Oh, my gosh. This is too much. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.39,1:19:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不敢相信 - 都是沃尔特的功劳\N{\rE}- I can't believe it. - It was all Walter.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.43,1:19:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,沃尔特 我知道这都是你操办的 对吧\N{\rE}Oh, Walter? I know that you did all of this, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.47,1:19:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- 出了点力而已 - 是 我知道是你\N{\rE}A little. That's all. - Yeah, I know you did.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.39,1:19:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- 大家都帮忙了 - 还不错吧\N{\rE}- They all helped. - Not too bad, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.99,1:19:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,趁我还没忘 给\N{\rE}Before I forget. Here.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.45,1:19:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这上面列出了 登月后你迈出第一步时可以说的话\N{\rE}It's a list of things for you to say when you take your first step.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.00,1:19:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我...知道所有人都在问你 就是想给你些点子\N{\rE}I-- I know everybody's asking you. I thought I'd give you some options.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.75,1:19:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我本来想说\N{\rE}Well, I was just gonna say,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.09,1:20:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“看这些酷酷的石头”之类的话\N{\rE}"Look at all those cool rocks," or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.46,1:20:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我能搞定的 凯莉 - 好\N{\rE}- I got this one, Kelly. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.84,1:20:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,不过谢谢你\N{\rE}And thank you, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.05,1:20:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,真心的 谢谢...你所做的一切\N{\rE}And I mean it. For, uh-- For everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.64,1:20:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得没有人比科尔戴维斯 更在乎这个计划\N{\rE}You know, I don't think anyone cares about this program more than Cole Davis.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.27,1:20:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,很高兴看见他有其他在乎的东西了\N{\rE}It's nice to see he's found something else to care about.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.13,1:20:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道我不是宇航员 但我能请你跳一支舞吗\N{\rE}I know I'm no, uh, astronaut, but can I steal you for a dance?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.05,1:20:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- 可以 - 可以 来\N{\rE}- Yes. Yes. - Yeah? Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.14,1:20:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你在数着日子 等待回到曼哈顿的那一天吗\N{\rE}So, you just counting down the days until you, uh, can get back to Manhattan?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.19,1:21:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,并没有\N{\rE}Not really.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.48,1:21:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rE}Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.59,1:21:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,往上...很好 好了 把灯搬过来\N{\rE}Up, up, up. Perfect. Right, now, move the light in.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.80,1:21:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,好 继续 别害羞\N{\rE}All right, keep going. Don't be shy.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.84,1:21:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,继续...\N{\rE}Keep going. Keep going. Keep going. Keep going. Keep going.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.39,1:21:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,充分利用 很好\N{\rE}Milk it. Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.18,1:21:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,女士们 觉得如何\N{\rE}Ladies, what do we think?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.44,1:21:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- 兰斯 太惊人了 - 很棒\N{\rE}- Lance, it's incredible. - It's great.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.90,1:21:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得还需要再来点尘土和更好的演员\N{\rE}I think it needs a little more dust and better actors,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.78,1:21:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,但我的要求被拒了\N{\rE}but I lost that battle.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.44,1:21:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我也就不纠结了\N{\rE}I will let it go.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.53,1:21:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,停 好\N{\rE}And stop. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.49,1:21:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我们有太阳了\N{\rE}We've got our sun.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.41,1:21:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我总是配合你编造的那些谎言\N{\rE}I always went along with every web you spun
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.54,1:22:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,要么是因为它们很有趣 要么我们是在骗坏人\N{\rE}because it was fun or, like, we were pulling one over on the bad guys,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.58,1:22:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,但这次的感觉...\N{\rE}but this feels--
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.63,1:22:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\rE}I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.50,1:22:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,就快完工了\N{\rE}We're almost done.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.97,1:22:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我送你的\N{\rE}This is from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.26,1:22:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,发射日礼物\N{\rE}It is for launch day.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.51,1:22:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,答应我 到时候再拆\N{\rE}Promise you will wait until then.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.23,1:22:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我答应 - 好\N{\rE}- I promise. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.27,1:22:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,记住 你们不是怪兽\N{\rE}Remember, you're not monsters.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.69,1:22:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,会跳那么高吗\N{\rE}Are they gonna be that high?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.94,1:22:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我只需要让他们的跳跃距离\N{\rE}Uh, I just need to give them any length
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.20,1:22:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,看起来像在月球上即可 但谢谢你的意见\N{\rE}that looks like they're on the moon. But thank you for the note.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.20,1:22:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,巴兹 动作幅度小一点\N{\rE}Buzz, take it down some.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.33,1:22:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,阿姆斯特朗 不要看我寻求肯定\N{\rE}And, Armstrong, stop looking at me for approval.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.49,1:22:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- 专心演好身处月球 把我当空气 - 他排练得很开心...\N{\rE}- Just be on the moon. I'm not here. He's having fun. He's having fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.17,1:22:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,他总是和我四目相交 别暗送秋波了 专心演身处月球\N{\rE}He keeps locking eyes with me. Stop flirting and be on the moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.30,1:22:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,昨天的科幻小说成为了今天的现实\N{\rE}Yesterday's science fiction is today's fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.35,1:22:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,方法虽然不同\N{\rE}The methods are different,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.76,1:23:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,但重要的是明天一早\N{\rE}but the important thing is that tomorrow morning,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.31,1:23:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,人类将飞向月球\N{\rE}man will lift off toward the moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.32,1:23:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上好 我是沃尔特克朗凯特\N{\rE}Good evening. I'm Walter Cronkite.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.74,1:23:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,在人类首次登月之旅的前夕\N{\rE}And on this eve of man's first flight toward a landing on the moon,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.75,1:23:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的准备工作都很顺利\N{\rE}all preparations go smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.29,1:23:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,天气预报状况良好\N{\rE}The weather prediction,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.71,1:23:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,还有宇航员们的帮助 尼尔阿姆...\N{\rE}along with the health of astronauts, Neil Arm--
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.70,1:23:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\rE}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.25,1:24:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你很会伤人心啊\N{\rE}Well, you know how to hurt a fella.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.71,1:24:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,礼貌性的电话都不打一个\N{\rE}No courtesy call?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.05,1:24:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有你的电话号码\N{\rE}Well, I don't have your number.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.76,1:24:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你逃跑了\N{\rE}You ran.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.43,1:24:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,这是你最擅长的事\N{\rE}That's what you do best.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.85,1:24:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你这个备用版本的登月是个错误 我原本就不该参与\N{\rE}Your alternate version is wrong. I never should've been a part of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.60,1:24:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我不干了\N{\rE}I quit.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.48,1:24:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,坐\N{\rE}Sit.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.20,1:24:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,今天你要扮演谁呢\N{\rE}So, who are we gonna be today?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.16,1:24:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我来看看\N{\rE}Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.24,1:24:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,(目的地:希思罗机场)
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.08,1:24:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,海伦帕克\N{\rE}Ooh, Helen Parker.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.41,1:24:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我打赌 你的英国口音一定很纯正\N{\rE}I bet you do a killer British accent.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.75,1:24:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你想一走了之 去当海伦 请便\N{\rE}You wanna take off and be Helen? Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.13,1:24:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,海伦不必提心吊胆地生活\N{\rE}Helen doesn't have to look over her shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.51,1:24:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,没有人会来找你的\N{\rE}No one is coming for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.80,1:25:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,除非呢\N{\rE}Unless?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.80,1:25:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,除非你向任何人透露 阿尔忒弥斯计划真实存在\N{\rE}Unless you ever tell anyone that Project Artemis was real,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.64,1:25:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,登月是虚假拍摄的\N{\rE}and the moon landing was fake.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.48,1:25:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,说到这个 计划有变\N{\rE}Oh, on that score, change of plans.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.74,1:25:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会播出备用版本的登月\N{\rE}we're going to air the alternate version.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.11,1:25:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,无论如何都播\N{\rE}No matter what.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.24,1:25:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,你们从来没打算播出真实的登月\N{\rE}Oh, you were never gonna broadcast the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.41,1:25:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,这不光是登月竞赛\N{\rE}This isn't just a race for the moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.41,1:25:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,而是哪一种意识形态说了算的竞赛\N{\rE}It is a race for which ideology gets to run things.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.42,1:25:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我让一个手下改装了登月舱摄像机 让它只传回声音\N{\rE}I got one of my men to rig the LEM camera so that it just beams back audio.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.88,1:25:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会把他们的声音同步到你的假舞台上\N{\rE}We're gonna sync with their sound and, uh, use your fake stage broadcast,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.18,1:25:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,从头到尾播出\N{\rE}start to finish.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.59,1:25:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,让我第一个代表美国感谢你\N{\rE}Let me be the first to thank you on behalf of America.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.73,1:25:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 别难过 人人都能得到想要的结果\N{\rE}Come on, don't feel bad. Everybody gets what they want.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.73,1:25:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以展开新生活 不必再逃避过往\N{\rE}You get a new life with no past to run from.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.28,1:26:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,全世界也不必在共产主义的月光下入眠\N{\rE}And the world doesn't have to sleep under a communist moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.99,1:26:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 巴拿马在召唤\N{\rE}- Okay. Panama beckons.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.21,1:26:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你最好快点 要赶不上飞机了 海伦\N{\rE}You better hurry. You're going to... miss your flight, Helen.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.63,1:26:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,这是为阿波罗号太空飞船上宇航员\N{\rE}This is a typical meal served to astronauts
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.76,1:26:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,提供的典型餐点\N{\rE}aboard Apollo space flights.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.64,1:26:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,燕麦片 吐司\N{\rE}Oatmeal, toast,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.97,1:26:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,和一个特制的零重力饮品袋 装的是能量早餐饮品“菓珍”\N{\rE}and a special zero-gravity pouch. Tang, the energy breakfast drink.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.77,1:26:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,其维生素C含量超过橙汁\N{\rE}And more vitamin C than orange juice.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.81,1:26:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,能量菓珍 太空人和地球家庭的选择\N{\rE}Energy Tang, for spacemen and Earth families.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.77,1:26:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,哥伦比亚广播公司呈献 《月球上的人》\N{\rE}CBS News presents Man On the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.41,1:26:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,讲述阿波罗11号的史诗之旅\N{\rE}The epic journey of Apollo 11
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.66,1:26:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,就在这历史性事件的前夕\N{\rE}on the eve of that historic event.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.58,1:26:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,本节目由西部电气赞助\N{\rE}Sponsored by Western Electric,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.21,1:26:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,西部电气 贝尔系统的制造和供应单位\N{\rE}manufacturing and supply unit of the Bell System.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.21,1:26:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,本节目由国际纸业赞助 好主意在这里继续...\N{\rE}And by the International Paper Company, where good ideas roll on...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.80,1:27:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,(阿波罗计划中的人们)
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.28,1:28:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,(假日酒店 祝阿波罗11号马到成功)
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.37,1:28:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,(私人活动 宇航员妻子的早午餐会)
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.22,1:28:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么来了\N{\rE}What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.81,1:28:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我得给你看一样东西\N{\rE}I need to show you something.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.81,1:28:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,这本来是个应急计划\N{\rE}It was supposed to be a contingency plan.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.27,1:28:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他是这样说服我的 就是个保险措施\N{\rE}That's how he sold it. It was an insurance policy.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.77,1:28:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,以防我们失败\N{\rE}In case we failed.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.57,1:28:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,知道了也好 你从来没相信过我们\N{\rE}It's good to know... that you never believed in us.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.41,1:28:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你很难过\N{\rE}I know you're upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.49,1:28:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我理解 - 你理解什么\N{\rE}- I understand-- - Oh, what do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.24,1:28:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,请告诉我你理解什么\N{\rE}Please tell me what you understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.24,1:28:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你对真相一点都不理解\N{\rE}'Cause you don't understand shit about truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.12,1:28:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你伪造这次任务...\N{\rE}If you fake this mission-- If you fake this mission,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.17,1:28:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,那我们之前做出的每一次牺牲全都白费了\N{\rE}every single thing that we have sacrificed will have been for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.67,1:29:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道我搞砸了 我知道\N{\rE}I know I messed up. I know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.05,1:29:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,但你心里清楚 如果没有我 你们根本走不到今天\N{\rE}But you know you couldn't have made it to this day without me.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.34,1:29:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我昨晚大可一走了之 但我没有\N{\rE}I could've walked away last night, but I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.84,1:29:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我回来是为了弥补这个错误\N{\rE}I came back to fix this.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.68,1:29:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,弥补什么\N{\rE}Fix what?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.89,1:29:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,莫切断了登月舱的画面 如果我们不一起修好它\N{\rE}Moe cut the LEM camera, and if we don't fix this together,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.44,1:29:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,那全世界看到的将会是这个版本\N{\rE}then this is gonna be the version that the world sees.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.32,1:29:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是应急计划\N{\rE}It's not a contingency.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.45,1:29:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊 你总能让我别无选择\N{\rE}God, you're so good at leaving me no options.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.04,1:29:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 我们去修好它\N{\rE}Fine, let's fix it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.46,1:29:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,但等这事结束 我再也不想看到你\N{\rE}But when this is over, I never wanna see your face again.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.27,1:30:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,为理查德尼克松做事就是这种下场\N{\rE}This is what happens when you work for Richard Nixon.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.15,1:30:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我看了你的素描本 露比\N{\rE}I got your book, Ruby.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.03,1:30:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你提早拆开了\N{\rE}You opened it early.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.82,1:30:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,拆得正是时候\N{\rE}It came at just the right time.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.75,1:30:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,适合发射的大气层\N{\rE}...proper atmosphere for launch
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.00,1:30:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,是氧气和氮气的混合物\N{\rE}which is a combination of oxygen and nitrogen.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.59,1:30:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,60%的氧气和40%氮气的大气层\N{\rE}Sixty percent oxygen and 40% nitrogen atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.42,1:30:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,当然 宇航员们呼吸的是\N{\rE}Of course, the astronauts themselves are breathing pure oxygen
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.30,1:30:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,太空服提供的纯氧\N{\rE}through their space suits.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.64,1:30:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,很快将进行另一次关键测试\N{\rE}Coming up shortly will be another key test
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.85,1:30:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,届时发射组...\N{\rE}in which both the, uh, launch crew for the--
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.56,1:30:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,发射载具组员和飞船乘组\N{\rE}the launch vehicle crew and the spacecraft team,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.19,1:30:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,会和指挥官尼尔阿姆斯特朗一起\N{\rE}uh, combine together with the commander, Neil Armstrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.02,1:30:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,彻查紧急情况检测系统\N{\rE}to make a thorough check of the Emergency Detection System.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.86,1:30:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是该系统...\N{\rE}This is the system...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.99,1:30:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我们正在卡纳维拉尔角直播 这创造历史的一天天气晴好\N{\rE}We're live from the Cape, where it's a beautiful day to make history.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.82,1:30:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我们将在这里为大家直播发射的部分\N{\rE}We'll be handling the launch portion of the broadcast from here,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.33,1:30:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在休斯敦的同行\N{\rE}and our counterparts in Houston
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.95,1:30:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,将报道任务控制中心引导的\N{\rE}will be covering Apollo 11's historic flight,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.25,1:31:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波罗11号历史性的航程\N{\rE}guided by Mission Control.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.05,1:31:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,各位\N{\rE}Guys!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.80,1:31:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,坏了\N{\rE}It's busted.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.43,1:31:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,摄像机的视频前置放大器\N{\rE}The camera's video preamplifier.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.84,1:31:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- 坏掉了 - 好吧 你能修好吗\N{\rE}- It's destroyed. - Okay, can you fix that?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.39,1:31:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我也许能从电视上拆一个改装 但...\N{\rE}I could maybe repurpose a part from a TV, but--
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.22,1:31:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,好啊 这里有很多电视\N{\rE}Well, that's fine. There's plenty of TVs around here.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.14,1:31:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,航天局的电视都太老旧了\N{\rE}NASA's TVs-- They are all too old.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.73,1:31:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我要一台全新的晶体管彩色电视\N{\rE}I mean a brand-new solid-state color TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.44,1:31:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你多快能弄到一台\N{\rE}Well, how fast can you get one?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.56,1:31:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你送我去电器商店最快要多久\N{\rE}How fast can you get me to an electronics store?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.19,1:31:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我  - 现在佛罗里达交通空前拥堵\N{\rE}- Me? - In the worst traffic in Florida history.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.19,1:31:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,走不开 得给大家做准备\N{\rE}I can't. I have to prep the guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.44,1:31:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,把钥匙给我\N{\rE}Give me the keys.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.28,1:31:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 我来拖延\N{\rE}Fine, I'll stall.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.45,1:31:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,快点 去吧...\N{\rE}Hurry. Go, go, go, go, go, go, go.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.12,1:31:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,所有酒店全部爆满\N{\rE}Hotels are at capacity.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.66,1:31:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,肯尼迪航天中心人满为患\N{\rE}Kennedy Space Center is so crowded,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.71,1:31:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我们听说进出几乎不可能\N{\rE}we're hearing it's nearly impossible to get in or out.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.30,1:31:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉 开慢点\N{\rE}Kelly, slow down.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.30,1:31:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,后面两位还好吗\N{\rE}Are you guys good back there?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.59,1:31:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- 很好 - 不好\N{\rE}- Yes. - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.18,1:31:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,请别这样...\N{\rE}Please, please stop. Please stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.10,1:32:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,到了 就是这家店\N{\rE}There it is. There's the store.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.45,1:32:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不 - 关门了\N{\rE}- No! - They're closed.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.71,1:32:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- 关门了 - 什么\N{\rE}- They're closed. - Oh, what?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.17,1:32:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,不...没关门\N{\rE}No, no. No, they are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.54,1:32:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉\N{\rE}Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.71,1:32:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你们还等什么呢 快去\N{\rE}What are you waiting for? Go!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.05,1:32:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是... - 好\N{\rE}- Oh. Yeah, yeah. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.59,1:32:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,好\N{\rE}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.68,1:32:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,好\N{\rE}Okay, um--
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.76,1:32:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- 对 这一台 很好 - 对 好\N{\rE}- Yes, this one. This is great. Yeah, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.35,1:32:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我很想帮忙 只是我不够高 - 来吧 唐 好\N{\rE}- I would help. I'm just not tall enough. - Come on, Don. All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.81,1:32:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好 慢点 好的 - 各位 快点\N{\rE}All right. Slowly, all right. Guys, come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.90,1:32:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊 我可不能蹲监狱\N{\rE}Oh, my God. I can't go to jail.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.57,1:32:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,(警察)
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.65,1:32:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,交给我\N{\rE}Let me handle this.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.25,1:33:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,她真厉害\N{\rE}She's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.08,1:33:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊\N{\rE}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.21,1:33:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,一路顺风 兄弟们\N{\rE}Have a good ride, boys.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.72,1:34:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,大约五分钟后\N{\rE}In a matter of, uh, five minutes or so,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.05,1:34:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我们将看到飞船指挥官尼尔阿姆斯特朗\N{\rE}we'll be ready for the spacecraft commander, Neil Armstrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.93,1:34:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,跨过位于98米高空的舷门门槛\N{\rE}to come across the sill at the 320-foot level.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.99,1:34:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- 搭乘穿梭面包车... - 快啊\N{\rE}- The trip in the transfer van... - Come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.87,1:34:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,大约要15分钟才能抵达发射平台\N{\rE}...could take some 15 minutes or so to reach the pad.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.83,1:34:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,届时 宇航员将搭乘 两部电梯中先来的那部\N{\rE}At which time the astronauts will board, uh, the first of two elevators
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.96,1:34:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,前往发射平台所在的98米高空\N{\rE}for the trip to the 320-foot level at the launchpad,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.88,1:34:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,然后进入飞船\N{\rE}uh, where they will then proceed to ingress the spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.01,1:34:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,站住 已经准备就绪了 小伙子\N{\rE}Whoa. We are locked and loaded, kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.47,1:34:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,不...飞行部要把这个放进飞船\N{\rE}No, no. Flight Deck wants this on the ship.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.94,1:34:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这里飞行部 放他过去 - 好\N{\rE}- This is Flight Deck. Let him through. - Got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.94,1:34:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,去吧\N{\rE}Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.98,1:34:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,好 我们必须启动发射前的程序了 否则会错过窗口期\N{\rE}Okay, we need to initiate prelaunch, or we lose the window.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.49,1:35:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,给他一分钟就好\N{\rE}Just give him one minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.53,1:35:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,...98米的高空\N{\rE}...320-foot level,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.11,1:35:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,三位宇航员都已登上飞船\N{\rE}all three astronauts now aboard the spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.95,1:35:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,几分钟前 宇航员巴兹奥尔德林 进来坐在了中间的位置\N{\rE}A few minutes ago, Astronaut Buzz Aldrin, uh, came in and took the center seat...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.37,1:35:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我听说船舱已经封闭 倒计时开始了\N{\rE}I'm hearing the cabin's now being sealed. Countdown has begun.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.96,1:35:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,这是他们发射时的姿态\N{\rE}These are the positions they will fly at liftoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.71,1:35:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,指挥官 这里是飞船测试员 听得清楚吗\N{\rE}CDR, STC, how do you read?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.71,1:35:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,飞船测试员 听得很清楚\N{\rE}STC, loud and clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.59,1:35:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- 早上好 尼尔 - 发射架已撤开\N{\rE}Good morning, Neil. Gantry is cleared.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.84,1:35:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,欢迎登船\N{\rE}Welcome aboard.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.01,1:35:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波罗11号准备发射 倒计时十分钟\N{\rE}Apollo 11 is a go for launch in T-minus ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.10,1:35:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,好\N{\rE}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.31,1:35:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,他回来了\N{\rE}He's here.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.40,1:35:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,接上了\N{\rE}It's connected.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.48,1:35:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,至少我认为接上了\N{\rE}At least I think I connected it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.32,1:35:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,斯图 什么意思\N{\rE}- Stu, what the hell does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.36,1:35:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我只有几秒钟时间 没来得及进行压力测试 我...\N{\rE}I only had a few seconds. I didn't have time to stress test it. I--
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.75,1:35:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,好 坐下吧\N{\rE}Okay. Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.17,1:35:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,好 都听着\N{\rE}All right, listen up!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.47,1:36:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,无论今天这里发生什么\N{\rE}Whatever happens here today,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.93,1:36:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我都会支持你们做出的每一个决定\N{\rE}I will stand by every decision that you make.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.14,1:36:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,近十年来 超过四十万人参与了这项计划\N{\rE}Over 400,000 people have worked on this program for nearly ten years.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.52,1:36:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,就为了实现一个人对全世界的承诺\N{\rE}All to keep one man's promise to the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.23,1:36:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们坚守这个承诺吧\N{\rE}So, let's keep it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.57,1:36:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 告诉我发射是否就绪吧\N{\rE}All right. Give me "Go/No go" for launch.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.90,1:36:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,收到 所有岗位 准备进行最后的就绪核查\N{\rE}Ah, roger. All stations, stand by
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.66,1:36:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- 机械姿态电控 - 就绪\N{\rE}for final "Go/No go."
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.74,1:36:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- 环境控制系统 - 就绪\N{\rE}MACE. Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.12,1:36:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- 电力系统 - 就绪\N{\rE}- ECS. - Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.66,1:36:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- 序列控制器 - 就绪\N{\rE}- Sequencer. - Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.91,1:36:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- 导航系统 - 就绪\N{\rE}- GNS. - Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.16,1:36:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- 航天器控制系统 - 这里最精彩了\N{\rE}SCS. - This is the best part.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.79,1:36:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,他们依次问下去 每一个...\N{\rE}They go down the line and every single--
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.54,1:36:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,每一个技术员都必须说 发射“就绪”或“未就绪”\N{\rE}every single technician has to say, "Go," or, "No go," for launch.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.67,1:36:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,任何一人都能阻止发射\N{\rE}Any one of them can stop it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.34,1:36:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,CFAT CSE 现在能回答“就绪”了吗\N{\rE}CFAT. CSE, can you give me a "go" now?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.55,1:36:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,CSE就绪\N{\rE}CSE is go.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.63,1:36:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,好 鹰号就绪\N{\rE}Okay. Uh, Eagle is go.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.28,1:37:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,CBTS 这里是CSA9号\N{\rE}CBTS, this is CSA 9.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.28,1:37:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,倒计时20秒\N{\rE}Twenty seconds and counting.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.70,1:37:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,倒计时15秒 制导系统已切换为自主模式\N{\rE}T-minus 15 seconds. Guidance is internal.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.20,1:37:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,12 11 10 9...\N{\rE}...Twelve, eleven, ten, nine...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.96,1:37:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,点火程序启动\N{\rE}Ignition sequence starts.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.85,1:37:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,5 4 3 2 1\N{\rE}Five, four, three, two, one.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.60,1:37:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,所有引擎启动\N{\rE}All engines running.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.76,1:38:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,发射 火箭升空\N{\rE}Liftoff. We have liftoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.81,1:38:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,发射塔已分离\N{\rE}Tower clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.85,1:38:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,休斯敦 交给你了\N{\rE}Houston, she's all yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.14,1:39:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,莫伯克斯来了 要找你们俩\N{\rE}Moe Berkus is here. For both of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.10,1:39:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波罗11号已经升空\N{\rE}Apollo 11 is on the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.98,1:39:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,四十万公里之外\N{\rE}250,000 miles away,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.06,1:39:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,月球在等待人类的首次到来\N{\rE}where the moon is waiting for man's first arrival.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.36,1:39:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,整个航程要用三天时间\N{\rE}Flight to take, uh, three days.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.57,1:39:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,飞船要抵达...\N{\rE}And, uh, the, uh, spacecraft to reach there...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.03,1:39:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉全都告诉我了\N{\rE}Kelly told me everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.37,1:39:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,好极了\N{\rE}Bravissimo.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.87,1:40:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- 省省吧 - 这是创造历史\N{\rE}- Shove it. - That was history.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.62,1:40:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨 海伦 抱歉 是凯莉\N{\rE}Hi, Helen. Uh, sorry, Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.87,1:40:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我听说你回来了 所以我也回来了\N{\rE}I heard you came back, so I came back too.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.17,1:40:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我...去月球片场看了一眼\N{\rE}I-- I took a little peeky-poo at the moon set,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.22,1:40:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,真是完美\N{\rE}and it is perfection.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.51,1:40:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,干得好\N{\rE}Great job.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.51,1:40:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你认为我会让你播出 这次任务的造假版本\N{\rE}If you think that I'm gonna let you broadcast some fake version of this,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.72,1:40:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,那我现在就去找媒体\N{\rE}I'll go to the press right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.10,1:40:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,科尔\N{\rE}Cole.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.94,1:40:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,科尔...\N{\rE}Cole. Cole.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.69,1:40:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你...去找媒体吧 带他们看看月球片场\N{\rE}You, uh-- You go to the press. Bring 'em by the moon set,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.07,1:40:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,但你要知道 今后再也不会有人相信国家航空航天局了\N{\rE}but just know that no one will ever trust the legitimacy of NASA again.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.04,1:40:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,这是国家安全问题\N{\rE}This is a matter of national security.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.04,1:40:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,本次直播必须在可控的情况下进行\N{\rE}This broadcast must take place in a controlled setting.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.29,1:40:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你应该最明白了\N{\rE}You of all people must understand that.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.71,1:40:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,任务的重点已经不再是登月了\N{\rE}The mission isn't about landing on the moon anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.47,1:40:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,而是全世界在电视上观看美国战胜苏联\N{\rE}It is about the world watching America beat Russia on TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.35,1:41:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我得赶飞机\N{\rE}I got a flight to catch.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.15,1:41:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我会及时赶回来看登月直播的\N{\rE}I'll be back in time for the lunar broadcast.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.65,1:41:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我想在这里看\N{\rE}I thought I'd watch it here.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.99,1:41:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉 和你一起在月球片场看\N{\rE}With you, Kelly. On the moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.54,1:41:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 我们正在创造历史\N{\rE}Hey. We're making history.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.83,1:42:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,你说我的那些话全都没错\N{\rE}Everything you said about me is true.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.20,1:42:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我是个骗子 一直都是\N{\rE}I'm a con artist, and I always have been.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.37,1:42:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我的真名甚至不是凯莉\N{\rE}My real name is not even Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.34,1:42:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,那些我跟你讲的故事\N{\rE}All those stories that I told you
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.88,1:42:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,说我和我妈挨家挨户推销\N{\rE}about my mom and I selling products door-to-door,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.18,1:42:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,那是真事\N{\rE}those were true.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.47,1:42:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,但都是骗局\N{\rE}They were all scams.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.89,1:42:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我们开始只是小打小闹 之后越做越大\N{\rE}And we started out small, and then they got bigger.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.93,1:42:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,大到涉及地产和保险什么的\N{\rE}Like real estate and insurance.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.85,1:42:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,然后...\N{\rE}And...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.94,1:42:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我16岁那年 在北达科他州 有个人掏枪了\N{\rE}when I was 16, a guy in North Dakota pulled a gun
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.36,1:42:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我妈比他更快掏出枪 把他打死了\N{\rE}and my mom pulled hers out first and she killed him.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.36,1:42:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,她叫我逃跑 我照做了\N{\rE}And she told me to run and I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.03,1:42:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,她进了监狱 我再也没见过她\N{\rE}And she went to prison and I never saw her again.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.46,1:42:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我伪造文件 用假名来找工作\N{\rE}And I forged documents and used fake names to get jobs.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.88,1:42:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我去纽约后发现了广告业\N{\rE}And when I went to New York, I found advertising.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.88,1:43:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,就像我妈教我的骗局 但却合法\N{\rE}And that was like the scams that my mom taught me, but it was legal.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.89,1:43:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我骗了很多人\N{\rE}And I lied to so many people.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.85,1:43:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,最糟糕的谎言是我对自己说的那些\N{\rE}The worst lies were the ones I told myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.06,1:43:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,说所有人都在骗人 这只是一场大型游戏而已\N{\rE}That everybody does it. You know. It's just a big game.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.02,1:43:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,但后来我来了这里\N{\rE}But then I came down here...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.95,1:43:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,认识了你\N{\rE}I met you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.74,1:43:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我了解到参与到真实事件中是什么感受\N{\rE}I learned what it was like to be a part of something real.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.17,1:43:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,莫提出的条件是抹去我的黑历史\N{\rE}Moe offered me a way to erase my past.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.46,1:43:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我原以为那就是我想要的 但...\N{\rE}I thought that's what I wanted, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.88,1:43:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想再逃亡了\N{\rE}I don't wanna run anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.52,1:43:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,莫是个值得尊敬的对手 但他遇到旗鼓相当的人了\N{\rE}Moe is a worthy opponent, but he has met his match.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.32,1:44:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我保证这是我最后一次 用欺骗的手段来获取我想要的东西\N{\rE}I promise this is the last time I will trick anyone into getting what I want.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.78,1:44:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我保证\N{\rE}I promise.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.24,1:44:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得不撒谎也能做到吗\N{\rE}Do you think you can do it without lying?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.12,1:44:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- 绝对不行 - 好吧 我想也是\N{\rE}- Absolutely not. - Yeah, I didn't think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.75,1:44:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,那你有什么计划\N{\rE}So, what's the plan?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.80,1:44:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我们为什么在这里碰头\N{\rE}Why are we meeting out here?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.68,1:44:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,因为莫监听一切对话 这人就像个魔术师 无处不在\N{\rE}Because Moe bugs everything. The guy's like Houdini. He's everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.30,1:44:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,好 莫不知道我们修好了登月舱摄像机\N{\rE}Okay, so, Moe doesn't know that we fixed the LEM camera.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.22,1:44:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我们就此来制定计划\N{\rE}We build a plan around that.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.68,1:44:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我们只需让他相信我们在直播假登月\N{\rE}All we have to do is convince him that we are broadcasting the fake moon landing,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.40,1:44:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,而实际上我们在播真的\N{\rE}when in reality, we're broadcasting the real one.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:38.19,1:44:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我们有没有办法给设备动手脚\N{\rE}Is there a way that we could rig the equipment
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.23,1:44:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,来播出真实的登月舱视频\N{\rE}so that it actually sends out the real LEM video feed?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.74,1:44:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托 两位\N{\rE}Come on, boys.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.74,1:44:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你们连登月都搞定了 给我个假设理论啊\N{\rE}You figured out how to land on the moon. Give me a hypothetical.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.20,1:44:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,好 假设的话 我们可以重新接线\N{\rE}Okay, um, hypothetically, we could rewire it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.08,1:44:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,让设备只接收任务控制中心的播出信号\N{\rE}So that it only picks up the broadcast signal from Mission Control.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.75,1:44:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好 然后和我们的信号同步 - 对\N{\rE}- Sure, then sync it with our feed. Hmm. Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.67,1:45:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 各位\N{\rE}Hey, fellas.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.55,1:45:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,莫伯克斯派这两位来测试播出信号\N{\rE}Moe Berkus sent these guys to test the broadcast feed.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.14,1:45:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- 莫...伯克斯 对 - 莫伯克斯...\N{\rE}- Moe-- Moe Berk-- Yes. Moe Berk-- Moe Berkus.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.89,1:45:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,你们谁都没接到电话\N{\rE}Telling me none of you got the phone call?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.60,1:45:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,好极了 摄像机在哪\N{\rE}Great. All right, where's the camera?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.81,1:45:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,你还好吗\N{\rE}Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.94,1:45:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,请你们快点好吗\N{\rE}Can you guys hurry up, please?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.53,1:45:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,唐 你把烟掐了吧\N{\rE}Don, maybe just take the cigarette out.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.49,1:45:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉...我之前从没吸过烟\N{\rE}I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I've just never smoked a cigarette before.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.62,1:45:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我不喜欢\N{\rE}I don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.95,1:45:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,11号 这里是休斯敦\N{\rE}...uh, 11, this is Houston.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.79,1:45:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,环月轨道进入就绪 完毕\N{\rE}Uh, you are go for LOI. Over.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.00,1:45:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,确认 向月球前进\N{\rE}Confirmed. On track for the moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.75,1:45:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波罗11号 这里是休斯敦\N{\rE}Apollo 11, this is Houston.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.63,1:45:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你的全部系统正常 要转到月球后面了\N{\rE}All your systems are looking good. Going around the corner.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.09,1:45:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我们另一边见 完毕\N{\rE}We'll see you on the other side. Over.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.63,1:45:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我们失去了信号\N{\rE}And we've had loss of signal
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.55,1:45:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,因为阿波罗11号飞到了月球后面\N{\rE}as Apollo 11 goes behind the moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.68,1:45:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,现在是东部夏令时下午3点半\N{\rE}It's now 3:30 Eastern Daylight Time.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:52.01,1:45:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,3点46分时 我们应该能够收到 登月舱的第一个信号\N{\rE}At 3:46 we should be getting the first signal from the Lunar Module.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.19,1:45:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,估计观众有上亿人\N{\rE}The estimated audience: hundreds of millions.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.81,1:46:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,可能有四亿人\N{\rE}Perhaps 400 million persons or so are watching
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.48,1:46:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,正在观看这一重大事件的直播...\N{\rE}this broadcast today of, uh, the greatest event...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.32,1:46:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,兄弟们\N{\rE}Boys.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.86,1:46:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,好 开始吧\N{\rE}All right. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.29,1:46:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,再往下一点 很好 各位\N{\rE}A little bit more. Well done, guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.25,1:46:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,伙计们 你们听到我说话 就当成是上帝的旨意\N{\rE}Boys, when you hear my voice, you hear God.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:28.30,1:46:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,这是个假月球\N{\rE}Now, this is a fake moon,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.72,1:46:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- 但对于全世界 这是真的 - 好戏上演了\N{\rE}- but to the world, it's real. - It's showtime, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.60,1:46:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,必须...记住我说到哪了\N{\rE}It needs to-- Remember where I left off.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:33.14,1:46:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,政府感谢你们即将付出的努力\N{\rE}Your government thanks you for the work you're about to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.56,1:46:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,别搞砸了\N{\rE}Now, don't fuck it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.27,1:46:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,这破烂饮料为什么放这里\N{\rE}What is this nasty shit doing here?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:43.90,1:46:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- 天啊 - 不好意思\N{\rE}- God. - Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:45.90,1:46:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这是本片场指定的汽水 这是我的椅子\N{\rE}This is a Tab set, and that is my chair.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.40,1:46:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- 凯莉 处理一下 - 兰斯 非常感谢\N{\rE}- Kelly, let's deal with this. - Lance, thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.78,1:46:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,这些屏幕是我们的信号\N{\rE}So, these screens-- This is our feed.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.83,1:46:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,好 然后...\N{\rE}Yeah. Okay. And then--
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.29,1:46:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,电视是直播画面 好\N{\rE}And the TV's a live broadcast. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.96,1:46:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,(阿波罗11号 月球直播)
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.92,1:47:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,对\N{\rE}Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.42,1:47:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,约瑟夫 我要坐下\N{\rE}Joseph, I'm sitting.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.84,1:47:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊 你认真的\N{\rE}Oh, my God. Are you real?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.55,1:47:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我是导演 兰斯瓦斯珀丁\N{\rE}I am the director, Lance Vespertine.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.42,1:47:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,别碍事好吗\N{\rE}Stay out of my way, will you?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.93,1:47:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,好 我想说很高兴认识你 但到目前为止我不高兴\N{\rE}All right, I'd say it was nice to meet you, but so far, it is not.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.64,1:47:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,鸽子已经进笼\N{\rE}The pigeon's in the coop.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.39,1:47:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,收到\N{\rE}Copy that.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.89,1:47:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,好 应该能收到了 休斯敦\N{\rE}Okay, you should have him now, Houston.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.35,1:47:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,鹰号 我们有你的信号了 看起来不错 完毕\N{\rE}Eagle, we've got you now. It's looking good. Over.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.82,1:47:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我们从前窗就可以看到地球\N{\rE}We've got the Earth right out of our front window.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:30.86,1:47:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,飞行指挥 我们准备着陆\N{\rE}Flight, we are go for landing.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.28,1:47:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,收到 明白 准备着陆 910米\N{\rE}Roger. Understand. Go for landing. 3,000 feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.12,1:47:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,鹰号 状态很好 可以开始着陆\N{\rE}Eagle, looking great. You're go.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.72,1:47:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,位置检查显示 水平飞行距离有些过长\N{\rE}Position checks downrange show us to be a little long.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.47,1:47:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,430米 状态依然很好\N{\rE}1,400 feet. Still looking very good.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.81,1:47:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,P30\N{\rE}P30.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.89,1:48:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,6加2.5\N{\rE}Six plus two-five.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.73,1:48:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,看起来大约250米\N{\rE}Looks like about 820.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.31,1:48:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,降低引擎的功率\N{\rE}Throttle down.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.36,1:48:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,飞行指挥 这里是鹰号\N{\rE}Flight, this is Eagle.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.61,1:48:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,宁静海里的石头比预期中多\N{\rE}Sea of Tranquility is rockier than expected.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.24,1:48:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不得不再飞300米\N{\rE}We're gonna have to extend another thousand feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.32,1:48:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 兄弟们\N{\rE}Hey, boys.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.99,1:48:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,那样的话情况如何\N{\rE}Where does that put us?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.12,1:48:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他们会剩下15秒的燃料 - 最好终止任务\N{\rE}- It'll give 'em 15 seconds of fuel left. - They're gonna wanna abort.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.29,1:48:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,尼尔能做到 只要放手让他飞即可\N{\rE}Neil can do this, they just gotta let him.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.62,1:48:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,(燃料百分比)
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.54,1:48:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,待命 鹰号\N{\rE}Stand by, Eagle.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:25.92,1:48:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我们正在计算延长飞行的耗油量\N{\rE}We are calculating what that will do to our fuel reserves.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.50,1:48:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,电气 环境和耗材主管计算 是15秒以内 准备终止任务\N{\rE}EECOM puts that within 15 seconds. Prepare for abort.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.05,1:48:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,飞行指挥\N{\rE}Flight...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.39,1:48:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我们曾在这个范围内 进行过成功测试 让他们着陆吧\N{\rE}...we have run successful tests within that range. Let 'em land.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:41.48,1:48:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,30秒...\N{\rE}Thirty. Thirty seconds.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.02,1:48:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这是骗人 - 你撒谎了\N{\rE}- That's a lie. - You lied.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:45.27,1:48:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我新学了几招 坐下\N{\rE}I've learned some new tricks. Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.94,1:48:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,好 接下来只报告燃料数字\N{\rE}Okay, the only callouts from now on will be fuel.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.15,1:48:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,加油啊\N{\rE}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:53.07,1:48:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,鹰号 看起来不错 可以着陆\N{\rE}Eagle, looking great. You're go.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.49,1:48:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,430米 状态依然很好\N{\rE}1,400 feet. Still looking very good.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.04,1:49:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,107米 降速4\N{\rE}350 feet, down at four.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.70,1:49:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,30秒...\N{\rE}Thirty. Thirty seconds.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.58,1:49:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,降速2.5 前进\N{\rE}Down two and a half. Forward.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.75,1:49:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- 前进 好 - 收到\N{\rE}- Forward. Good. Roger that.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.59,1:49:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,前进速度11 正稳步下降\N{\rE}Eleven forward. Coming down nicely.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:12.34,1:49:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,61米 降速4.5\N{\rE}200 feet, four and a half down.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:14.09,1:49:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,降速5.5...前进速度9\N{\rE}Five and a half down. Five and a half down, nine forward.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:16.80,1:49:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rE}That's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.32,1:49:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,(月表接触)
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.44,1:49:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,接触灯亮了\N{\rE}Contact light.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.70,1:49:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,关闭引擎\N{\rE}Engine stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.38,1:49:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,飞行指挥\N{\rE}Flight.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:53.21,1:49:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是宁静海基地\N{\rE}Tranquility Base here.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.38,1:49:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,鹰号已着陆\N{\rE}The Eagle has landed.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.60,1:50:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,收到 宁静海基地 地面收到\N{\rE}Roger, Tranquility, we copy on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:06.35,1:50:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,有一群人脸都快憋青了\N{\rE}You got a bunch of guys about to turn blue.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:08.52,1:50:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我们又能呼吸了 多谢\N{\rE}We're breathing again. Thanks a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:16.86,1:50:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,呼 老天\N{\rE}Whew. Boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.95,1:50:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要忙一会儿了\N{\rE}We're going to be busy for a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.58,1:50:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,好了...可以了\N{\rE}All right, all right, all right. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.25,1:50:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,集中注意力 还没完呢\N{\rE}Let's focus. We're only halfway there.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.21,1:50:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,好 接下来交给我们 谢谢各位\N{\rE}Yeah, we've got it from here. Thank you, guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:32.13,1:50:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,大家各就各位...打起精神\N{\rE}Places. Places, everyone. Look sharp.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.21,1:50:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,打起精神来\N{\rE}Let's look sharp!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:36.47,1:50:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,爱德华...走下舞台 真要命\N{\rE}Edvard, Edvard, off the stage. You're killing me.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:38.76,1:50:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,爱德华 完事了 停 你完工了 别再调整了\N{\rE}Edvard, we are done. Uh-uh. You're done. No more tweaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.68,1:50:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你是复读机吗  - 我不是复读机\N{\rE}- What are you, the repeater? - No, I'm not the repeater.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.02,1:50:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,这是你来之前我们创立的系统\N{\rE}This is the system we created before you got here.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.32,1:50:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,已取下摄像机\N{\rE}Camera is coming down.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:01.62,1:51:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,(直播中)
Dialogue: 0,1:51:02.62,1:51:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,三 二 一 开拍\N{\rE}Three, two, one, and action.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:10.12,1:51:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,电视上有画面了\N{\rE}And we're getting a picture on the TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:13.63,1:51:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,画面还不错吧\N{\rE}You got a good picture, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.46,1:51:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,对比度很强烈\N{\rE}Uh, there's a great deal of contrast in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:18.34,1:51:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,收到 电视电路断路器已接通\N{\rE}Roger, TV circuit breaker's in,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.72,1:51:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,听得很清楚\N{\rE}and read you loud and clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:24.89,1:51:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,收到\N{\rE}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.35,1:51:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,好 请确认一下\N{\rE}Okay. Will you verify the position, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:34.11,1:51:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,摄像机镜头的位置和光圈尺寸\N{\rE}the, uh, opening I ought to have on the camera?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:36.07,1:51:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,稍等\N{\rE}Stand by.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:37.36,1:51:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,阿姆斯特朗 准备下飞船\N{\rE}Armstrong, prepare to disembark.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:41.57,1:51:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,遮光面罩\N{\rE}Your visor.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.74,1:51:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我要打开舱门出去了\N{\rE}I am opening the door for egress.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.85,1:52:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,好 尼尔 我们看到你正走下舷梯\N{\rE}Okay, Neil, we can see you coming down the ladder now.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:13.52,1:52:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,好 左脚\N{\rE}Okay, left.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:17.15,1:52:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,右脚\N{\rE}And right.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:21.28,1:52:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,左脚 右脚\N{\rE}Left and right.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:23.91,1:52:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,好 左脚下来...\N{\rE}Now, left foot off. Left foot off.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:26.58,1:52:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,慢点...下来\N{\rE}Easy. Easy. Step down.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.70,1:52:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,落地\N{\rE}And land.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.37,1:52:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么提前知道他要做什么\N{\rE}How do you know what, uh, he's gonna do ahead of time?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:35.83,1:52:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,国家航空航天局全都排练过 凯莉借鉴了一下\N{\rE}NASA rehearsed all of this, and Kelly appropriated it.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:40.76,1:52:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,就是偷嘛\N{\rE}Oh, stole it.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:42.42,1:52:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我就知道我找对人了\N{\rE}I knew I hired the right people.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:45.43,1:52:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,好 来吧\N{\rE}Okay, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:48.51,1:52:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,(真实信号 播出信号)
Dialogue: 0,1:52:50.22,1:52:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,天衣无缝 真难以置信\N{\rE}It's seamless. It's incredible.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.52,1:52:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我来到舷梯底部了\N{\rE}I'm at the foot of the ladder.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.10,1:53:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,登月舱的支脚仅仅压进月球表面2到5厘米\N{\rE}The LEM footpads are only depressed in the surface about one or two inches,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.48,1:53:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,不过靠近了看 月表的尘土似乎非常细腻\N{\rE}although the surface appears to be very, very fine-grained as you get close to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.11,1:53:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,几乎就像粉末 下面的尘埃非常细\N{\rE}It's almost like a powder. Down there, it's very fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.00,1:53:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我要走下登月舱了\N{\rE}I'm gonna step off the LEM now.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:19.71,1:53:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,这是个人的一小步\N{\rE}That's one small step for man...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.80,1:53:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,却是人类的一大步\N{\rE}one giant leap for mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:34.64,1:53:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,这么精彩的话 我们可能得花好几年才想得出\N{\rE}We could have spent years coming up with something that good.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.19,1:53:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rE}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:41.15,1:53:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,这是剧本里的吗\N{\rE}- Was that, uh, in the script?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:43.57,1:53:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,不是\N{\rE}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.86,1:53:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,这句台词不错\N{\rE}That's a good line.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:52.04,1:53:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,一级一级舷梯跳下来是很简单的\N{\rE}It's a very simple matter to hop down from one step to the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:55.91,1:53:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,尼尔要展示牌匾了\N{\rE}Neil is now unveiling the plaque.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.88,1:54:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“地球的人类\N{\rE}"Here man, from the planet Earth,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:00.84,1:54:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,于公元1969年7月首次踏上月球\N{\rE}first set foot upon the moon, July 1969 AD.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:05.97,1:54:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我们为全人类的和平而来”\N{\rE}We came in peace for all mankind."
Dialogue: 0,1:54:11.56,1:54:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,准备好上镜了吗\N{\rE}You ready for the camera?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:13.39,1:54:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,尼尔 这里是休斯敦 视野正常\N{\rE}Uh, Neil, this is Houston. The field of view is okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:16.81,1:54:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我们希望你把摄像机对准右边一点 完毕\N{\rE}We'd like you to aim it a little bit more to the right. Over.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:20.02,1:54:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,好\N{\rE}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.07,1:54:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,太往右了\N{\rE}Too much to the right.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:23.61,1:54:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,能往左4 5度吗\N{\rE}Can you bring it back left about, uh, four or five degrees?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.12,1:54:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,好 看起来不错 尼尔\N{\rE}Okay. That looks good, Neil.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:34.41,1:54:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,哥伦比亚号...这里是休斯敦 接收信号 完毕\N{\rE}Columbia, Columbia, this is Houston, AOS. Over.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:36.91,1:54:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,尼尔阿姆斯特朗目前已经在月球表面\N{\rE}Neil Armstrong has been on the lunar surface now
Dialogue: 0,1:54:39.42,1:54:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,停留近45分钟了\N{\rE}almost 45 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.08,1:54:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,宁静海基地 这里是休斯敦\N{\rE}Uh, Tranquility Base, this is Houston.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:43.50,1:54:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,请两位一起走进镜头一下好吗\N{\rE}Could we get both of you on the camera for a minute, please?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:46.72,1:54:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,美国总统想跟你们说几句 完毕\N{\rE}The President of the United States would like to say a few words to you. Over.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:50.76,1:54:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我们的荣幸\N{\rE}That would be an honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:53.18,1:54:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,好 总统先生 请讲吧\N{\rE}All right, go ahead, Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.18,1:54:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是休斯敦 完毕\N{\rE}This is Houston. Out.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:56.27,1:54:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,你们好 尼尔和巴兹\N{\rE}Hello, Neil and Buzz.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:58.77,1:55:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我正在白宫的椭圆办公室 用电话跟你们通话\N{\rE}I am talking to you by telephone from the Oval Room at the White House...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.07,1:55:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,这地方到处都是特勤局的人\N{\rE}They have Secret Service all over this place.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:05.23,1:55:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,这绝对是有史以来最重要的一次通话\N{\rE}...and this certainly has to be the most historic telephone call ever made.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:10.82,1:55:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你们跟我们通话的同时...\N{\rE}And as you talk to us...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:12.45,1:55:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得你跟他真的很像\N{\rE}He actually reminds me a lot of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:14.95,1:55:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,别这么说 真的 连玩笑都别开\N{\rE}Do not say that. No, don't even joke about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:18.21,1:55:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,总统发表无聊讲话时我们要待命 别动\N{\rE}We're still holding while the president drones on. Don't move.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:22.63,1:55:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,阿姆斯特朗 我主要盯着你\N{\rE}Armstrong, I'm watching you the most.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:24.34,1:55:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,在这全人类史上无比珍贵的时刻...\N{\rE}For one priceless moment in the whole history of man...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.67,1:55:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,肯尼迪航天中心 我们直接通话吧\N{\rE}Kennedy, let's go direct.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:32.72,1:55:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,科尔 你收到画面了吗\N{\rE}Cole, are you receiving picture?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:34.89,1:55:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,这边的视频信号灯没亮\N{\rE}The video feed light isn't on up here.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:36.68,1:55:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,尼尔 什么意思 坏掉了\N{\rE}Uh, what do you mean, Neil? It's not working?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:39.85,1:55:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,那得你来告诉我 你能看到画面吗\N{\rE}You tell me. Do you see picture?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.40,1:55:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的摄像机发出了电力过载警报\N{\rE}We're getting a power surge warning on the camera.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:44.82,1:55:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,好像坏了 你还能看到我们吗\N{\rE}I think it crapped out. Can you still see us?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:47.28,1:55:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,能 还能看见\N{\rE}Yeah, I can still see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:51.11,1:55:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,稍等 尼尔\N{\rE}Um, one second, Neil.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:52.78,1:55:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,尼尔说月球上的视频信号灯没有亮\N{\rE}Neil's saying the video feed light isn't on up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:54.66,1:55:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你确定那台摄像机能用\N{\rE}Are you sure that camera's working?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:55.99,1:55:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我安装了新零件 应该没问题的 但...\N{\rE}I installed the new part. It should be working just fine but--
Dialogue: 0,1:55:58.20,1:56:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- 但什么  - 但我...当时赶时间\N{\rE}- But what? - But I-- I was in a rush.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:02.12,1:56:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,见鬼\N{\rE}Shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:07.00,1:56:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\rE}What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:08.01,1:56:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不确定登月舱上的 摄像机是否运作正常\N{\rE}We're not sure that the camera on the LEM is working.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:11.38,1:56:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得播出的画面是你们的\N{\rE}I think that's your feed broadcasting.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:14.72,1:56:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,电视上的画面和片场一样吗\N{\rE}Does the feed on your TV look like your set?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:20.43,1:56:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我...看不出是不是我们\N{\rE}I-- I can't tell if it's us.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:22.31,1:56:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,测试一下 让一个特工挥挥手什么的\N{\rE}Test it. Have one of your agents give a little wave or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:26.36,1:56:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,不行 所有人都在这里\N{\rE}I can't. Everyone is here.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:46.13,1:56:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这是什么鬼  - 我不知道\N{\rE}- What the hell is that? - I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:49.88,1:56:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,他差5厘米就进镜头了\N{\rE}He is two inches away from being on that screen.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:51.51,1:56:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,是...2厘米\N{\rE}It's-- It's one inch.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:52.59,1:56:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,这也是你那该死的剧本里的情节\N{\rE}Is that in your goddamn script?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:56.68,1:56:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,约瑟夫 有新加的戏\N{\rE}Joseph, were there new pages?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:58.18,1:57:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,不仅代表美国\N{\rE}...representing not only the United States
Dialogue: 0,1:57:00.93,1:57:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,也代表所有国家热爱和平的人\N{\rE}but men of peace of all nations...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:07.52,1:57:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,是小淘气 天啊 猫咪...\N{\rE}Oh, Mischief! Oh, God. Kitty, kitty! Pss, kitty, kitty, kitty.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:10.15,1:57:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,小淘气...\N{\rE}Mischief! Mischief!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:11.36,1:57:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你去哪\N{\rE}Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:13.78,1:57:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- 小淘气... - 凯莉\N{\rE}Mischief. Mischief. - K-- Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:15.36,1:57:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- 过来 - 那只猫\N{\rE}Come here. - The cat?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:16.91,1:57:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,过来...\N{\rE}Come here. Come here. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:26.83,1:57:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你认识这只猫\N{\rE}Do you know this cat?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:30.50,1:57:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,猫咪...\N{\rE}Kitty, kitty, kitty!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:31.55,1:57:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,过来 小宝...过来 你个小混蛋\N{\rE}Come here, you sweet-- Come here, you little bitch.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:34.38,1:57:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,猫咪...\N{\rE}Kitty, kitty, kitty.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:35.93,1:57:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- 给我过来 - 不\N{\rE}- Come here, you! No!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:39.76,1:57:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉 你那边到底怎么了\N{\rE}Kelly, what the hell is going on over there?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:42.68,1:57:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉\N{\rE}Kelly? Kelly?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:44.94,1:57:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,绕到后面去\N{\rE}Go round the back!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:46.52,1:57:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,小淘气...\N{\rE}Mischief! Mischief!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:49.57,1:57:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,猫咪...\N{\rE}Kitty, kitty, kitty!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:50.61,1:57:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,抓住它...快...\N{\rE}Catch him! Catch him! Oh! Go, go.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.78,1:57:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我们走 快\N{\rE}Let's go! Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:56.61,1:57:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,来 没事的\N{\rE}Come here. It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:58.49,1:58:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,小淘气 过来吧\N{\rE}Mischief. Just come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:00.33,1:58:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,闭嘴...\N{\rE}Just shut up. Just shut up!
Dialogue: 0,1:58:01.74,1:58:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,过来 猫咪...过来 小宝宝 你认识我的\N{\rE}Come here, kitty, kitty, kitty. Come here, little baby. You know me.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:06.17,1:58:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rE}No!
Dialogue: 0,1:58:21.76,1:58:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,非常感谢\N{\rE}And thank you very much
Dialogue: 0,1:58:23.35,1:58:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我很期待 我们都很期待\N{\rE}and I look forward, all of us look forward,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:25.27,1:58:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,星期四在大黄蜂号上见到你们\N{\rE}to seeing you on the Hornet on Thursday.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:30.98,1:58:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我也很期待 先生\N{\rE}I look forward to that very much, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:36.24,1:58:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,播出的是你的人 科尔\N{\rE}Those are your guys, Cole.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:38.03,1:58:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,太好了 是我们的人\N{\rE}Yes! Those are our guys!
Dialogue: 0,1:58:44.20,1:58:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,对 我知道你们都知道\N{\rE}Yes. I know you know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:46.00,1:58:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,就是提醒一下大家我们今天在干什么\N{\rE}Just reminding everybody what we're doing here today.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:49.29,1:58:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,那是我们的人\N{\rE}Those are our guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:51.46,1:58:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,大家继续忙吧\N{\rE}Carry on.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:58.72,1:59:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我看到的是什么\N{\rE}What am I looking at here?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:00.39,1:59:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,月球\N{\rE}Oh, that's the moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:03.76,1:59:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,尼尔 这里是休斯敦\N{\rE}Neil, this is Houston.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:05.31,1:59:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你拿哈苏杂志...\N{\rE}Did you get the Hasselblad magazine...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:06.89,1:59:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,真的是月球\N{\rE}That's really the moon?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:08.14,1:59:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,拿了 我们有大约...\N{\rE}Yes, I did. And we got about, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:11.73,1:59:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- 老天 看起来好假 - 得有9公斤...\N{\rE}- Jesus, it looks fake. - ...I'd say 20 pounds of, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:14.44,1:59:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,精挑细选 但没有记录的样品\N{\rE}...carefully selected, if not documented samples.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:19.15,1:59:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,休斯敦 收到 好样的 完毕\N{\rE}Houston. Roger. Well done. Out.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:21.49,1:59:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,非官方时间 离开地面111小时37分32秒\N{\rE}Unofficial time off the surface at 111:37:32.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:31.54,1:59:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我从没想过自己能这么近地看到月球\N{\rE}I never thought I would see the moon up close.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:34.13,1:59:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我也一样 沃尔特\N{\rE}Me neither, Walter.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:42.26,1:59:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我没搞定 天啊 - 抱歉\N{\rE}I didn't get it. Oh, my God. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:44.35,1:59:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- 别和上次一样 - 不 别冲着我们开\N{\rE}Not like last time. No. Don't point it at us.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:47.02,1:59:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,在波兰 我们说“na zdrowie”\N{\rE}In Polish, we call it "na zdrowie."
Dialogue: 0,1:59:48.98,1:59:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好 na zdrowie - 好...凯莉\N{\rE}All right. Na zdrowie. - Okay, okay, okay. Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:51.60,1:59:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- 凯莉... - 好点了\N{\rE}- Kelly. Kelly. - It's getting a little better.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:53.23,1:59:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么事  - 老天 说吧 就说一次\N{\rE}- Yes? What? - Christ, just say it. Just say it once.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:57.11,1:59:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你是我认识的最棒的导演\N{\rE}You are the best director I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:58.57,2:00:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 好了 我知道此事要保密\N{\rE}I am. [inhales sharply] Now, I know we're not supposed to talk about this,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:01.66,2:00:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,但是凯莉 能写进我的简历就太好了 如果我...感觉...\N{\rE}but, Kelly, this would be so great on my résumé if I-- Just feels--
Dialogue: 0,2:00:04.20,2:00:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,任何人把此事透露出去\N{\rE}Anyone mentions this to anyone,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:06.66,2:00:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,就会在一个无名岛上阴暗的牢房里\N{\rE}you will spend the rest of your life in a dark, dank prison cell
Dialogue: 0,2:00:10.16,2:00:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,度过余生\N{\rE}on a nameless island.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:13.92,2:00:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 为了配合香槟酒\N{\rE}Oh. - Now, to wash down the bubbly,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:16.30,2:00:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我代表美国政府请大家喝苏格兰威士忌\N{\rE}on behalf of the US government, have a little, uh, scotch.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:20.13,2:00:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,爱德华\N{\rE}Edvard.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:21.51,2:00:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我来一杯\N{\rE}I'll take one of those.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:22.72,2:00:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我做了一档价值十亿美元的电视节目 但观众只有一个人\N{\rE}I had a billion-dollar TV show for an audience of one.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:25.76,2:00:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,希望你看得开心\N{\rE}Hope you enjoyed it.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:27.89,2:00:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- 干杯 - 这是一场完美的失败\N{\rE}- Cheers. - It was a perfect failure.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:30.56,2:00:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- 对 干杯... - 干杯\N{\rE}- That's right. Cheers. Cheers. Cheers.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:37.23,2:00:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,能聊几句吗\N{\rE}Can I talk with you a moment?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:41.03,2:00:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,没有多少人违抗了我的命令\N{\rE}Not many people have gone against my orders
Dialogue: 0,2:00:44.07,2:00:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,还能活命的\N{\rE}and lived to talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:45.49,2:00:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,不过话说回来 也没有多少人救过我\N{\rE}Then again, not many people have saved my ass.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:49.20,2:00:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,要解释月球上为什么有只猫 那可太难了\N{\rE}It would've been a real doozy to explain how the cat ended up on the moon.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:54.33,2:00:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你真是个美国英雄\N{\rE}You're a goddamn American hero.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:57.96,2:00:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,干得好\N{\rE}Great job.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:01.17,2:01:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 现在这里到处都是媒体\N{\rE}Now, this place is crawling with press.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:03.72,2:01:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,溅落之前 我们无法清理这里\N{\rE}So, uh, we can't really clear anything out until after splashdown.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:08.01,2:01:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,在这期间呢 把一切和拍摄有关的文件全部销毁\N{\rE}In the meantime, shred any documents associated with the shoot.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:13.48,2:01:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你的名字会从史册中抹去\N{\rE}Your name will be wiped from the history books.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:16.19,2:01:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,过往将被重写\N{\rE}The story, rewritten.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:20.90,2:01:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- 那我可以走了 - 是的\N{\rE}- Then I'm free to go. - You are.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:23.99,2:01:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,不过呢 有个未来的项目 我需要你这样的人帮忙\N{\rE}Although, I could use someone like you for an upcoming project.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:31.29,2:01:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,不 谢了\N{\rE}No, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:32.41,2:01:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,你随意吧 我不理解 但没问题\N{\rE}Suit yourself. Hard to get, but okay.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:36.58,2:01:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,如果需要我 喊一声就行 我可能会听见\N{\rE}If you ever need me... just holler. I'm probably listening.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:50.18,2:01:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,莫\N{\rE}Moe.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:53.56,2:01:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,真有外星人吗\N{\rE}Are there really aliens out there?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:58.19,2:01:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,外星人就生活在我们中间\N{\rE}They walk among us.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:03.74,2:02:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,带我飞向月球\N{\rE}Fly me to the moon
Dialogue: 0,2:02:07.61,2:02:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们在群星中嬉戏\N{\rE}Let's play among the stars
Dialogue: 0,2:02:12.37,2:02:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,让我看看木星和火星上春天的样子\N{\rE}Let me see what spring is like On Jupiter and Mars...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:18.00,2:02:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,四十万公里\N{\rE}A quarter of a million miles.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:19.92,2:02:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,想想尼尔阿姆斯特朗的话\N{\rE}Just think of it as, uh, Neil Armstrong said,
Dialogue: 0,2:02:22.38,2:02:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,人类踏上月球时的第一句话\N{\rE}the first words as man stepped foot on the moon,
Dialogue: 0,2:02:25.88,2:02:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“这是个人的一小步 却是人类的一大步”\N{\rE}"A small step for man, a giant leap for mankind."
Dialogue: 0,2:02:31.26,2:02:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,这一天不会再有了\N{\rE}And a day that can never come again.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:33.43,2:02:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,这一天和这一句话将永远载入史册\N{\rE}A day that shall forever live in history, as will those words,
Dialogue: 0,2:02:36.77,2:02:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,会被学生们记住\N{\rE}which will be memorized by schoolboys...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:38.81,2:02:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,阿姆斯特朗 你很有前途 不过不是演戏 天啊 绝对不是\N{\rE}Armstrong, you've got a future. Not in acting. My God, no.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:43.61,2:02:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,凯莉 帕蒂...是叫帕蒂吧\N{\rE}Well, Kelly, Patty-- Patty, right?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:45.86,2:02:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我叫露比 - 好\N{\rE}- My name is Ruby. Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:47.53,2:02:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们成功了 - 不 我们没成功\N{\rE}- We did it. No, we didn't.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:59.50,2:03:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是近陆地单位\N{\rE}This is, uh, landward here.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:00.96,2:03:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,游泳1号看到阿波罗号了\N{\rE}Uh, Swim One has Apollo visual.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:03.63,2:03:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,如果它正在14.5公里外下降\N{\rE}Well, if it's coming down nine miles away,
Dialogue: 0,2:03:06.09,2:03:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,那将会刚好落在能见度极限范围内\N{\rE}uh, that's just going to be at the, uh, outer limit of, uh, visibility...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:09.47,2:03:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,加油...宝贝...\N{\rE}Come on. Come on, baby. Come on, baby.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:27.44,2:03:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,他们从月球返回了\N{\rE}They're back from the moon.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:29.28,2:03:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,宇航员阿姆斯特朗 奥尔德林和柯林斯\N{\rE}Astronauts Armstrong, Aldrin and Collins
Dialogue: 0,2:03:31.91,2:03:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,溅落在太平洋 夏威夷的西南方\N{\rE}landing in the Pacific Ocean, southwest of Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:41.42,2:03:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我想你应该抽一支烟\N{\rE}I guess you deserve a cigarette.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:45.50,2:03:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- 朋友 - 是...我...\N{\rE}- Aw, buddy. - Yeah, yeah. I, uh...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:50.93,2:03:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想在里面失控\N{\rE}I didn't wanna lose it in there. You know?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:56.18,2:03:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你不希望带摄像机登月\N{\rE}You know, I know you didn't want the camera up there,
Dialogue: 0,2:03:58.35,2:04:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,但是 天啊 看到那画面...\N{\rE}but, man, seeing that was, uh...
Dialogue: 0,2:04:04.57,2:04:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,足以改变人生\N{\rE}It was life-changing.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:06.69,2:04:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们成功了 - 是的...哥们\N{\rE}- We did it. - We did. We did, man.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:11.03,2:04:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 现在1969年 对吧  我们在这个十年内做到了\N{\rE}Hey, it's 1969, right? We got it in before the decade.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:13.74,2:04:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是啊 踩着时间线呢 - 是的 我们成功了\N{\rE}I know. Not a moment to spare. - Oh. Yeah, we did.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:16.74,2:04:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 瞧那是谁 - 嘿\N{\rE}Look who it is. Hey.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:20.66,2:04:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- 去吧 走吧 - 好\N{\rE}- Go. Get out of here. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:24.79,2:04:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 你也不晚 小子\N{\rE}Listen, uh, it's not too late for you either, kid.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:28.71,2:04:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢你 亨利 - 好了\N{\rE}- Thank you, Henry. - All right.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:33.64,2:04:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿\N{\rE}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:36.93,2:04:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我们成功了\N{\rE}We did it.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:39.93,2:04:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨 孩子们\N{\rE}Hey, guys, huh?
Dialogue: 0,2:04:41.31,2:04:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,把人送上了月球\N{\rE}Sent a man to the moon.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:59.04,2:05:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗...\N{\rE}You know...
Dialogue: 0,2:05:05.71,2:05:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我还不知道你的名字呢\N{\rE}I never did catch your name.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:14.64,2:05:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,温妮\N{\rE}Winnie.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:18.47,2:05:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,温妮 很高兴认识你 温妮\N{\rE}Winnie. Nice to meet you, Winnie.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:24.48,2:05:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,苏联人说\N{\rE}You know, the Russians, they-- they're saying
Dialogue: 0,2:05:26.52,2:05:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,整个登月过程是我们在摄影棚里拍的\N{\rE}that we shot the whole thing on a soundstage.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:28.90,2:05:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,真不知道这种疯狂的想法是从哪来的\N{\rE}I wonder where they got a crazy idea like that.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:32.57,2:05:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,谁在乎他们怎么想啊\N{\rE}Who cares what they think?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:35.49,2:05:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,就算没人相信 真相依然是真相\N{\rE}Truth is still the truth even if nobody believes it.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:40.24,2:05:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,就算所有人都信 谎言依然是谎言\N{\rE}Lie is still a lie even if everybody believes it.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:45.58,2:05:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你这次做得真完美\N{\rE}You know, you really nailed this.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:49.42,2:05:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,连月尘都如此逼真\N{\rE}All the way down to the lunar dust.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:53.72,2:05:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,可惜都是假的\N{\rE}Too bad it's all fake.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:02.02,2:06:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,这是假的吗\N{\rE}Was that fake?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:05.19,2:06:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,不是 感觉非常真实\N{\rE}No, that felt very real.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:27.37,2:06:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,(政府财产 非请莫入)
Dialogue: 0,2:07:26.77,2:07:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,12 11 10 9...点火程序 5...\N{\rE}Twelve, eleven, ten, nine... Ignition sequence, five...
Dialogue: 0,2:11:29.72,2:11:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,字幕翻译:吴梦熊

